)@@G@@.                                     FOR THIS LEAD ITEM    @[@@@@.     YI
)@@G@@@G@@@@LINKERADD +         0                 SAVE LINK ADDRESS FROM DIRLNYJ
)@@G@@K     @F@@@@ENTRYINFO +         0                 SAVE OF ENTRY INFORMATYK

)@@G@@ET    @F@@@@BUFRADDR  EQUF      ENTRYINFO,,H2     ADDRESS OF USER'S BUFFYM

)@@G@@EX INTO LEAD ITEM @E@@@@.                                     SEC 0 OR 1YO
)@@G@@ (M.I. LINK)@[@@@@.     @E@@@@GOTONE*   +         0                 LEADYP
)@@G@@-ITEM-IN-CORE FLAG@G@@@@DIR$MFDF* +         0                 NONZERO IFYQ
)@@G@@ NEW DIRECOTRY FORMAT   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IOPAK     '$$--DGET--$$'      YR
)@@G@@        GENERAL DGET$ FILE I/O PACKET     @^@@@@          +         0   YS
)@@G@@@A@@@@          +         0,R$,0,0,0,0    @ @@@@          +         28,BYT
)@@G@@UF    @^@@@@          +         0   @ @@@@          ON        PRE33     YU
)@@G@@@D@@@@MCTPKT    +         0,MCTTBL          MCT$ PACKET     @G@@@@MASK1 YV
)@@G@@    +         037777777777      MASK FLAG BITS OUT OF ABSOLUTE    @F@@@@YW
)@@G@@.                                     WORD ADDRESSABLE ADDRESS    @ @@@@YX
)@@G@@          OFF       PRE33     @G@@@@MASK2     +         037777777700    YY
)@@G@@  MASK FLAG BITS OUT OF ABSOLUTE    @G@@@@.                             YZ
)@@G@@        ADDR AND TRUNCATE SECTOR ADDR     @F@@@@.                       ZA
)@@G@@              TO NEXT LOWERE TRACK ADDR.  @D@@@@ADDL      +         0   ZB
)@@G@@              LENGTH OF ADDTBL@G@@@@NXSEC     +         0               ZC

)@@G@@        TO BE ANALYZED BY DIRSEC    @F@@@@FIRSTR    +         0         ZE
)@@G@@        TRACK ADDRESS OF FIRST TRACK@G@@@@.                             ZF
)@@G@@        CONTAINING MFD ITEMS (AFTER LUT)  @G@@@@QSEC      +         0   ZG
)@@G@@              TOTAL SECTOR LENGTH OF DGET$ FILE @F@@@@DX        +       ZH
)@@G@@  0                 POINTER INTO 'BUF' WHICH    @G@@@@.                 ZI
)@@G@@                    CONATINS DAS, POINTING TO ENTRY   @E@@@@.           ZJ
)@@G@@                          FOR CURRENT TRACK.    @F@@@@RELADD    +       ZK
)@@G@@  0                 FOR NEW (MFDF) DIRECTORY    @F@@@@.                 ZL
)@@G@@                    ONLY WORD 0 OF FIRST DAS FOR@G@@@@.                 ZM
)@@G@@                    A GIVEN UNIT HAS PROPER LDAT INDEX@F@@@@.           ZN
)@@G@@                          AND SECTOR ADDRESS.  WE MUST@H@@@@.           ZO
)@@G@@                          KEEP TRACK OF THE RELATIVE ADDRESS.     @[@@@@ZP
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@MSCON$FN* .                           TO ALLOW CHANGING OF MZQ
)@@G@@SCON$ FUNCTION    @E@@@@MSPKT     +         DGET$             MSCON$ DGEZR
)@@G@@T$ PACKET   @D@@@@          '$$--DGET--$$'              DGET$ FILE NAME ZS
)@@G@@@G@@@@          +         DIRSIZ            NECESSARY RESERVE RETURNED HZT
)@@G@@ERE   @E@@@@          +         TRKBUF,TRKBUF2    BUFFERS FOR DGET$     ZU
)@@G@@@E@@@@PAKID$*   +         0                 PACK ID FOR DGETP$    @E@@@@ZV
)@@G@@SAVR2     RES       1                 REGISTER SAVE AREA    @^@@@@SAVX8 ZW
)@@G@@    RES       1   @^@@@@SAVX11    RES       1   @D@@@@SAVX11X   RES     ZX
)@@G@@  2                 INTERNAL SAVING @F@@@@LUFQF     +         0         ZY
)@@G@@        SAVE USER'S QUALFL ADDRESS  @G@@@@LBUF      RES       28        ZZ
)@@G@@        BUFFER FOR LEAD ITEM SECTOR 0     @F@@@@          +         0   AA
)@@G@@              MAIN ITEM LINK LOOP STOPPER @G@@@@L1BUF     RES       28  AB
)@@G@@              BUFFER FOR LEAD ITEM SECTOR 1     @E@@@@BUF       RES     AC
)@@G@@  28                DAS AND STAGING BUFFER@E@@@@TRKBUF    RES       1792AD
)@@G@@              FIRST DGET$ BUFFER    @G@@@@.                             AE
)@@G@@        ALSO USED DURING DIRSEC,DIRLNK TO @F@@@@.                       AF
)@@G@@              HOLD CURRENT DIRECTORY TRACK@E@@@@MCTSIZ    EQU       512*AG
)@@G@@(PRE33>0)     LENGTH OF MCT$ BUFFER @E@@@@LUTSIZ    EQU       28*LUTL   AH
)@@G@@        SIZE OF LUT BUFFER    @F@@@@LEFT      EQU      1792-(MCTSIZ+LUTSAI
)@@G@@IZ) REMAINDER OF TRACK BUFFER @B@@@@          DO MAXDIR<LEFT ,ADDSIZ EQUAJ
)@@G@@ LEFT @C@@@@          DO MAXDIR>LEFT-1 ,ADDSIZ EQU MAXDIR   @F@@@@TRKBUFAK
)@@G@@2   .                           SECOND DGET$ TRACK BUFFER   @D@@@@MCTTBLAL
)@@G@@    RES       MCTSIZ            MCT$ BUFFER     @E@@@@LUT       RES     AM
)@@G@@  LUTSIZ            LOOKUP TABLE BUFFER   @G@@@@ADDTBL    RES       ADDSAN
)@@G@@IZ            TABLE OF DIRECTORY TRACK ADDRESSES@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. LOOKAO
)@@G@@UP TABLE INFO     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@LUTSTART  EQU       1               AP
)@@G@@  FIRST LUT SECTOR IN DGET$ FILE    @E@@@@DCLUTS*   +         0         AQ
)@@G@@        LUT SIZE IN WORDS     @E@@@@LUTSECS   +         0               AR
)@@G@@  LUT SIZE IN SECTORS   @F@@@@NXLUTSEC  +         0                 NEXTAS
)@@G@@ LUT SECTOR FOR DIRLUT  @D@@@@LUTRD     '$$--DGET--$$'              LUT AT
)@@G@@I/O PACKET  @^@@@@          +         0   @A@@@@          +         0,R$AU
)@@G@@,0,0,0,0    @ @@@@          +         LUTSIZ,LUT@E@@@@          -       AV
)@@G@@  LUTL              INITIAL CALL INDICATOR@[@@@@.     @G@@@@LEDFLG    + AW
)@@G@@        0                 INDICATES LEAD ITEM WAS RETRIEVED @D@@@@.     AX
)@@G@@                                VIA DIRLED CALL.@ @@@@          ON      AY
)@@G@@  DIRSIZ>0  @E@@@@LOGMSG    '@LOG  DIREC$ MSG - DIRSIZ SHOULD BE INCREASAZ
)@@G@@ED . '@ @@@@          OFF       DIRSIZ>0  @^@@@@          ON        SNAPBA
)@@G@@@#@@@@NXSECSNP  'NXSEC '@A@@@@          +         0200005,NXSEC   @^@@@@BB
)@@G@@          +         0   @#@@@@ADDSNP    'ADDTBL'@ @@@@          +       BC
)@@G@@  0,ADDTBL  @^@@@@          +         0   @#@@@@DASSNP    'DAS   '@ @@@@BD
)@@G@@          +         28,BUF    @^@@@@          +         0   @#@@@@LUTSNPBE
)@@G@@    'LUT   '@ @@@@          +         LUTSIZ,LUT@^@@@@          +       BF
)@@G@@  0   @#@@@@          OFF     @]@@@@/$(LC$CODE).@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DIRFBG
)@@G@@IL - SETS DGET$ FILE NAME AS SOMETHING OTHER THAN $$--DGET--$$.   @[@@@@BH
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.      FORTRAN:   CALL DIRFIL (12HDGETFILENAME) @[@@@@.     BI
)@@G@@@C@@@@.      ASSEMBLY:  DL    A0,('DGETFILENAME')     @A@@@@.           BJ
)@@G@@      LMJ   X11,DIRFIL$ @A@@@@.                 <NORMAL RETURN>   @[@@@@BK
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.     THE INPUT PARAMETER MUST BE A 12-CHARACTER FIELDATA FIBL
)@@G@@LENAME,     @A@@@@.     LEFT-JUSTIFIED, SPACE-FILLED. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BM
)@@G@@FILARG    EQU       1                 NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@.     BN
)@@G@@@F@@@@DIRFIL*   LA        A2,(-1,FILARG)    # OF ARGS, NO ERROR RETURN  BO
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POIBP
)@@G@@NTS   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,*0,A0          LOAD FILENAME ADDRESS BQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DL        A0,,A0            LOAD THE FILENAME     @F@@@@BR
)@@G@@DIRFIL$*  DS        A0,IOPAK          STORE NEW NAME IN I/O PACKET@D@@@@BS
)@@G@@          DS        A0,MSPKT+1        AND MSCON PACKET@D@@@@          DSBT
)@@G@@        A0,CSFIM+2        AND CSF$ IMAGE  @E@@@@          DS        A0,LBU
)@@G@@UTRD          ALSO LUT I/O PACKET   @C@@@@          J         0,X11     BV
)@@G@@        RETURN    @E@@@@/. DIREND - FREES DGET$ FILE AND RE-INITIALIZES BW
)@@G@@DIREC$.     @F@@@@.           THE POINT OF THIS IS THAT DIREC$ TRIES TO BX
)@@G@@AVOID THE   @E@@@@.           OVERHEAD OF THE MSCON$/DGET$, WHERE POSSIBBY
)@@G@@LE, BY@F@@@@.           RETAINING THE COPY OF THE DIRECTORIES ACROSS SEVBZ
)@@G@@ERAL  @F@@@@.           EXECUTIONS.  THIS IS INAPPROPRIATE IN SOME CASESCA
)@@G@@:  YOU@G@@@@.           MAY EXECUTE SOMETHING USING DIREC$, THEN DO SOMECB
)@@G@@ @CAT'S     @F@@@@.           AND @DELETE'S, AND EXECUTE THE PROGRAM AGACC
)@@G@@IN TO SEE   @G@@@@.           THE CHANGES.  THAT WON'T WORK IF DIREC$ ISCD
)@@G@@ USING A COPY     @G@@@@.           OF THE DIRECTORIES FROM BEFORE THE CCE
)@@G@@HANGES.  IN THAT CASE,  @F@@@@.           CALLING DIREND THROWS AWAY THECF
)@@G@@ OLD COPY SO THAT A     @D@@@@.           SUBSEQUENT DIRINT WILL GET A NCG
)@@G@@EW COPY.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIREND  @[@@@@.     CH
)@@G@@@A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LMJ     X11,DIREND$@A@@@@.                <NORMALCI
)@@G@@ RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ENDARG    EQU       0                 NUMBCJ
)@@G@@ER OF ARGUMENTS (DUMMY) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIREND*   LA        A2,(-1,ENDCK
)@@G@@ARG)    # OF ARGS, NO ERROR RETURN  @G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK CL
)@@G@@        SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POINTS   @D@@@@DIREND$*  LA        A0,(CM
)@@G@@'@FREE ')     CHANGE CSFIM    @C@@@@          LA        A1,CSFIM        CN
)@@G@@  TO '@FREE'@E@@@@          SA        A0,CSFIM          AFTER SAVING 'ASCO
)@@G@@G,T'  @G@@@@          LA        A0,(4,CSFIM)      GET CSF$ IMAGE LENGTH CP
)@@G@@AND ADDR    @E@@@@          ER        CSF$              FREE THE DGET$ FCQ
)@@G@@ILE   @D@@@@          SA        A1,CSFIM          RESTORE 'ASG,T' @E@@@@CR
)@@G@@          SZ        NXSEC             ZERO DRUM ADDRESS     @D@@@@      CS
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             RETURN TO CALLER@G@@@@/. DIRINT - ASSIGNCT
)@@G@@S DGET$ FILE, OBTAINS A COPY OF THE DIRECTORIES, AND  @G@@@@.           CU
)@@G@@BUILDS ADDTBL.  IF FILE ALREADY EXISTS, JUST BUILDS ADDTBL. @[@@@@.     CV
)@@G@@@D@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRINT (ECODE,$ERR,MASK,FORK)   @[@@@@.     CW
)@@G@@@C@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,MASK   MASK BITS    @E@@@@.           CX
)@@G@@     LXI,U   A0,(FORK$ PARAMETER)  (OPTIONAL)   @A@@@@.                LCY
)@@G@@MJ     X11,DIRINT$@E@@@@.                <ERROR RETURN>    A1,A2 CONTAINCZ
)@@G@@ ERROR CODE @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@DA
)@@G@@.    MASK VALUES: (BITS MAY BE SET IN ANY COMBINATION)@[@@@@.     @G@@@@DB
)@@G@@.    LIBIT  = 002 - IF SET, DIRSEC WILL RETURN LEAD ITEMS (SECTOR 0)    DC
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    MIBIT  = 004 - IF SET, DIRSEC WILL RETURN MAIN ITEMS (SECTOR DD
)@@G@@0)    @G@@@@.    SEPBIT = 010 - IF SET, DIRSEC WILL PUT LEAD ITEMS IN BUDE
)@@G@@FFER ADDRESS@G@@@@.                   GIVEN IN DIRSEC CALL, AND MAIN ITEDF
)@@G@@MS IN BUFFER+28   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.      IF BOTH LIBIT AND MIBIT ARE SDG
)@@G@@ET, DIRSEC WILL RETRIEVE LEAD ITEMS @G@@@@.      AS WELL AS MAIN ITEMS. DH
)@@G@@FOR ASSEMBLY CALLS, A0 WILL CONTAIN 0 IF A@G@@@@.      LEAD ITEM WAS RETDI
)@@G@@URNED, OR 1 IF A MAIN ITEM WAS RETRUEND.  FOR   @G@@@@.      FOR FORTRANDJ
)@@G@@ CALLS, THIS VALUE WILL BE RETURNED IN ECODE (WITH A  @G@@@@.      NORMADK
)@@G@@L RETURN). IF YOU WANT TO MOVE ON TO THE NEXT LEAD ITEM     @G@@@@.     DL
)@@G@@ WITHOUT RETURNING ALL THE MAIN ITEMS FOR THE CURRENT LEAD ITEM,  @G@@@@DM
)@@G@@.      DIREC$'S EXTERNALIZED CELL 'GOTONE' SHOULD BE CLEARED BEFORE THE DN
)@@G@@@^@@@@.      NEXT DIRSEC CALL.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    FORK$ WORD - WHEN DDO
)@@G@@OING A DGET$, NO OTHER ACTIVITES MAY BE RUNNING.@G@@@@.    FOLLOWING THEDP
)@@G@@ DGET$, DIRINT MUST BUILD ADDTBL:  THIS TAKES A WHILE,@G@@@@.    SO IF YDQ
)@@G@@OU'D LIKE TO DO SOMETHING ELSE WHILE IT'S GOING ON, YOU MAY @G@@@@.    IDR
)@@G@@NDICATE SO WITH THE FORK$ WORD.  IF IT IS 0, IT WILL BE IGNORED,  @G@@@@DS
)@@G@@.    BUT IF IT IS NON-ZERO, DIRINT WILL DO AN ER FORK$ TO THE ADDRESS   DT
)@@G@@@C@@@@.    SPECIFIED, AFTER THE ACTUAL DGET$ IS DONE. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DU
)@@G@@.    IF A CALLING PROGRAM WISHES TO SEE THE REMOVABLE COPY OF     @F@@@@DV
)@@G@@.    DIRECTORIES FOR FILES ON A CURRENTLY MOUNTED REMOVABLE DISK, @F@@@@DW
)@@G@@.    THE FOLLOWING SEQUENCE WILL CHANGE DIRINT TO DO A DGETP$     @^@@@@DX
)@@G@@.    INSTEAD OF A DGET$:@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         L,U       A0,DGETP$ DY
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         S         A0,MSCON$FN       CHANGE FUNCTION TO DGETP$   DZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         L         A0,('PACKID')   @D@@@@.         S         A0,PEA
)@@G@@AKID$         STORE THE PACKID@F@@@@.         LMJ       X11,DIREND$     EB
)@@G@@  GET RID OF ANY DGET$ FILE   @D@@@@.         LA,U      A0,MASK         EC
)@@G@@  LOAD THE MASK   @C@@@@.         LMJ       X11,DIRINT$       DO DGETP$ ED
)@@G@@@#@@@@.         ...ETC. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    NOTE THAT 'LIBIT' MAY NOTEE
)@@G@@ BE SET FOR DGETP$, SINCE THE REMOVABLE   @F@@@@.    PACK DIRECTORY DOESEF
)@@G@@ NOT CONTAIN LEAD ITEMS.  'SEPBIT' WILL   @B@@@@.    BE IGNORED IN THIS EG
)@@G@@INSTANCE, ALSO.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@INTARG    EQU       4               EH
)@@G@@  NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@DIRINT*   LA,U      A2,INTARG EI
)@@G@@        # OF ARGUMENTS, WITH ERROR RETURN @G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FEJ
)@@G@@ORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POINTS   @F@@@@          LA,U    EK
)@@G@@  A3,*USERFORK,A0   POINT TO FORK$ PARAMETER    @E@@@@          LA      EL
)@@G@@  A3,,A3            LOAD FORK$ PARAMETER  @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,*EM
)@@G@@INTMASK,A0    POINT TO MASK BITS    @D@@@@          LA        A0,,A0    EN
)@@G@@        LOAD MASK BITS  @C@@@@          J         DIRINT2           CONTEO
)@@G@@INUE  @F@@@@DIRINT$*  SZ        FORPKT            DECLARE ASSEMBLY ENTRAEP
)@@G@@NCE   @E@@@@          LA        A3,A0             LOAD ENTRY PARAMETER  EQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SSL       A3,18             SHIFT TO GET FORK$ WORD     ER
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TZ        A3                IF THERE'S A FORK$ WORD,    ES
)@@G@@@C@@@@          LA        A3,,A3               GET IT @F@@@@          LXET
)@@G@@I,U     X11,,X11          LOAD ERROR RETURN POINT     @F@@@@          LXEU
)@@G@@M,U     X11,1,X11         LOAD NORMAL RETURN POINT    @E@@@@DIRINT2   SXEV
)@@G@@        X11,SAVX11        SAVE RETURN POINTS    @G@@@@          SZ      EW
)@@G@@  FLAGS             CLEAR SEP,WANTL,WANTM,INTERNAL,   @D@@@@.           EX
)@@G@@                          AND TRYCNT FLAGS@G@@@@          AND,U     A0,LEY
)@@G@@IBIT++MIBIT   MUST WANT EITHER LI'S OR MI'S     @E@@@@          JZ      EZ
)@@G@@  A1,BADMASK        IF NEITHER, MASK ERROR@F@@@@          LA        A1,MFA
)@@G@@SCON$FN       GET MSCON$ FUNCTION CODE    @C@@@@          TE,U      A1,DFB
)@@G@@GETP$         DGETP$ ?  @C@@@@          J         NOTDGETP          NO, FC
)@@G@@GO ON @D@@@@          SA        A0,DGETP          YES, SET FLAG   @F@@@@FD
)@@G@@          TEP,U     A0,LIBIT          DOES USER WANT LEAD ITEMS?  @F@@@@FE
)@@G@@          J         BADMASK           YES, WELL THERE AREN'T ANY! @G@@@@FF
)@@G@@          J         REASG             (NO) OK, SKIP SETTING OF FLAGS    FG
)@@G@@@]@@@@NOTDGETP  . @D@@@@          TEP,U     A0,LIBIT          WANT LEAD FH
)@@G@@ITEMS?@D@@@@          SA        A0,WANTL          YES, SET FLAG   @D@@@@FI
)@@G@@          TEP,U     A0,MIBIT          WANT MAIN ITEMS?@D@@@@          SAFJ
)@@G@@        A0,WANTM          YES, SET FLAG   @G@@@@          TEP,U     A0,SFK
)@@G@@EPBIT         BIT 3 SET FOR SEPARATE ITEMS?     @D@@@@          SA      FL
)@@G@@  A0,SEP            YES, SET FLAG   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PLUG INITIAL RESFM
)@@G@@ERVE INTO CSF$ IMAGE AND ASSIGN DGET$ FILE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@REASG     LAFN
)@@G@@        A0,MSPKT+3        GET INITIAL RESERVE   @F@@@@          JZ      FO
)@@G@@  A0,ZRO            IF ZERO, LEAVE IT ALONE     @D@@@@          SSL     FP
)@@G@@  A0,5              ADD ABOUT 3%    @G@@@@          TLE,U     A0,3      FQ
)@@G@@        AT LEAST 3 TRACKS BEING ADDED?    @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,2FR
)@@G@@              NO, ADD 2 TRACKS TO ACCOMODATE    @G@@@@          AA      FS
)@@G@@  A0,MSPKT+3        DYNAMIC EXPANSION, TO BE SAFE     @A@@@@ZRO       LAFT
)@@G@@        A2,('/     ')   @E@@@@CN        DSL       A0,36             CONVFU
)@@G@@ERT TO FD DECIMAL @ @@@@          DI,U      A0,10     @E@@@@          AAFV
)@@G@@,U      A1,'0'            CONVERT TO FIELDATA   @E@@@@          DSL     FW
)@@G@@  A1,6              LEFT-JUSTIFY IN A2    @ @@@@          JNZ       A0,CFX
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@          SA        A2,INTRES         STORE IN ASG IMAGE    FY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,U       A0,CSFIM          GET DGET$ FILE @ASG IMAGE   FZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ER        CSF$              @ASG,T OUR DGET$ FILE @F@@@@GA
)@@G@@          JNZ       A0,CSFR           IF NO GOOD, HANDLE ERROR    @[@@@@GB
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. OBTAIN COPY OF DIRECTORIES IN DGET$ FILE@[@@@@.     @C@@@@GC
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,MSPKT          DO DGET$  @ @@@@          ER      GD
)@@G@@  MSCON$    @D@@@@          JN        A0,MSCR           JUMP IF NO GOOD GE
)@@G@@@E@@@@DGETOK    L         A0,A3             WANNA FORK ANYTHING?  @D@@@@GF
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,$+2            IF NOT, GO ON   @C@@@@          ERGG
)@@G@@        FORK$             YES, DO IT@G@@@@          DO DEBUG>1 , SLJ TONGH
)@@G@@$       DEBUG MUST BE >1 FOR DIRINT TRACE @F@@@@          LA        A0,(GI
)@@G@@28,BUF)       SET TO READ SEC. 0 INTO BUF @ @@@@          SA        A0,IGJ
)@@G@@OPAK+4@G@@@@          SZ        IOPAK+5           INITIALIZE DGET$ DRUM GK
)@@G@@ADDR TO ZERO@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,IOPAK          LOAD I/O PACKET GL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ER        IOW$              READ FIRST SECTOR     @D@@@@GM
)@@G@@          TZ,S1     IOPAK+3           CHECK I/O STATUS@D@@@@          SLGN
)@@G@@J       IOR               HANDLE I/O ERROR@E@@@@          SZ        DIR$GO
)@@G@@MFDF          ASSUME OLD MFD FORMAT @F@@@@          TP        BUF+3     GP
)@@G@@        NEW MFD FILE (MFDF) FORMAT? @F@@@@          SA        A0,DIR$MFDGQ
)@@G@@F       YES, SET NEW-FORMAT FLAG    @ @@@@          ON        PRE33=0   GR
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TZ        DIR$MFDF          CORRECT FORMAT DGET$ FILE?  GS
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         $+3               YES, GO ON@E@@@@          LAGT
)@@G@@,U      A1,MFDFERR        NO, GET ERROR TYPE    @F@@@@          J       GU
)@@G@@  ERREXT1           RETURN ERROR TYPE TO USER   @ @@@@          OFF     GV
)@@G@@  PRE33=0   @E@@@@          L,H1      A0,BUF+2          FIRST DIR TRK NUGW
)@@G@@MBER  @G@@@@          AN,U      A0,1              CONVERT TO LOGICAL TRAGX
)@@G@@CK NUMBER   @E@@@@          S         A0,FIRSTR         SAVE ADDR OF FIRGY
)@@G@@ST TRK@G@@@@          L,H2      A0,BUF+2          GET # OF DIRECTORY TRAGZ
)@@G@@CKS WRITTEN @F@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              CONVERT TO # OF HA
)@@G@@SECTORS     @F@@@@          S         A0,QSEC           STORE # OF SECTOHB
)@@G@@RS WRITTEN  @F@@@@          LA,H2     A0,BUF+1          GET LENGTH OF LOHC
)@@G@@OKUP TABLE  @F@@@@          SA        A0,DCLUTS         STORE FOR DIRLUWHD
)@@G@@/DIRLUT     @D@@@@          DSL       A0,36             SET FOR DIVIDE  HE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DI,U      A0,28             CONVERT TO SECTOR COUNT     HF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TZ        A1                ANY REMAINDER?  @E@@@@      HG
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              YES, BUMP COUNT BY 1  @F@@@@          A,HH
)@@G@@U       A0,1              BUMP ANOTHER ONE FOR TESTS  @F@@@@          SAHI
)@@G@@        A0,LUTSECS        STORE # OF SECS+1 FOR DIRLUT@F@@@@          LMHJ
)@@G@@J       A1,RESET          INITIALIZE NXSEC, DX, ETC.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@HK
)@@G@@. DIRLNK PROVIDES THE ABILITY TO ACCEPT A DIRECTORY LINK ADDRESS  @F@@@@HL
)@@G@@. (EG, LINK-TO-SECTOR-1-OF-MAIN-ITEM) AND RETRIEVE THE ITEM IT    @F@@@@HM
)@@G@@. POINTS TO.  IN ORDER TO DO THIS, IT MUST TRANSLATE THE LINK     @F@@@@HN
)@@G@@. ADDRESS WHICH POINTS TO THE ACTUAL MFD ITEM INTO A RELATIVE     @F@@@@HO
)@@G@@. ADDRESS THAT POINTS TO THE COPY OF THAT ITEM IN THE DGET$ FILE. @B@@@@HP
)@@G@@. IT MAKES USE OF TWO FACTS TO DO THIS:   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    1. THE HQ
)@@G@@MFD IS COPIED TO THE DGET$ FILE TRACK BY TRACK. @F@@@@.       THEREFORE,HR
)@@G@@ IF A GIVEN ITEM STARTS AT SECTOR 49 OR WORD    @G@@@@.       1372 WITHIHS
)@@G@@N SOME GIVEN TRACK OF THE MFD, THEN IT WILL START     @F@@@@.       AT SHT
)@@G@@ECTOR 49 OR WORD 1372 OF THE COPY OF THAT TRACK IN    @G@@@@.       OUR HU
)@@G@@DGET$ FILE.  ALL WE NEED TO DO IS FIND THE RIGHT TRACK.     @G@@@@.    2HV
)@@G@@. THE DGET$ FILE CONTAINS COPIES OF EACH DIRECTORY ALLOCATION     @G@@@@HW
)@@G@@.       SECTOR (DAS).  THE DAS CONTAINS THE ADDRESS OF THE MFD TRACK    HX
)@@G@@@G@@@@.       FROM WHICH IT WAS COPIED, AS WELL AS THE MFD ADDRESSES FROHY
)@@G@@M     @E@@@@.       WHICH THE NEXT FEW (UP TO 8) TRACKS WERE COPIED.    HZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DURING THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE, WE READ EVERY DAS IN TIA
)@@G@@HE DGET$ FILE.    @G@@@@. FROM EACH ONE WE PULL OUT THE MFD ADDRESS OF EIB
)@@G@@ACH TRACK DESCRIBED IN  @G@@@@. THE DAS.  THESE ARE BUILT INTO A TABLE CIC
)@@G@@ALLED ADDTBL.  POSITION IN    @F@@@@. ADDTBL INDICATES POSITION IN THE DID
)@@G@@GET$ FILE (EG, THE 7TH WORD OF@F@@@@. ADDTBL CONTAINS THE MFD ADDRESS FRIE
)@@G@@OM WHICH MSCON$ COPIED THE 7TH@G@@@@. TRACK OF DIRECTORY ITEMS INTO THE IF
)@@G@@DGET$ FILE).  NOTE THAT THIS IS     @G@@@@. ALL ZERO-RELATIVE.  ALSO NOTIG
)@@G@@E THAT TRACK ZERO OF THE DGET$ FILE IS    @F@@@@. NOT TRACK ZERO OF DIREIH
)@@G@@CTORY ITEMS:  THE BEGINNING OF THE DGET$  @F@@@@. FILE CONSISTS OF A TABII
)@@G@@LE OF CONTENTS AND THE LOOKUP TABLE.  THE @F@@@@. TRACK NUMBER OF THE FIIJ
)@@G@@RST TRACK IN THE DGET$ FILE WHICH CONTAINS@F@@@@. DIRECTORY ITEMS IS RETIK
)@@G@@URNED BY MSCON$, IN WORD 2,,H1 OF SECTOR 0@F@@@@. OF THE FILE.  THIS IS IL
)@@G@@THE TRACK WHICH WAS COPIED FROM THE MFD   @C@@@@. LOCATION WHOSE ADDRESSIM
)@@G@@ IS IN WORD 0 OF ADDTBL.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. AFTER INITIALIZATION IS COMPIN
)@@G@@LETE, CALLS MAY BE MADE TO DIRLNK TO@E@@@@. READ A SECTOR CORRESPONDING IO
)@@G@@TO A GIVEN MFD (LINK) ADDRESS.@G@@@@. FIRST WE SEARCH ADDTBL TO FIND THEIP
)@@G@@ ADDRESS OF A TRACK WHICH WOULD     @F@@@@. CONTAIN THE ADDRESS WE ARE LIQ
)@@G@@OOKING FOR.  THE INDEX INTO ADDTBL  @F@@@@. IS THE RELATIVE TRACK NUMBERIR
)@@G@@ IN THE DGET$ FILE FOR THE FIND.    @F@@@@. THE OFFSET INTO THE TRACK ISIS
)@@G@@ DETERMINED FROM THE DIFFERENCE     @G@@@@. BETWEEN THE ADDRESS WE ARE LIT
)@@G@@OOKING FOR AND THE MFD ADDRESS OF THE     @F@@@@. TRACK IT IS IN (FROM AIU
)@@G@@DDTBL).  THIS OFFSET INTO THE TRACK IN THE@A@@@@. DGET$ FILE GIVES THE IIV
)@@G@@TEM WE WANT.@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.                                     DWIGIW
)@@G@@HT ARTHUR   @D@@@@.                                     BOSTON, MAY 1976IX

)@@G@@  POINT TO FIRST WORD OF DAS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. PICK UP NEXT DIRECTORYKC
)@@G@@ TRACK ADDRESS FROM DAS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@GETTRACK  LA        A0,BUF,A2 KD
)@@G@@        GET DIRECTORY TRACK ADDR FROM DAS @E@@@@          JN        A0,SKE

)@@G@@T       GOOD TRACK: JUMP IF NEW-UNIT CLEAR@F@@@@          SA        A0,RKG
)@@G@@ELADD         SAVE 1ST REL ADDR ON UNIT   @G@@@@.                       KH
)@@G@@              ONLY RELEVANT FOR MFDF FORMAT,    @G@@@@.                 KI
)@@G@@                    BUT ALWAYS DOING IT SAVES A TEST  @ @@@@          ONKJ
)@@G@@        PRE33     @F@@@@          AA        A0,(0400000,0)    MARK AS POKK
)@@G@@SSIBLE SHORT TRACK@ @@@@          OFF       PRE33     @E@@@@          LAKL
)@@G@@,U      A3,0              CLEAR NEW-UNIT FLAG   @C@@@@          J       KM
)@@G@@  STORETRK          GO ON     @]@@@@SAMEUNIT  . @ @@@@          ON      KN
)@@G@@  PRE33     @G@@@@          TNZ       DIR$MFDF          SAME UNIT: NEW FKO
)@@G@@ORMAT ADDRESS?    @G@@@@          J         STORETRK          NO, USE ABKP
)@@G@@SOLUTE ADDRESS, AS IS   @ @@@@          OFF       PRE33     @G@@@@      KQ
)@@G@@    LA        A0,RELADD         YES, GET LAST REL ADDR THIS UNIT  @E@@@@KR
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,0100           BUMP FOR THIS TRACK   @D@@@@      KS
)@@G@@    SA        A0,RELADD         UPDATE RELADD   @G@@@@STORETRK  S       KT
)@@G@@  A0,ADDTBL,*A1     STORE DIR TRACK ADDR IN ADDTBL    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@KU
)@@G@@. ANY TRACKS FOUND IN A DAS WILL NOT HAVE DAS'S IN SECTOR 0,@H@@@@. SO BKV
)@@G@@UMP DRUM ADDRESS OF NEXT EXPECTED DAS TRACK FOR EACH TRACK WE FIND.     KW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@          L         A0,IOPAK+5        GET DRUM ADDRESSKX
)@@G@@@G@@@@          A,U       A0,0100           BUMP ADDR OF NEXT TRACK WITHKY
)@@G@@ DAS  @E@@@@          S         A0,IOPAK+5        UPDATE DRUM ADDRESS   KZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         NEXTTRACK         GET NEXT TRACK FROM DAS     LA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. AN EMPTY DAS TRACK ENTRY HAS BEEN ENCOUNTERED - SKIPLB
)@@G@@ IT   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SKIPTRACK LA        A0,RELADD         ACCOUNT FOLC
)@@G@@R MISSING TRACK IN MFDF @G@@@@          AA,U      A0,0100           RELALD
)@@G@@TIVE ADDRESSING STRUCTURE.    @G@@@@          SA        A0,RELADD       LE
)@@G@@  (RELEVANT ONLY MFDF FORMAT, BUT   @G@@@@.                             LF
)@@G@@        ALWAYS DOING IT SAVES A TEST).    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. INCREMENT LG
)@@G@@A2 (INDEX INTO DAS) AND GO GET NEXT TRACK ENTRY.@F@@@@. IF WE'VE REACHEDLH
)@@G@@ THE END OF A DAS, GO GET THE NEXT ONE.  IF NO  @B@@@@. MORE EXIST, INITLI
)@@G@@IALIZATION IS COMPLETE. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NEXTTRACK TLEM,U    A2,24     LJ
)@@G@@        REACHED 8TH TRACK IN DAS YET?     @F@@@@          J         GETTLK
)@@G@@RACK          NO, CONTINUE WITH THIS DAS  @G@@@@          TZ        BUF,LL
)@@G@@A2            YES, IS LINK-TO-NEXT-DAS ZERO     @G@@@@          TP      LM
)@@G@@  BUF,A2               OR NEGATIVE? (LOWER A2=27 HERE)@F@@@@          LALN
)@@G@@,U      A3,1              IF SO, SET NEW-UNIT FLAG    @F@@@@          L LO
)@@G@@        A0,IOPAK+5        ADDR OF NEXT EXPECTED DAS   @F@@@@          TLLP
)@@G@@E       A0,QSEC           HAVE WE REACHED THE END?    @E@@@@          J LQ
)@@G@@        GETDAS            NO, READ NEXT DAS     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. INITLR
)@@G@@IALIZATION IS COMPLETE - STORE ADDTBL LENGTH, AND RETURN    @[@@@@.     LS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA,H2     A1,ADDL           STORE ADDTBL LENGTH   @^@@@@LT
)@@G@@          ON        SNAP@F@@@@          SA,H1     A1,ADDSNP+1       STORLU
)@@G@@E # OF WORDS TO SNAP    @C@@@@          LA,U      A0,ADDSNP         SNAPLV
)@@G@@$ PKT @D@@@@          ER        SNAP$             SNAP ADDTBL     @#@@@@LW
)@@G@@          OFF     @E@@@@          LX        X11,SAVX11        LOAD RETURLX
)@@G@@N ADDRESS   @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TOFF$    @E@@@@          J LY
)@@G@@        0,X11             TAKE NORMAL RETURN    @E@@@@/. DIRSEC - GETS TLZ
)@@G@@HE NEXT DESIRED ITEM FROM THE DGET$ FILE. @E@@@@.           THE TYPE OF MA
)@@G@@ITEM TO BE RETURNED IS DETERMINED BY@B@@@@.           THE MASK PASSED TOMB
)@@G@@ DIRINT.    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRSEC (ECODE,$ERR,BMC
)@@G@@UFF)  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,BUFF    @A@@@@.     MD
)@@G@@           LMJ     X11,DIRSEC$@F@@@@.                <ERROR/EOF RETURN> ME
)@@G@@  A1,A2 CONTAINS ERROR CODE   @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURN>    MF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DIRSEC SCANS ALL DIRECTORY TRACKS IN THE DGET$ FILE MG
)@@G@@SEQUENTIALLY.     @H@@@@. NXSEC HOLDS THE ADDRESS OF THE NEXT SECTOR IN MH
)@@G@@THE DGET$ FILE TO BE READ.    @G@@@@. IF IT IS THE FIRST SECTOR IN A TRAMI
)@@G@@CK, WE READ THAT TRACK INTO TRKBUF. @F@@@@. WE THEN CHECK EACH ALLOCATEDMJ
)@@G@@ SECTOR IN THE TRACK TO DETERMINE   @H@@@@. WHETHER IT IS THE TYPE OF SEMK
)@@G@@CTOR THE USER WANTS.  IF SO, WE GIVE IT TO HIM. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WHENML
)@@G@@ THE END OF THE DGET$ FILE IS ENCOUNTERED, WE USE AN ERROR RETURN,@A@@@@MM
)@@G@@. AND GIVE THE USER AN EOF STATUS.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DIRLED MAY OPTIOMN
)@@G@@NALLY BE USED TO POINT DIRSEC AT A PARTICULAR LEAD    @H@@@@. ITEM.  IN MO
)@@G@@THIS CASE, SUCCESSIVE DIRSEC CALLS WILL RETURN THE MAIN ITEMS     @G@@@@MP
)@@G@@. ASSOCIATED WITH THAT LEAD ITEM ONLY.  WHEN NO MORE MAIN ITEMS ARE     MQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. FOUND, THE EOF STATUS IS RETURNED AND DIRSEC REVERTS TO NORMAL  MR
)@@G@@@#@@@@. SEARCHING MODE. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SECARG    EQU       3         MS
)@@G@@        NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIRSEC*   LA,U      A2,SMT
)@@G@@ECARG         # OR ARGS, WITH ERROR RETURN@G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FMU
)@@G@@ORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POINTS   @E@@@@          LA,U    MV
)@@G@@  A0,*USERBUFAD,A0  GET BUFFER ADDRESS    @C@@@@          J         DIRSMW
)@@G@@EC2           CONTINUE  @E@@@@DIRSEC$*  SZ        FORPKT            CLEAMX
)@@G@@R FORTRAN CELL    @E@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11          LOAD ERRORMY
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @E@@@@          LXM,U     X11,1,X11         NORMAL RETURN POMZ
)@@G@@INT   @C@@@@DIRSEC2   SX        X11,SAVX11        STORE X11 @A@@@@      NA
)@@G@@    DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TON$     @E@@@@          SA        A0,BUFRADDR     NB
)@@G@@  SAVE BUFFER ADDRESS   @G@@@@          TZ        GOTONE            ARE NC
)@@G@@WE RETRIEVING MAIN ITEMS (IN  @G@@@@.                                   ND
)@@G@@  WHICH CASE LEAD ITEM IS INCORE) ? @F@@@@          J         GTMITM    NE
)@@G@@        YES, GET NEXT MAIN ITEM FOR @D@@@@.                             NF
)@@G@@        THIS LEAD ITEM. @F@@@@          SZ        LEDFLG            NO, NG
)@@G@@BE SURE LEDFLG IS CLEAR @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WE ARE LOOKING FOR THE NEXT NH
)@@G@@LEAD ITEM (OR MAIN ITEM, IF DGETP$) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIRSC1    L       NI
)@@G@@  A2,NXSEC          GET ADDR OF NEXT SECTOR     @F@@@@          TNZ     NJ
)@@G@@  A2                ERROR IF NOT INITIALIZED    @ @@@@          SLJ     NK
)@@G@@  NOTINT    @E@@@@          TG        A2,QSEC           BEYOND LAST SECTNL
)@@G@@OR?   @F@@@@          J         EOF               YES, RETURN WITH EOF SNM
)@@G@@TATUS @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF ADDRESS IS SECTOR 0 OF A TRACK, WE MUST REANN
)@@G@@D IN THAT TRACK   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          AND,U     A2,077          NO
)@@G@@  FIRST SECTOR IN TRACK?@G@@@@          JNZ       A3,HAVETRACK      NO,HNP
)@@G@@AVETRACK   YES,READ TRACK     @E@@@@          LA        A1,(1792,TRKBUF)NQ
)@@G@@  SET ACW AND DRUM ADDR @D@@@@          DS        A1,IOPAK+4           INR
)@@G@@N I/O PACKET@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,IOPAK          READ THE TRACK  NS
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ER        IOW$@C@@@@          TZ,S1     IOPAK+3         NT
)@@G@@  IO OK?    @E@@@@          SLJ       IOR               NOPE, RETURN IO NU
)@@G@@STATUS@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. DX POINTS TO THE ENTRY WITHIN A DAS FOR THE CUNV
)@@G@@RRENT TRACK SO THAT DIRSEC    @H@@@@. CAN CHECK THE SECTOR ALLOCATION BINW
)@@G@@TS FOR THE TRACK.  SINCE WE JUST READ     @F@@@@. IN A NEW TRACK, WE MUSNX
)@@G@@T FIND THE ENTRY IN THE CURRENT DAS WHICH @H@@@@. CORRESPONDS TO THE NEWNY
)@@G@@ TRACK. IF WE HAVE REACHED THE END OF THE CURRENT DAS,@G@@@@. OUR NEW TRNZ
)@@G@@ACK HAS A DAS IN SECTOR 0, SO WE MUST MOVE THAT INTO OUR    @F@@@@. CURROA
)@@G@@ENT-DAS BUFFER, BUF.   NOTE THAT DX IS INITIALIZED TO BUF+24@D@@@@. TO FOB
)@@G@@ORCE THIS ACTION ON THE INITIAL DIRSEC CALL.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NEWDX OC
)@@G@@    L         A0,DX             GET CURRENT INDEX INTO DAS  @F@@@@.     OD
)@@G@@                                WHICH IS SITTING IN BUF     @F@@@@      OE
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,3              INCREMENT TO NEXT TRACK DESC@F@@@@      OF
)@@G@@    TG,U      A0,BUF+27         REACHED END OF CURRENT DAS? @F@@@@      OG
)@@G@@    J         BTDAS             YES, MOVE NEW DAS INTO BUF  @G@@@@      OH
)@@G@@    S         A0,DX             NO, SET NEW INDEX IN CURRENT DAS  @F@@@@OI
)@@G@@          L         A1,0,A0           GET TRACK ADDR FROM DAS     @E@@@@OJ
)@@G@@          JZ        A1,NEWDX          IF ZERO, TRY ANOTHER  @F@@@@      OK
)@@G@@    JN        A1,NEWDX             ALSO IF TRACK UNALLOCATED@E@@@@      OL
)@@G@@    J         HAVETRACK         HAVE A GOOD TRACK     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@OM
)@@G@@. MUST GET NEW DAS FROM THE DIRECTORY TRACK WE JUST READ IN @[@@@@.     ON
)@@G@@@F@@@@BTDAS     LA        A0,(1,BUF)        SET DAS ENTRY INDEX TO 0    OO
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA,H2     A0,DX                (FIRST ENTRY DESCRIBES SEOP
)@@G@@LF)   @F@@@@          LR,U      R1,28             SET FOR 28-WORD BT OF OQ
)@@G@@DAS   @E@@@@          LA        A1,(1,TRKBUF)     FROM TRKBUF TO BUF    OR
)@@G@@@C@@@@          BT        A0,0,*A1          DO IT     @G@@@@          J OS
)@@G@@        BUMP1             THE ADDRESS GIVEN WAS A DAS, SO   @H@@@@.     OT
)@@G@@                                BUMP NXSEC AND SEARCH FOR LEAD ITEM.    OU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. AT THIS POINT, A2 CONTAINS SECTOR ADDRESS, AND DX   OV
)@@G@@@D@@@@. POINTS TO TRACK INDEX IN CURRENT-DAS BUFFER (BUF).  @[@@@@.     OW
)@@G@@@G@@@@HAVETRACK SSC       A2,5              POSITION ADDRESS TO DETERMINOX
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@.                                     WHICH 32-SECTOR ALLOCAOY
)@@G@@TION  @F@@@@.                                     WORD IN DAS IS APPLICAOZ
)@@G@@BLE.  @F@@@@          AND,U     A2,1              SET UP A3 AS INDEX TO PA
)@@G@@1ST OR@G@@@@.                                        2ND SECTOR ALLOCATIPB
)@@G@@ON WORD     @G@@@@          A         A3,DX             FOLLOWING TRACK PC
)@@G@@ADDRESS IN DAS    @F@@@@          SSL       A2,31             GET SECTORPD
)@@G@@ NUMBER MOD 32    @G@@@@          L         A0,1,A3           GET BIT MAPE
)@@G@@SK FOR THESE 32 SECTORS @F@@@@          LSSL      A0,0,A2           ISOLPF
)@@G@@ATE BIT FOR THIS SECTOR @ @@@@          ON        SNAP>1    @A@@@@      PG
)@@G@@    S         A0,NXSECSNP+2   @A@@@@          L,U       A0,NXSECSNP     PH
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ER        SNAP$     @#@@@@          OFF     @H@@@@      PI
)@@G@@    JP        A0,BUMP1          IF BIT CLEAR, THIS SECTOR NOT IN USE    PJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A2,NXSEC          IN USE - GET ADDR     @E@@@@PK
)@@G@@          AND,U     A2,077            ISOLATE SECTOR NUMBER @E@@@@      PL
)@@G@@    MSI,U     A3,28             CONVERT TO WORD INDEX @F@@@@          L PM
)@@G@@        A0,TRKBUF,A3      GET FIRST WORD OF SECTOR    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@PN
)@@G@@. DIRECTORY HOUSEKEEPING MAY LEAVE SHREDS OF MAIN ITEMS LYING AROUND WITPO
)@@G@@H     @H@@@@. DAS BITS SAYING THEY'RE IN USE.  THEREFORE, WE HAVE TO SEAPP
)@@G@@RCH THE DGET$     @G@@@@. FILE IGNORING MAIN ITEMS, AND SNAGGING ONLY LEPQ
)@@G@@AD ITEMS.  IF THE USER  @G@@@@. WANTS MAIN ITEMS, WE'LL HAVE TO MAKE INTPR
)@@G@@ERNAL CALLS ON DIRLNK TO GET  @G@@@@. THEM, FEEDING IT LINKS FROM THE LEPS
)@@G@@AD ITEM. THIS HAS ITS ADVANTAGES:   @F@@@@. AT LEAST THIS WAY WE GROUP APT
)@@G@@LL THE F-CYCLES OF A FILE TOGETHER. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LA      PU
)@@G@@  A1,(1*/33)        SET TO CHECK FOR L.I. SEC 0 @C@@@@          TZ      PV
)@@G@@  DGETP             DGETP$ ?  @F@@@@          LSSL      A1,1            PW
)@@G@@  YES, CHECK FOR M.I. SEC 0   @F@@@@          AND       A0,A1           PX
)@@G@@  CORRECT TYPE OF SECTOR?     @D@@@@          JZ        A1,BUMP1        PY
)@@G@@  NO,BUMP1   YES  @F@@@@          TNZ       WANTM             DOES USER PZ
)@@G@@WANT MAIN ITEMS?  @F@@@@          J         GTLITM            NO, JUST GQA
)@@G@@IVE HIM LEAD ITEM @A@@@@          L         A0,(1,TRKBUF)   @F@@@@      QB
)@@G@@    AU        A0,A3             A1 = (1,TRKBUF+ITEMADDR)    @ @@@@      QC
)@@G@@    LXM,U     A0,LBUF   @D@@@@          L,U       R1,28             BLOCQD
)@@G@@K TRANSFER  @G@@@@          BT        A0,0,*A1          LITM TO LBUF FORQE
)@@G@@ FINDING MITMS    @G@@@@          LA        A0,(1,LBUF+11)    SET INITIAQF
)@@G@@L INDEX INTO LEAD ITEM 0@F@@@@          SA        A0,LINDEX         FOR QG
)@@G@@FINDING MAIN ITEM LINKS @E@@@@          S         A0,GOTONE         MARKQH
)@@G@@ LITM IN CORE     @E@@@@          SZ        LFLAG             CLEAR GOTLQI
)@@G@@1, HMANY    @D@@@@          TNZ       WANTL             USER WANTS LITM?QJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         GTMITM            NO, GO GET HIM A MITM @[@@@@QK
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. TRANSFER LEAD ITEM 0 TO USER'S BUFFER   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@QL
)@@G@@GTLITM    AA,U      A2,1              BUMP SECTOR ADDRESS   @H@@@@      QM
)@@G@@    SA        A2,NXSEC          UPDATE ADDRESS OF NEXT SECTOR TO READ   QN
)@@G@@@H@@@@          AA        A3,(1,TRKBUF)     POINT TO LEAD ITEM SECTOR INQO
)@@G@@ TRKBUF     @F@@@@GTLITM2   LA        A0,BUFRADDR       GET USER'S BUFFEQP
)@@G@@R ADDRESS   @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1              SET INCREMENT FOQQ
)@@G@@R BT  @ @@@@          LR,U      R1,28     @F@@@@          BT        A0,0QR
)@@G@@,*A3          BT LEAD ITEM TO USER BUFFER @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,0QS
)@@G@@              SET LEAD-ITEM FLAG, AND     @D@@@@          TNZ       FORPQT
)@@G@@KT            FORTRAN CALL ?  @B@@@@          J         DNOTFOR         QU
)@@G@@  NOPE@E@@@@          LA        A0,FORPKT         LOAD PACKET ADDRESS   QV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA,U      A0,*ECODE,A0      POINT TO ECODE CELL   @D@@@@QW
)@@G@@          SZ        0,A0              CLEAR ERROR CODE@E@@@@          SZQX
)@@G@@        ECODE,A0          SET LEAD ITEM FLAG    @E@@@@DNOTFOR   LX      QY
)@@G@@  X11,SAVX11        LOAD RETURN ADDRESS   @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SQZ
)@@G@@LJ TOFF$    @C@@@@          J         0,X11             RETURN    @[@@@@RA
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. USER WANTS MAIN ITEMS, SO LET'S FIND THEM USING LINKS FROMRB
)@@G@@ LEAD ITEM  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@GTMITM    L         A0,HMANY          HOW RC
)@@G@@MANY MITM'S PASSED SO FAR     @F@@@@          TG,S4     A0,LBUF+9       RD
)@@G@@  ANY MORE IN THIS LEAD ITEM? @E@@@@          J         NOMORM1         RE
)@@G@@  NO, GET NEXT LEAD ITEM@F@@@@          A,U       A0,1              YES,RF
)@@G@@ SHOW WE PASSED 1 MORE  @ @@@@          S         A0,HMANY  @G@@@@      RG
)@@G@@    LA        A0,LINDEX         PICK UP POINTER TO MAIN ITEM LINK @F@@@@RH
)@@G@@          TZ        GOTL1             LEAD ITEE SECTOR 1 INCORE?  @G@@@@RI
)@@G@@          J         LIT1              YES, FIND MAIN ITEM LINKS THERE   RJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@LIT0      TZ        0,A0              FIND NEXT LINK  @E@@@@      RK
)@@G@@    J         GOTMILINK         GOOD LINK: HANDLE IT  @F@@@@          TLRL
)@@G@@EM,U    A0,LBUF+27        END OF LEAD ITEM SECTOR 0?  @D@@@@          J RM
)@@G@@        LIT0              NO, KEEP GOING  @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,LRN
)@@G@@1BUF          STUFF LEAD ITEM SEC 1 IN L1BUF    @F@@@@          LA      RO
)@@G@@  A1,LBUF           USE LBUF+0 AS LINK WORD     @ @@@@          ON      RP
)@@G@@  DEBUG     @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,1              MARK AS INTERNALRQ
)@@G@@ CALL @D@@@@          SA        A2,INTERNAL          ON DIRLNK$   @#@@@@RR
)@@G@@          OFF     @E@@@@          LA        A2,SAVX11         LOAD USER'RS
)@@G@@S RETURN    @D@@@@          LA        A3,ENTRYINFO      LOAD THE REST   RT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DS        A2,SAVX11X        HOLD IT FOR NOW @E@@@@      RU
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,DIRLNK$       GET LEAD ITEM SECTOR 1@G@@@@          J RV
)@@G@@        NOMORM            IF ERROR, FORGET THIS LEAD ITEM   @E@@@@      RW
)@@G@@    DL        A2,SAVX11X        LOAD USER'S RETURN    @C@@@@          SARX
)@@G@@        A2,SAVX11         REPLACE IT@E@@@@          SA        A3,ENTRYINRY
)@@G@@FO      REPLACE SOME MORE     @^@@@@          LA,U      A0,1@G@@@@      RZ
)@@G@@    SA        A0,GOTL1          SET LEAD-ITEM-SEC-1-INCORE FLAG   @G@@@@SA
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(1,L1BUF+1)    SET INDEX INTO LEAD ITEM SEC 1    SB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A0,LINDEX            FOR FIRST MAIN ITEM LINK SC
)@@G@@@D@@@@LIT1      TZ        0,A0              LOOK FOR LINK   @C@@@@      SD
)@@G@@    J         GOTMILINK         GOT LINK  @G@@@@          TLEM,U    A0,LSE
)@@G@@1BUF+15       REACHED END OF LEAD ITEM SEC 1?   @E@@@@          J       SF
)@@G@@  LIT1              NO, TRY NEXT LINK     @F@@@@          J         NOMOSG
)@@G@@RM1           YES, FORGET THIS LEAD ITEM  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ERROR RETUSH
)@@G@@RN FROM INTERNAL DIRLNK$ CALL @[@@@@.     @D@@@@NOMORM    DL        A2,SSI
)@@G@@AVX11X        LOAD SAVED STUFF@D@@@@          SA        A2,SAVX11       SJ
)@@G@@  RESTORE RETURNS @D@@@@          SA        A3,ENTRYINFO      AND OTHER SK
)@@G@@STUFF @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. END OF MAIN ITEM LINKS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@NOMORMSL
)@@G@@1   TZ        LEDFLG            ARE WE DOING A SINGLE LEAD ITEM?  @E@@@@SM
)@@G@@          J         EOF               YES, TREAT AS EOF     @D@@@@      SN
)@@G@@    SZ        LFLAG             GOTL1,HMANY=0   @E@@@@          SZ      SO
)@@G@@  GOTONE            CLEAR LINCOR FLAG     @G@@@@          J         DIRSSP
)@@G@@C1            NO, SEARCH FOR NEXT LEAD ITEM     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. UPDASQ
)@@G@@TE NXSEC AND FIND NEXT LEAD ITEM    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BUMP1     L       SR
)@@G@@  A2,NXSEC          POINT TO NEXT SECTOR  @^@@@@          A,U       A2,1SS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          S         A2,NXSEC  @E@@@@          J         DIRSC1    ST
)@@G@@        LOOK FOR A LEAD ITEM  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@. HAVE LINK TO MAIN ITEMSU
)@@G@@ SECTOR 0 - USE INTERNAL DIRLNK CALL TO GET IT FOR USER     @[@@@@.     SV
)@@G@@@F@@@@GOTMILINK L         A1,0,*A0          PICK UP LINK TO MAIN ITEM   SW
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                                     AND INCREMENT LINK WORD POINSX
)@@G@@TER   @G@@@@          SA        A0,LINDEX         UPDATE LEAD ITEM INDEXSY
)@@G@@ POINTER    @E@@@@          LA        A0,BUFRADDR       GET USER'S BUFFESZ
)@@G@@R ADDR@F@@@@          TZ        SEP               SEPARATE LI/MI BUFFERSTA
)@@G@@?     @E@@@@          A,U       A0,28             YES, PUT MI IN BUFF+28TB
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        DEBUG     @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,1      TC
)@@G@@        MARK AS INTERNAL CALL @D@@@@          SA        A2,INTERNAL     TD
)@@G@@     ON DIRLNK$   @#@@@@          OFF     @D@@@@          LA        A2,STE
)@@G@@AVX11         LOAD RETURNS    @D@@@@          LA        A3,ENTRYINFO    TF
)@@G@@  AND POINTERS    @C@@@@          DS        A2,SAVX11X        SAVE THEM TG
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIRLNK$       INTERNAL DIRLNK CALL FOR MAITH
)@@G@@N ITEM@F@@@@          J         NOMORM            IF ERR, FORGET THIS FITI
)@@G@@LE    @D@@@@          LA        A2,SAVX11X+1      GET CALLER INFO @F@@@@TJ
)@@G@@          SA        A2,ENTRYINFO      RESTORE IN NORMAL PLACE     @E@@@@TK
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,1              SET MAIN-ITEM FLAG    @D@@@@      TL
)@@G@@    TNZ       FORPKT            FORTRAN CALL ?  @B@@@@          J       TM
)@@G@@  MINOFOR           NOPE@E@@@@          LA        A1,FORPKT         LOADTN
)@@G@@ PACKET ADDRESS   @F@@@@          LA,U      A1,*ECODE,A1      LOAD ERRORTO
)@@G@@ CELL ADDRESS     @F@@@@          SA        A0,,A1            STORE ERROTP
)@@G@@R CODE FOR USER   @G@@@@MINOFOR   LX        X11,SAVX11X       RETRIEVE UTQ
)@@G@@SER'S RETURN ADDRESS    @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TOFF$    @C@@@@TR
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             RETURN    @G@@@@/. DIRLED - GIVEN TS
)@@G@@A LEAD ITEM LINK ADDRESS (AS FROM THE LOOKUP TABLE,   @G@@@@.           TT
)@@G@@A SEARCH ITEM, OR A MAIN ITEM BACK LINK), FIND THE SECTOR   @G@@@@.     TU
)@@G@@      IT POINTS TO, AND PLACE IT IN LBUF FOR DIRSEC.  IF THE USER @H@@@@TV
)@@G@@.           WANTS LEAD ITEMS (AS INDICATED IN THE DIRINT MASK), THEN GIVTW
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@.           IT TO HIM, ALSO.  ON SUBSEQUENT CALLS, IF THE LETX
)@@G@@AD ITEM IS  @G@@@@.           STILL IN CORE (GOTONE IS NONZERO), JUST METY
)@@G@@RGE INTO DIRSEC   @E@@@@.           CODE AND RETURN THE MAIN ITEMS TO THTZ
)@@G@@E USER.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRLED (ECODE,$ERR,BUA
)@@G@@UFF,LINK)   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,BUFF    @A@@@@UB
)@@G@@.                LA      A1,LINK    @A@@@@.                LMJ     X11,DUC
)@@G@@IRLED$@F@@@@.                <ERROR RETURN>       A1,A2 CONTAINS ERROR CUD
)@@G@@ODE   @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LEDARGUE
)@@G@@    EQU       4                 NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@UF
)@@G@@DIRLED*   LA,U      A2,LEDARG         # OF ARGS, WITH ERROR RETURN@G@@@@UG
)@@G@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POINTS   UH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,*USERLINK,A0   POINT TO LINK WORD    @F@@@@UI
)@@G@@          LA        A1,,A1            GET LINK WORD FROM USER     @F@@@@UJ
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,*USERBUFAD,A0  GET USER'S BUFFER ADDRESS   @E@@@@UK
)@@G@@          J         DIRLED2           MERGE INTO ASM CODE   @E@@@@DIRLEDUL
)@@G@@$*  SZ        FORPKT            INDICATE ASM ENTRY    @D@@@@          LXUM
)@@G@@I,U     X11,,X11          SET ERROR RETURN@E@@@@          LXM,U     X11,UN
)@@G@@1,X11         AND NORMAL RETURN     @D@@@@DIRLED2   SX        X11,SAVX11UO
)@@G@@        SAVE RETURN INFO@A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TON$     @F@@@@UP
)@@G@@          SA        A0,BUFRADDR       SAVE USER'S BUFFER ADDRESS  @G@@@@UQ
)@@G@@          TZ        GOTONE            DO WE ALREADY HAVE A LEAD ITEM?   UR
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         GTMITM            YES, MERGE INTO DIRSEC CODE US
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA        A0,LEDFLG         NO, SET THIS-LEAD-ITEM-ONLY UT
)@@G@@FLAG  @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,LBUF           SET OUR BUFFER ADDRESSUU
)@@G@@ FOR DIRLNK$@ @@@@          ON        DEBUG     @F@@@@          LA,U    UV
)@@G@@  A2,1              SET INTERNAL-DIRLNK$ FLAG   @A@@@@          SA      UW
)@@G@@  A2,INTERNAL     @ @@@@          OFF       DEBUG     @F@@@@          LAUX
)@@G@@        A2,SAVX11         SAVE USER'S RETURN, ETC.    @A@@@@          LAUY
)@@G@@        A3,ENTRYINFO    @ @@@@          DS        A2,SAVX11X@E@@@@      UZ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,DIRLNK$       INTERNAL DIRLNK$ CALL @D@@@@          J VA
)@@G@@        NOMORM            DIRLNK$ ERROR   @F@@@@          DL        A2,SVB
)@@G@@AVX11X        GET SAVED RETURN/ENTRY INFO @D@@@@          SA        A2,SVC
)@@G@@AVX11         AND RESTORE IT  @A@@@@          SA        A3,ENTRYINFO    VD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,(1,LBUF+11)    SET MAIN ITEM LINK INDEX    VE
)@@G@@@ @@@@          SA        A0,LINDEX @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,1      VF
)@@G@@        MARK LEAD ITEM INCORE @ @@@@          SA        A0,GOTONE @G@@@@VG
)@@G@@          TNZ       WANTL             DOES USER WANT THE LEAD ITEM?     VH
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         GTMITM            NO, MERGE INTO DIRSEC CODE  VI
)@@G@@@C@@@@          LA        A3,(1,LBUF)       SET FOR BT@E@@@@          J VJ
)@@G@@        GTLITM2           MERGE INTO DIRSEC CODE@H@@@@/. DIRLNK - GIVEN VK
)@@G@@A DIRECTORY LINK ADDRESS, FIND THE SECTOR IT POINTS TO,     @D@@@@.     VL
)@@G@@      AND TRANSFER IT TO THE CALLER'S BUFFER.   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     VM
)@@G@@ FORTRAN:  CALL DIRLNK (ECODE,$ERR,BUFF,LINK)   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     VN
)@@G@@ ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,BUFF    @A@@@@.                LA      A1,LINK    VO
)@@G@@@A@@@@.                LMJ     X11,DIRLNK$@F@@@@.                <ERROR VP
)@@G@@RETURN>       A1,A2 CONTAINS ERROR CODE   @A@@@@.                <NORMALVQ
)@@G@@ RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LNKARG    EQU       4         VR
)@@G@@        NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIRLNK*   LA,U      A2,LVS
)@@G@@NKARG         # OF ARGS, WITH ERROR RETURN@G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FVT
)@@G@@ORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETURN POINTS   @E@@@@          LA,U    VU
)@@G@@  A1,*USERLINK,A0   POINT TO LINK ADDRESS @E@@@@          LA        A1,,VV
)@@G@@A1            LOAD LINK ADDRESS     @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,*USERBUVW
)@@G@@FAD,A0  LOAD BUFFER ADDRESS   @C@@@@          J         DIRLNK2         VX
)@@G@@  CONTINUE  @E@@@@DIRLNK$*  SZ        FORPKT            CLEAR FORTRAN PAVY
)@@G@@CKET  @E@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11          LOAD ERROR RETURN     VZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LXM,U     X11,1,X11         LOAD NORMAL RETURN    @C@@@@WA
)@@G@@DIRLNK2   SX        X11,SAVX11        SAVE IT   @A@@@@          DO DEBUGWB
)@@G@@>0 , SLJ TON$     @E@@@@          SA        A1,LINKERADD      SAVE LINK WC
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @E@@@@          SA        A0,BUFRADDR       SAVE BUFFER ADDRWD
)@@G@@ESS   @G@@@@LINK01    TZ        ADDL              IS DIRINT INITIALIZATIWE
)@@G@@ON COMPLETE?@ @@@@          TNZ       NXSEC     @B@@@@          SLJ     WF
)@@G@@  NOTINT            NO  @D@@@@          S         R2,SAVR2          YES,WG
)@@G@@ SAVE R2    @C@@@@          S         X8,SAVX8            AND X8  @[@@@@WH
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@. CODE RIPPED OFF FROM @SECURE 19R2 ELEMENT 'DIRECT'  @[@@@@WI
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@          LA        A0,A1             GET LINK WORD PASSED BWJ
)@@G@@Y USER@D@@@@          JZ        A0,ADDCN3         IF ZERO, ERROR  @ @@@@WK
)@@G@@          ON        PRE33     @F@@@@          TZ        DIR$MFDF        WL
)@@G@@  NEW FORMAT DIRECTORY FILE?  @F@@@@          J         ADDCN1          WM
)@@G@@  YES, GO DIRECTLY TO SEARCH  @G@@@@          SSL       A1,24           WN
)@@G@@  SHIFT UNTIL A1 = FLAGS AND SS #   @E@@@@          AND,U     A1,0377   WO
)@@G@@        MASK OFF MOST FLAGS   @D@@@@          TEP,U     A2,0200         WP
)@@G@@  REMOVABLE DISC? @F@@@@          J         ADDCN1            YES, GO DIWQ
)@@G@@RECTLY TO SEARCH  @E@@@@          LA,T2     A1,MCTTBL+6       GET MCT HEWR
)@@G@@ADER LENGTH @ @@@@          ON        LEVEL27   @D@@@@          TNZ,T2  WS
)@@G@@  MCTTBL+5          LEVEL 27 EXEC?  @F@@@@          LA,T2     A1,MCTTBL+WT
)@@G@@8       YES, GET OLD HEADER LENGTH  @ @@@@          OFF       LEVEL27   WU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          A         A1,A2             ADD SUBSYSTEM # @H@@@@      WV
)@@G@@    L,T3      A2,MCTTBL,A1      GET OFFSET FOR SUBSYSTEM STATUS ENTRY   WW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,S1      A3,MCTTBL,A2      PICK UP EQUIPMENT CODE@G@@@@WX
)@@G@@          TG,U      A3,030            FASTRAND FORMAT MASS STORAGE?     WY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         ADDCN1            YES, DO SEARCH  @D@@@@      WZ
)@@G@@    L         X8,(1,1)          GET ADDTBL INDEX@G@@@@ADDCN0    L       XA
)@@G@@  A1,ADDTBL-1,X8    GET DIR TRACK ADDR FROM ADDTBL    @E@@@@          ANXB
)@@G@@D       A1,MASK1          MASK OFF FLAG BITS    @E@@@@          AN,U    XC
)@@G@@  A2,1              SET UP FOR RANGE TEST @ @@@@          AU,U      A2,1XD
)@@G@@792   @G@@@@          AND       A0,MASK1          REMOVE FLAG BITS FROM XE
)@@G@@INPUT ADDR  @G@@@@          TNW       A2,A1             IS INPUT ADDR WIXF
)@@G@@THIN THIS TRACK?  @B@@@@          J         ADDCN5            YES @F@@@@XG
)@@G@@ADDCN4    TLEM      X8,ADDL           ARE WE AT END OF TABLE?     @F@@@@XH
)@@G@@          J         ADDCN0            NO, TRY NEXT TRACK IN ADDTBL@E@@@@XI
)@@G@@          J         ADDCN3            YES, NO FIND: ERROR   @F@@@@ADDCN5XJ
)@@G@@    L,U       A3,0,X8           A3 = INDEX INTO ADDTBL + 1  @D@@@@      XK
)@@G@@    AN,U      A3,1              ADJUST SLIGHTLY @G@@@@          A,U     XL
)@@G@@  A2,1              RESET A2 = TRACK ADDR FROM ADDTBL @F@@@@          ANXM
)@@G@@        A1,A2             SUBTRACT TO GET WORD INDEX  @E@@@@          TNXN
)@@G@@        ADDTBL,A3         SHORT TRACK CASE?     @C@@@@          J       XO
)@@G@@  ADDCN7            NO - SKIP @D@@@@          AND       A0,(0777777)    XP
)@@G@@  YES, MASK OFF H1@F@@@@          AN,H2     A1,ADDTBL,A3      SUBTRACT TXQ
)@@G@@O GET WORD INDEX  @E@@@@          JN        A1,ADDCN4         JUMP IF SHXR
)@@G@@ORT TRACK   @D@@@@ADDCN7    LA,U      A0,0              CLEAR FOR DIVIDEXS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DI,U      A0,034            FORM SECTOR INDEX     @E@@@@XT
)@@G@@          JNZ       A1,ADDCN3         JUMP IF BAD REMAINDER @F@@@@      XU
)@@G@@    S         A0,A1             STORE SECTOR INDEX IN A1    @C@@@@      XV
)@@G@@    J         ADDCN2            CONTINUE  @ @@@@          OFF       PRE3XW
)@@G@@3     @G@@@@ADDCN1    L         X8,(1,-1)         SET ADDTBL INDEX AND IXX
)@@G@@NCREMENT    @E@@@@          L         A2,ADDL           A2 = TABLE LENGTXY
)@@G@@H     @E@@@@          S         A2,R1             STORE REPEAT COUNT    XZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          L         R2,MASK2          GET MASK FOR MSE@G@@@@      YA
)@@G@@    MSE       A0,ADDTBL+1,*X8   SEARCH FOR EQUAL TRACK ADDRESS    @D@@@@YB
)@@G@@          J         ADDCN3            NO FIND - ERROR @ @@@@          L YC
)@@G@@        R2,SAVR2  @F@@@@          L,U       A3,0,X8           A3 = REL IYD
)@@G@@NDEX INTO ADDTBL  @F@@@@          AND       A0,(0777777)      MASK OFF HYE
)@@G@@1 OF INPUT ADDR   @H@@@@          AN,H2     A1,ADDTBL,A3      - FOUND TRYF
)@@G@@K ADDR TO GET SECTOR INDEX    @F@@@@          S         A1,A0           YG
)@@G@@  STORE SECTOR INDEX IN A0    @C@@@@ADDCN2    L         X8,SAVX8        YH
)@@G@@  RESTORE X8@E@@@@          A         A3,FIRSTR         GET LOGICAL TRACYI
)@@G@@K #   @E@@@@          LSSL      A3,6              CONVERT TO SECTOR #   YJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          A         A0,A3             ADD SECTOR INDEX@F@@@@      YK
)@@G@@    S         A0,IOPAK+5        STORE AS DRUM ADDRESS FOR IO@E@@@@      YL
)@@G@@    L         A2,NXSEC          GET NEXT SECTOR ADDR  @C@@@@          ANYM
)@@G@@,U      A2,1              ADJUST    @G@@@@          SSL       A2,6      YN
)@@G@@        CONVERT TO DGET$ FILE TRACK #     @F@@@@          SSL       A0,6YO
)@@G@@              CONVERT TARGET ADDR ALSO    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WE CURRENTYP
)@@G@@LY HAVE ONE DIRECTORY TRACK INCORE.  IF THE REQUIRED  @F@@@@. SECTOR IS YQ
)@@G@@WITHIN THAT TRACK, WE CAN JUST BLOCK TRANSFER IT TO   @E@@@@. THE CALLERYR
)@@G@@'S BUFFER.  IF NOT, WE MUST READ THE SECTOR IN  @^@@@@. FROM THE DGET$ FYS
)@@G@@ILE.  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TNE       A0,A2             SAME TRACKYT
)@@G@@?     @F@@@@          J         BT                YES, ALREADY HAVE IT IYU
)@@G@@NCORE @E@@@@          LA        A0,BUFRADDR       LOAD BUFFER ADDRESS   YV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,28             SET TO READ 1 SECTOR  @ @@@@YW
)@@G@@          S         A0,IOPAK+4@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,IOPAK        YX
)@@G@@  READ THE SECTOR @^@@@@          ER        IOW$@C@@@@          TZ,S1   YY
)@@G@@  IOPAK+3           IO OK?    @B@@@@          SLJ       IOR             YZ
)@@G@@  NO  @D@@@@          J         LINKDONE          YES, ALL DONE   @[@@@@ZA
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@BT        MSI,U     A1,034            CONVERT SECTOR INDEX TZB
)@@G@@O WORD INDEX@G@@@@          AH        A1,(1,TRKBUF)     ADD START OF TRKZC
)@@G@@ BUFFER, AND INC  @E@@@@          LA        A0,BUFRADDR       LOAD BUFFEZD
)@@G@@R ADDRESS   @D@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1              SET INC FOR BT  ZE
)@@G@@@ @@@@          L,U       R1,28     @F@@@@          BT        A0,0,*A1  ZF
)@@G@@        MOVE SECTOR TO USER'S BUFFER@]@@@@LINKDONE  . @ @@@@          ONZG
)@@G@@        DEBUG     @E@@@@          TNZ       INTERNAL          INTERNAL DZH
)@@G@@IRLNK$ CALL?@E@@@@          SLJ       TOFF$             NO, TURN OFF SNOZI
)@@G@@OPY   @F@@@@          SZ        INTERNAL          CLEAR INTERNAL-DIRLNK$ZJ
)@@G@@ FLAG @#@@@@          OFF     @E@@@@          LX        X11,SAVX11      ZK
)@@G@@  LOAD RETURN ADDRESS   @C@@@@          J         0,X11             RETUZL
)@@G@@RN    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. LINK ERROR@[@@@@.     @E@@@@ADDCN3    L,U     ZM
)@@G@@  A1,LNKERR         A0 GETS ERROR TYPE    @F@@@@          L         A2,LZN
)@@G@@INKERADD      A2 GETS USER'S LINK WORD    @C@@@@          L         R2,SZO
)@@G@@AVR2          RESTORE R2@C@@@@          L         X8,SAVX8          RESTZP
)@@G@@ORE X8@ @@@@          ON        DEBUG     @E@@@@          TNZ       INTEZQ
)@@G@@RNAL          INTERNAL DIRLNK$ CALL?@E@@@@          SLJ       TOFF$     ZR
)@@G@@        NO, TURN OFF SNOOPY   @F@@@@          SZ        INTERNAL        ZS
)@@G@@  CLEAR INTERNAL-DIRLNK$ FLAG @#@@@@          OFF     @G@@@@          J ZT
)@@G@@        ERREXT2           NO, RETURN ERROR STATUS TO USER   @F@@@@/. DIRZU
)@@G@@LUT - RETURNS LUT SECTORS ONE AT A TIME TO USER'B BUFFER.   @[@@@@.     ZV
)@@G@@@C@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRLUT (ECODE,$ERR,BUFF)  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@ZW
)@@G@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,BUFF    @A@@@@.                LMJ     X11,DZX
)@@G@@IRLUT$@F@@@@.                <ERROR/EOF RETURN>     A1,A2 CONTAINS ERRORZY
)@@G@@ CODE @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE ZZ
)@@G@@NEXT 28 WORDS OF LOOKUP TABLE WILL BE TRANSFERRED TO THE SUPPLIED @G@@@@AA
)@@G@@. BUFFER.  IF THE END OF THE LOOKUP TABLE IS ENCOUNTERED, THE ERROR     AB
)@@G@@@D@@@@. RETURN WILL BE TAKEN, AND AN EOF STATUS RETURNED.   @[@@@@.     AC
)@@G@@@E@@@@LUTARG    EQU       3                 NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS   @[@@@@AD
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@DIRLUT*   LA,U      A2,LUTARG         # OF ARGS, WITH ERROR AE
)@@G@@RETURN@G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK         SET UP FORPKT AND RETUAF
)@@G@@RN POINTS   @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,*USERBUFAD,A0  GET USER'S BUFFEAG
)@@G@@R ADDRESS   @E@@@@          J         DIRLUT2           MERGE INTO ASM CAH
)@@G@@ODE   @E@@@@DIRLUT$*  SZ        FORPKT            INDICATE ASM ENTRY    AI
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11          SET ERROR RETURN@E@@@@      AJ
)@@G@@    LXM,U     X11,1,X11         AND NORMAL RETURN     @D@@@@DIRLUT2   SXAK
)@@G@@        X11,SAVX11        SAVE RETURN INFO@A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SAL
)@@G@@LJ TON$     @E@@@@          SA        A0,BUFRADDR       SAVE BUFFER ADDRAM
)@@G@@ESS   @E@@@@          LA        A0,NXLUTSEC       NEXT LUT SECTOR TO GETAN
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TG        A0,LUTSECS        REACHED END OF LUT?   @B@@@@AO
)@@G@@          J         EOF               YES @H@@@@          AA,U      A0,LAP
)@@G@@UTSTART       NO, BUMP TO START OF LUT IN DGETT FILE  @H@@@@          LMAQ
)@@G@@J       X11,GETLUT        POINT A0 TO START OF SECTOR IN CORE     @E@@@@AR
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A0,1              SET INCREMENT FOR BT  @F@@@@      AS
)@@G@@    LXM       A1,BUFRADDR       GET USER'S BUFFER ADDRESS   @E@@@@      AT
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A1,1              SET INCREMENT FOR BT  @E@@@@          LRAU
)@@G@@,U      R1,28             SET TO MOVE 1 SECTOR  @H@@@@          BT      AV
)@@G@@  A1,,*A0           TRANSFER LUT SECTOR TO USER'S BUFFER    @E@@@@      AW
)@@G@@    LA        A0,NXLUTSEC       GET NEXT LUT SECTOR   @C@@@@          AAAX
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              BUMP IT   @E@@@@          SA        A0,NXLUTSEAY
)@@G@@C       UPDATE NEXT LUT SECTOR@E@@@@          LX        X11,SAVX11      AZ
)@@G@@  PICK UP RETURN INFO   @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TOFF$    @D@@@@BA
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             NORMAL RETURN   @G@@@@/. DIRLUW - BB
)@@G@@GIVEN QUALIFIER AND FILENAME, PERFORMS HASHING AND RETURNS  @E@@@@.     BC
)@@G@@      THE LOOKUP TABLE WORD WHICH IS THUS REFERENCED. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@BD
)@@G@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRLUW (ECODE,$ERR,QUALFL,LUTW) @[@@@@.     @A@@@@BE
)@@G@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,QUALFL  @A@@@@.                LMJ     X11,DBF
)@@G@@IRLUW$@F@@@@.                <ERROR RETURN>       A1,A2 CONTAINS ERROR CBG
)@@G@@ODE   @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WHERBH
)@@G@@E 'QUALFL' IS THE ADDRESS OF A 4-WORD BUFFER CONTAINING THE @G@@@@. FIELBI
)@@G@@DATA QUALIFIER AND FILENAME.  FOR FORTRAN CALLS, THE LOOKUP TABLE @G@@@@BJ
)@@G@@. WORD WILL BE RETURNED IN 'LUTW' -- FOR ASSEMBLY, IT WILL BE PUT IN A0.BK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@LUWARG    EQU       4                 NUMBER OF ARGUMEBL
)@@G@@NTS   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIRLUW*   LA,U      A2,LUWARG         # OF ARG, BM
)@@G@@WITH ERROR RETURN @G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK         SET UP FORBN
)@@G@@PKT AND RETURN POINTS   @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,*USERBUFAD,A0  GET BO
)@@G@@USER'S BUFFER ADDRESS   @E@@@@          J         DIRLUW2           MERGBP
)@@G@@E INTO ASM CODE   @E@@@@DIRLUW$*  SZ        FORPKT            INDICATE ABQ
)@@G@@SM ENTRY    @D@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11          SET ERROR RETURNBR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LXM,U     X11,1,X11         AND NORMAL RETURN     @D@@@@BS
)@@G@@DIRLUW2   SX        X11,SAVX11        SAVE RETURN INFO@A@@@@          DOBT
)@@G@@ DEBUG>0 , SLJ TON$     @F@@@@          TZ        ADDL              IS IBU
)@@G@@NITIALIZATION COMPLETE? @ @@@@          TNZ       NXSEC     @B@@@@      BV
)@@G@@    SLJ       NOTINT            NO  @H@@@@          DL        A2,2,A0   BW
)@@G@@        YES, GET FILENAME FROM USER'S PACKET    @E@@@@          DL      BX
)@@G@@  A0,0,A0           ALSO THE QUALIFIER    @F@@@@          DA        A0,ABY
)@@G@@2             GENERATE LOOKUP TABLE INDEX @ @@@@          DSC       A0,1BZ
)@@G@@8     @B@@@@          AH        A0,A1               H @B@@@@          DSCA
)@@G@@L       A0,18                A@C@@@@          SSL       A1,18           CB
)@@G@@      S     @C@@@@          AA        A0,A1                  H    @ @@@@CC
)@@G@@          DSL       A0,36     @G@@@@          DI        A0,DCLUTS       CD
)@@G@@  DIVIDE BY SIZE OF LOOKUP TABLE    @G@@@@.                             CE
)@@G@@        NOW HAVE LUT WORD INDEX IN A1     @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,0CF
)@@G@@              SET FOR DIVIDE AGAIN  @F@@@@          DI,U      A0,28     CG
)@@G@@        GET LUT SECTOR INDEX IN A0, @D@@@@.                             CH
)@@G@@        WORD INDEX IN A1@F@@@@          AA,U      A0,LUTSTART       ADD CI
)@@G@@LUT STARTING SECTOR     @H@@@@          LMJ       X11,GETLUT        POINCJ
)@@G@@T A0 TO START OF THE DESIRED SECTOR @D@@@@          AA        A1,A0     CK
)@@G@@        ADD WORD OFFSET @E@@@@          LA        A0,,A1            PICKCL
)@@G@@ UP THE LUT ENTRY @D@@@@          TNZ       FORPKT            FORTRAN CACM
)@@G@@LL?   @B@@@@          J         LUWASM            NO  @G@@@@          LACN
)@@G@@        A1,FORPKT         YES, GET PARAMETER LIST ADDRESS   @E@@@@      CO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,*USERLUTW,A1   POINT TO USER'S WORD  @E@@@@          SACP
)@@G@@        A0,,A1            STORE ENTRY FOR USER  @E@@@@LUWASM    LX      CQ
)@@G@@  X11,SAVX11        PICK UP RETURN INFO   @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SCR
)@@G@@LJ TOFF$    @D@@@@          J         0,X11             NORMAL RETURN   CS
)@@G@@@G@@@@/. DIRLUF - GIVEN A QUALIFIER AND FILENAME, FINDS LOOKUP TABLE ENTCT
)@@G@@RY,   @G@@@@.           AND FOLLOWS SEARCH ITEM CHAIN, IF NECESSARY, TO CU
)@@G@@FIND THE    @F@@@@.           LEAD ITEM LINK.  RETURNS LEAD ITEM LINK WOCV
)@@G@@RD OR 0.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.      FORTRAN:  CALL DIRLUF (ECODE,$ERR,QCW
)@@G@@UALFL,LUTW) @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.      ASSEMBLY: LA,U    A0,QUALFL  @A@@@@CX
)@@G@@.                LMJ     X11,DIRLUF$@F@@@@.                <ERROR RETURNCY
)@@G@@>       A1,A2 CONTAINS ERROR CODE   @A@@@@.                <NORMAL RETURCZ
)@@G@@N>    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WHERE 'QUALFL' IS THE ADDRESS OF A 4-WORD BUFFDA
)@@G@@ER CONTAINING THE @A@@@@. FIELDATA QUALIFIER AND FILENAME.  @[@@@@.     DB
)@@G@@@G@@@@. FOR FORTRAN CALLS, THE RESULTING LEAD ITEM LINK (OR 0) IS RETURNDC
)@@G@@ED    @D@@@@. IN 'LUTW':  FOR ASSEMBLY, IT IS RETURNED IN A0.     @[@@@@DD
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. IF AN ERROR IS ENCOUNTERED IN THE SEARCH ITEM CHAIN, THE EDE
)@@G@@RROR RETURN @D@@@@. WILL BE TAKEN, WITH ECODE (A1) SET TO 'LUFERR'.     DF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@LUFARG    EQU       4                 NUMBER OF ARGUMEDG
)@@G@@NTS   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DIRLUF*   LA,U      A2,LUFARG         # OF ARG, DH
)@@G@@WITH ERROR RETURN @G@@@@          LMJ       A3,FORLNK         SET UP FORDI
)@@G@@PKT AND RETURN POINTS   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,*USERBUFAD,A0  GET DJ
)@@G@@QUALFL ADDRESS    @E@@@@          J         DIRLUF2           MERGE INTODK
)@@G@@ ASM CODE   @E@@@@DIRLUF$*  SZ        FORPKT            INDICATE ASM ENTDL
)@@G@@RY    @D@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11          SET ERROR RETURN@E@@@@DM
)@@G@@          LXM,U     X11,1,X11         AND NORMAL RETURN     @D@@@@DIRLUFDN
)@@G@@2   SX        X11,SAVX11        SAVE RETURN INFO@A@@@@          DO DEBUGDO
)@@G@@>0 , SLJ TON$     @F@@@@          TZ        ADDL              IS INITIALDP
)@@G@@IZATION COMPLETE? @ @@@@          TNZ       NXSEC     @B@@@@          SLDQ
)@@G@@J       NOTINT            NO  @E@@@@          SZ        GOTONE          DR
)@@G@@  CLEAR L.I. INCORE FLAG@E@@@@          SA        A0,LUFQF          SSAVDS
)@@G@@E QUALFL ADDRESS  @D@@@@          LA        A2,SAVX11         GRAB RETURDT
)@@G@@N INFO@D@@@@          LA        A3,ENTRYINFO      AND ENTRY INFO  @D@@@@DU
)@@G@@          DS        A2,SAVX11X        SAVE FOR LATER  @E@@@@          LMDV
)@@G@@J       X11,DIRLUW$       FIND LOOKUP TABLE WORD@D@@@@          J       DW
)@@G@@  LUFERROR          ERROR RETURN    @G@@@@          JP        A0,LUFDONEDX
)@@G@@        IF ENTRY IS POSITIVE, RETURN IT   @H@@@@.                       DY
)@@G@@              (IT'S EITHER 0 OR A LEAD ITEM LINK)     @G@@@@          SADZ
)@@G@@        A0,A1             OTHERWISE, PUT LINK WORD IN A1    @[@@@@.     EA
)@@G@@@G@@@@. LUT ENTRY POINTS TO SEARCH ITEM -- GET IT, AND FIND LEAD ITEM LIEB
)@@G@@NK    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@LUFSEARCH . @ @@@@          ON        DEBUG     EC
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA,U      A0,1              SET INTERNAL DIRLNK$ CALL FLED
)@@G@@AG    @A@@@@          SA        A0,INTERNAL     @#@@@@          OFF     EE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,LBUF           USE LBUF FOR SEARCH ITEM    EF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIRLNK$       LINK TO SEARCH ITEM   @D@@@@EG
)@@G@@          J         LUFERROR          ERROR RETURN    @H@@@@          LAEH
)@@G@@        A2,LUFQF          OK, GET ADDR OF USER'S QUALFL BUFFER    @F@@@@EI
)@@G@@          DL        A0,0,A2           GET SPECIFIED QUALIFIER     @D@@@@EJ
)@@G@@          DL        A2,2,A2           AND FILENAME    @F@@@@          LXEK
)@@G@@I,U     X11,5             SET INCREMENT FOR SEARCH    @F@@@@          LXEL
)@@G@@M,U     X11,LBUF          POINT TO SEACH ITEM BUFFER  @E@@@@LUFLOOP   DTEM
)@@G@@E       A0,1,X11          MATCHING QUALIFIER?   @B@@@@          J       EN
)@@G@@  LUFLOOPE          NO  @F@@@@          DTE       A2,3,X11          YES,EO
)@@G@@ MATCHIN FILENAME TOO?  @B@@@@          J         LUFLOOPE          NO  EP
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,5,X11          YES, GET LEAD ITEM LINK     EQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         LUFDONE           AND RETURN IT TO THE USER   ER
)@@G@@@F@@@@LUFLOOPE  TLEM,U    X11,LBUF+20       ALL DONE WITH SEARCH ITEM?  ES
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         LUFLOOP           NO, CONTINUE    @E@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    TP        LBUF+0            YES, ARE THERE MORE?  @E@@@@          J EU
)@@G@@        LUFZERO           NO, RETURN A ZERO LINK@F@@@@          LA      EV
)@@G@@  A1,LBUF+0         YES, GET LINK TO NEXT S.I.  @G@@@@          J       EW
)@@G@@  LUFSEARCH         CONTINUE SEARCH FOR LEAD ITEM     @E@@@@LUFZERO   LAEX
)@@G@@,U      A0,0              INDICATE NO SUCH FILE @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. HAVEEY
)@@G@@ LEAD ITEM LINK OR 0:  RETURN IT TO THE USER    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@LUFDONEZ
)@@G@@E   DL        A2,SAVX11X        GET SAVED ENTRY/RETURN INFO @D@@@@      FA
)@@G@@    SA        A2,SAVX11         AND RESTORE IT  @A@@@@          SA      FB
)@@G@@  A3,ENTRYINFO    @E@@@@          TNZ       FORPKT            CALLED FROFC
)@@G@@M FORTRAN?  @E@@@@          J         LUFASM            NO, FROM ASSEMBLFD
)@@G@@Y     @F@@@@          LA        A1,FORPKT         YES, POINT TO PARAMETEFE
)@@G@@R LIST@F@@@@          LA,U      A1,*USERLUTW,A1   POINT TO USER'S DATA WFF
)@@G@@ORD   @F@@@@          SA        A0,,A1            STORE LINK WORD OR ZERFG
)@@G@@O     @F@@@@LUFASM    LX        X11,SAVX11        GET NORMAL RETURN ADDRFH
)@@G@@ESS   @A@@@@          DO DEBUG>0 , SLJ TOFF$    @D@@@@          J       FI
)@@G@@  0,X11             NORMAL RETURN   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. DIRLUF ERROR HANFJ
)@@G@@DLER  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@LUFERROR  DL        A0,SAVX11X        RETRIEVE UFK
)@@G@@SER'S ENTRY/RETURN INFO @D@@@@          SA        A0,SAVX11         AND FL
)@@G@@RESTORE THEM@A@@@@          SA        A1,ENTRYINFO    @E@@@@          LAFM
)@@G@@,U      A1,LUFERR         INDICATE DIRLUF ERROR @E@@@@          J       FN
)@@G@@  ERREXT1           TAKE ERROR RETURN     @D@@@@/. GETLUT - SUBROUTINE TFO
)@@G@@O GET THE DESIRED LUT SECTOR. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ENTER WITH DGET$ FILE FP
)@@G@@SECTOR # IN A0.  READS UP THE SECTOR, IF  @F@@@@. NECESSARY, AND SETS A0FQ
)@@G@@ TO THE ADDRESS OF THE SECTOR IN CORE.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. DESTROYS XFR
)@@G@@11, A0, A2, A3    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@GETLUT    LA        A2,LUTRD+5      FS
)@@G@@  GET FIRST SECTOR IN CORE    @D@@@@          TLE       A0,A2           FT
)@@G@@  IS OURS THERE?  @C@@@@          J         GETLUT1           NO, GET ITFU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          A,U       A2,LUTL           PERHAPS -- GET UPPER LIMIT  FV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TLE       A0,A2             WELL, IS IT THERE?    @D@@@@FW
)@@G@@          J         GETLUT2           YES, USE IT     @E@@@@GETLUT1   SAFX
)@@G@@        A0,A2             SAVE DESIRED SECTOR   @D@@@@          DSL     FY
)@@G@@  A2,36             SET FOR DIVIDE  @F@@@@          DI,U      A2,LUTL   FZ
)@@G@@        WANT TO READ FULL LUT RECORD@F@@@@          SA        A0,A2     GA
)@@G@@        SAVE DESIRED SECTOR AGAIN   @G@@@@          ANA       A0,A3     GB
)@@G@@        CALCULATE 1ST SECTOR OF LUT RECORD@E@@@@          SA        A0,LGC
)@@G@@UTRD+5        SET IN I/O PACKET     @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,LUTRD  GD
)@@G@@        GET I/O PACKET  @E@@@@          ER        IOW$              READGE
)@@G@@ THE LUT RECORD   @B@@@@          TZ,S1     LUTRD+3           OK? @B@@@@GF
)@@G@@          SLJ       IOR               NO  @^@@@@          ON        SNAPGG
)@@G@@@ @@@@          LA,U      A0,LUTSNP @ @@@@          ER        SNAP$     GH
)@@G@@@#@@@@          OFF     @G@@@@          LA        A0,A2             YES,GI
)@@G@@ RESTORE DESIRED SECTOR #     @G@@@@GETLUT2   ANA       A0,LUTRD+5      GJ
)@@G@@  CALCULATE INDEX INTO LUT BUFFER   @G@@@@          MSI,U     A0,28     GK
)@@G@@        CONVERT SECTOR INDEX TO WORD INDEX@G@@@@          LA,U      A0,LGL
)@@G@@UT,A0         POINT TO START OF SECTOR IN CORE  @D@@@@          J       GM
)@@G@@  0,X11             RETURN TO CALLER@F@@@@/. FORLNK - INTERFACE FOR FORTGN
)@@G@@RAN CALLS TO DIREC$ SUBROUTINES     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   ENTER WITH A2 GO
)@@G@@= (ERROR-RETURN INDICATION,# OF ARGUMENTS).     @F@@@@.   WILL RETURN WIGP
)@@G@@TH A0 POINTING TO USER'S PARAMETER LIST, AND    @F@@@@.   LOWER X11 = NOGQ
)@@G@@RMAL RETURN ADDRESS.  IF H1 OF A2 IS POSITIVE   @F@@@@.   ON INPUT, THE GR
)@@G@@ERROR RETURN ADDRESS WILL BE PUT IN UPPER X11.  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@FORLNKGS
)@@G@@    LXI,U     X11,0             CLEAR ERROR RETURN    @F@@@@          TZGT
)@@G@@,S1     0,X11             IS THIS AN ASCII FTN CALL   @G@@@@.           GU
)@@G@@                          (OR 'T' SERIES FORTRAN-V WITH NO  @D@@@@.     GV
)@@G@@                                ARGUMENTS) ?    @C@@@@          J       GW
)@@G@@  FORLNK2           YES, GO ON@G@@@@          LA,U      A0,,X11         GX
)@@G@@  NO, LOAD PARAMETER LIST ADDRESS   @G@@@@          AU,U      A0,,A2    GY
)@@G@@        POINT A1 TO WORD BEYOND LAST ARG  @E@@@@          TNZ,S1    0,A1GZ
)@@G@@              'E' SERIES FORTRAN-V? @G@@@@          AA,U      A2,1      HA
)@@G@@        YES, ACCOUNT FOR WALKBACK WORD    @D@@@@.                       HB
)@@G@@              IN NORMAL RETURN@F@@@@          AX,U      X11,,A2         HC
)@@G@@  SET NORMAL RETURN ADDRESS   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOW HAVE NORMAL RETURNHD
)@@G@@ ADDRESS IN LOWER X11, AND ADDRESS OF USER'S    @^@@@@. PARAMETER LIST IHE
)@@G@@N A0. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOTE - FOR 'T' SERIES FORTRAN-V WITH NO ARGUMEHF
)@@G@@NTS, WE DON'T CARE@F@@@@.        ABOUT THE PARAMETER LIST, BUT A2 HAD BEHG
)@@G@@TTER BE NEGATIVE! @F@@@@.        ALSO, SINCE WE USE 'FORPKT' TO INDICATEHH
)@@G@@ A FORTRAN CALL   @F@@@@.        (VS. ASSEMBLY), WE MUST MAKE SURE THAT HI
)@@G@@A0 IS NONZERO.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@FORLNK2   TNZ,U     0,A0            HJ
)@@G@@  'T' SERIES, NO ARGS, AND A0=0?    @H@@@@          LA,U      A0,1      HK
)@@G@@        YES (OUCH!), FORPKT MUST BE NONZERO     @F@@@@          SA      HL
)@@G@@  A0,FORPKT         SAVE A0 AS PACKET ADDRESS   @F@@@@          JN      HM
)@@G@@  A2,0,A3           JUMP IF NO ERROR RETURN     @F@@@@          LXI,U   HN
)@@G@@  X11,*ERRORRTN,A0  SET ERROR RETURN ADDRESS    @D@@@@          J       HO
)@@G@@  0,A3              RETURN TO CALLER@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. RE-INITIALIZE FLHP
)@@G@@AGS AND ADDRESSES @[@@@@.     @F@@@@RESET     SZ        GOTONE          HQ
)@@G@@  CLEAR LEAD-ITEM-IN-CORE FLAG@E@@@@          SZ        LFLAG           HR
)@@G@@  CLEAR HMANY,GOTL1     @F@@@@          TZ        LEDFLG            JUSTHS
)@@G@@ DOING ONE LEAD ITEM?   @E@@@@          J         RESET2            YES,HT
)@@G@@ SKIP SOME OF THIS@E@@@@          SZ        NXLUTSEC          INITIALIZEHU
)@@G@@ DIRLUT     @F@@@@          LA        A0,FIRSTR         GET ADDR PF FIRSHV
)@@G@@T DIREC TRK @E@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              CONVERT TO SECTOHW
)@@G@@RS    @G@@@@          SA        A0,NXSEC          STORE AS NEXT SECTOR FHX
)@@G@@OR DIRSEC   @G@@@@          LA,U      A0,BUF+24         INITIALIZE DAS EHY
)@@G@@NTRY INDEX TO     @F@@@@          SA        A0,DX             BT OF DAS HZ
)@@G@@FROM FIRST TRACK  @E@@@@          LA,XU     A0,-LUTL          GET A NEGAIA
)@@G@@TIVE NUMBER @F@@@@          SA        A0,LUTRD+5        SET INITIAL CALLIB
)@@G@@ ON DIRLUT  @G@@@@RESET2    SZ        LEDFLG            CLEAR JUST-THIS-IC
)@@G@@LEAD-ITEM FLAG    @D@@@@          J         0,A1              RETURN TO ID
)@@G@@CALLER@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. MSCON$ ERROR DURING DIRINT  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IE
)@@G@@MSCR      L         A2,A0             SAVE A0 AS RETURNED BY MSCON$     IF
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LSSL      A0,12             GET ERROR STATUS - IF IT'S 0IG
)@@G@@33,   @G@@@@          SSL       A0,30              EXEC HAS RESET INITIAIH
)@@G@@L RESERVE   @F@@@@          TNE,U     A0,033             IN MSPKT+3 TO NII
)@@G@@EEDED VALUE,@D@@@@          J         TRYAGN             SO TRY AGAIN   IJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@DGETER    L,U       A1,MSCERR         NO GOOD, SET ERROR TYPE     IK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         ERREXT2           AND DO ERROR RETURN   @F@@@@IL
)@@G@@TRYAGN    L         A0,TRYCNT         GET DGET$ ATTEMPT COUNT     @D@@@@IM
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,1              INCREMENT COUNT @C@@@@          S IN
)@@G@@        A0,TRYCNT         STORE IT  @D@@@@          TG,U      A0,3      IO
)@@G@@        THIRD ATTEMPT?  @C@@@@          J         DGETER            YES,IP
)@@G@@ QUIT @ @@@@          ON        DIRSIZ>0  @G@@@@          AN,U      A0,1IQ
)@@G@@              ADJUST ATTEMPT COUNT FOR TEST     @E@@@@          JNZ     IR
)@@G@@  A0,$+3            IF FIRST TIME THRU,   @G@@@@          L,U       A0,LIS
)@@G@@OGMSG         TELL 'EM DIRSIZ GOTTA BE CHANGED  @E@@@@          ER      IT
)@@G@@  CSF$              SEND @LOG MESSAGE     @ @@@@          OFF       DIRSIU
)@@G@@IZ>0  @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIREND$       FREE DGET$ FILE @H@@@@IV
)@@G@@          J         REASG             TRY RE-ASSIGNING WITH PROPER RESERIW
)@@G@@VE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. I/O ERROR ENCOUNTERED @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IOR   IX
)@@G@@    J         0                 ENTERED VIA SLJ @E@@@@          L,U     IY
)@@G@@  A1,IOERR          SET I/O ERROR TYPE    @E@@@@          L         A2,3IZ
)@@G@@,A0           A1 = STATUS, ETC.     @G@@@@          J         ERREXT2   JA
)@@G@@        NO, RETURN ERROR TYPE/CODE TO USER@[@@@@.     @#@@@@. MAXDIR TOOJB
)@@G@@ SMALL@[@@@@.     @D@@@@OVFL      LA,U      A1,SIZERR         GET ERROR JC
)@@G@@TYPE  @E@@@@          LA        A2,MSPKT+3        AND REQUIRED SIZE     JD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         ERREXT2           RETURN ERROR STATUS TO USER JE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@. MCT$ ERROR@[@@@@.     @F@@@@MCTR      LA,U      A1,MJF
)@@G@@CTERR         SET FOR MCT$ ERROR TYPE     @D@@@@          LA,S1     A2,MJG
)@@G@@CTPKT         GET STATUS IN A2@F@@@@          J         ERREXT2         JH
)@@G@@  RETURN ERROR STATUS TO USER @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. BAD DIRINT MASK SPECIFJI
)@@G@@IED   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@BADMASK   L         A2,A0             GET MASK IJJ
)@@G@@N A2  @F@@@@          L,U       A1,MSKERR         SET 'BAD MASK' ERROR CJK
)@@G@@ODE   @G@@@@          J         ERREXT2           RETURN ERROR TYPE/CODEJL
)@@G@@ TO USER    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. EOF ENCOUNTERED DURING DIRSEC/DIRLED/DIRJM
)@@G@@LUT OPERATION     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@EOF       LMJ       A1,RESET        JN
)@@G@@  RE-INITIALIZE FLAGS, ETC.   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. NOW, IF SOMEONE GETS EJO
)@@G@@OF RTN, THEN CALLS AGAIN, DIRSEC WILL START OVER AT   @D@@@@. THE BEGINNJP
)@@G@@ING >WITHOUT< RE-INITIALIZING ADDTBL, ETC.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          L,JQ
)@@G@@U       A1,EOFERR         SET 'DIRSEC EOF' ERROR TYPE @D@@@@          J JR
)@@G@@        ERREXT1           RETURN TO USER  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CSF$ ERRORJS
)@@G@@ ENCOUNTERED@[@@@@.     @E@@@@CSFR      XOR       A0,(1*/33)        FILEJT
)@@G@@ ALREADY ASSIGNED?@E@@@@          JZ        A1,RERUN          YES, MAY BJU
)@@G@@E RERUN     @E@@@@          L         A2,A0             NO, A2 GETS STATJV
)@@G@@US    @F@@@@          L,U       A1,CSFERR         A0 GETS CSF$ ERROR CODJW
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@          J         ERREXT2           RETURN ERROR CODE TO CJX
)@@G@@ALLER @E@@@@RERUN     TNZ       NXSEC             ALREADY INITIALIZED?  JY
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         DGETOK            NO, DO IT @F@@@@          LMJZ
)@@G@@J       A1,RESET          RE-INITIALIZE FLAGS, ETC.   @E@@@@          LXKA
)@@G@@        X11,SAVX11        LOAD RETURN ADDRESS   @C@@@@          J       KB
)@@G@@  0,X11             RETURN    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. DIRSEC/DIRLNK/DIRLUW/DKC
)@@G@@IRLED CALLED BEFORE DIRINT COMPLETE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NOTINT    J       KD
)@@G@@  0                 ENTERED BY SLJ (BECAUSE OF  @G@@@@.                 KE
)@@G@@                    MORE THAN ONE WAY TO GET HERE)    @D@@@@          L,KF
)@@G@@U       A1,INITERR        GET ERROR TYPE  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. RETURN ERRKG
)@@G@@OR TYPE/CODE TO CALLER  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ERREXT1   LA,U      A2,0      KH
)@@G@@        NO ERROR CODE INVOLVED@D@@@@ERREXT2   TNZ       FORPKT          KI
)@@G@@  FORTRAN CALL ?  @E@@@@          J         ERRASM            NO. SKIP SKJ
)@@G@@TATUS STORE @E@@@@          LX        X11,FORPKT        LOAD PACKET ADDRKK
)@@G@@ESS   @E@@@@          LX,U      X11,*ECODE,X11    POINT TO ERROR CELLS  KL
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DS        A1,,X11           STOTRE ERROR CODE FOR USER  KM
)@@G@@@F@@@@ERRASM    LX,H1     X11,SAVX11        LOAD ERROR RETURN POINT     KN
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        DEBUG     @E@@@@          TNZ       INTERNAL  KO
)@@G@@        INTENRAL DIRLNK$ CALL?@E@@@@          SLJ       TOFF$           KP
)@@G@@  NO, TURN OFF TRACE    @F@@@@          SZ        INTERNAL          CLEAKQ
)@@G@@R INTERNAL-DIRLNK$ FLAG @#@@@@          OFF     @E@@@@          J       KR
)@@G@@  0,X11             TAKE ERROR RETURN     @#@@@@          END     ___ J KS
)@@G@@        ERREXT2           RETURN ERROR STATUS TO USER @[@@@@.     @ @@@@KT
)@@G@@. BAD DIRINT MASK SPECIFIED   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@E@@@@. @MFDKU
)@@G@@ - DIREC$ INITIALIZATION AND ERROR INTERFACE ROUTINES @[@@@@.     @^@@@@KV
)@@G@@$(1)      LIT       .   @^@@@@          AXR$      .   @G@@@@          COKW
)@@G@@NFIG    .                 DEFINE CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS   @D@@@@      KX
)@@G@@    EQUFS     .                 DEFINE TAGS     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. DIREKY
)@@G@@C$ INITIALIZATION INTERFACE ROUTINE @[@@@@.     @D@@@@DIRMASK   EQU     KZ
)@@G@@  016               DIRINT MASK     @B@@@@DG$       EQU       DGFILE='$$LA
)@@G@@--DGET--$$' @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DIR000*   . @ @@@@          ON        DG$=LB
)@@G@@0     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF DGET$ FILENAME IS NOT $$--DGET--$$, BETTER LC
