)@@G@@INFORM DIREC$.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          DL        A0,(DGFILE)     LD
)@@G@@  GET DGET$ FILENAME    @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIRFIL$       LET LE
)@@G@@DIREC$ KNOW WHAT IT IS  @ @@@@          OFF       DG$=0     @[@@@@.     LF
)@@G@@@G@@@@. IF THE N-OPTION IS SET, GET A NEW COPY OF THE DIRECTORY.  IF NOTLG
)@@G@@,     @E@@@@. USE THE COPY WE HAVE (IF WE DON'T HAVE ONE, GET ONE).     LH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@          TNZ       NPT               N OPTION? @G@@@@LI
)@@G@@          J         DIR010            NO, USE OLD COPY OF MFD, IF ANY   LJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIREND$       YES, RESET FOR NEW DGET$ COPLK
)@@G@@Y     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. GET DGET$ FILE AND DO THE DGET$ (UNLESS YOU ALLL
)@@G@@READY HAVE A GOOD ONE)  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@DIR010    LA,U      A0,DIRMASKLM
)@@G@@        GET DIRINT MASK @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIRINT$       DO DLN
)@@G@@GET$ AND SET UP DIREC$  @D@@@@          J         DIRECERR          ERROLO
)@@G@@R RETURN    @ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. USE LP
)@@G@@DIREC$'S TAG 'DIR$MFDF' AS A CONVENIENT WAY TO DETERMINE    @F@@@@. WHETLQ
)@@G@@HER DIRECTORY ITEMS CONFORM TO THE OLD MFD FORMAT OR TO     @D@@@@. THE LR
)@@G@@NEW (MFDF) FORMAT, AND SET MFD$F ACCORDINGLY.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTELS
)@@G@@ - IF DIREC$ IS NOT BEING USED, THE SINGLE-FILE ROUTINE MUST SET  @^@@@@LT
)@@G@@.        MFD$F PROPERLY.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          TZ        DIR$MFDF  LU
)@@G@@        DID DIRINT GET NEW FORMAT DGET$?  @F@@@@          SR        R15,LV
)@@G@@MFD$F         YES, SET NEW-FORMAT FLAG    @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMLW
)@@G@@FD    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LOAD CHECK/PRINT SEGMENT, AND RETURN TO MFD100LX
)@@G@@ IN MAIN SEGMENT. @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          L$OAD     CHEKPRTSG,MFD100LY
)@@G@@,1  . LOAD CHK/PRT SEG AND RETURN TO MFD100     @^@@@@/. DIREC$ ERROR ROLZ
)@@G@@UTINE @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ERRMSG    'MFD ERROR TYPE & CODE &'   DIREC$ ERRMA
)@@G@@OR MSG@G@@@@DIRECERR* LXI       X11,X11           SAVE RETURN ADDR IN UPMB
)@@G@@PER X11     @D@@@@          TE,U      A1,3              DIRSEC$ EOF?    MC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         ERR100            NO  @ @@@@          ON      MD
)@@G@@  SORTOK    @D@@@@          TZ        SORT              SORT DESIRED?   ME
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         DOSORT            YES, DO IT@ @@@@          OFMF
)@@G@@F       SORTOK    @D@@@@          J         MFD600            NO, FINISHMG
)@@G@@ UP   @E@@@@ERR100    DS        A1,ECODE          SAVE ERROR TYPE & CODEMH
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK            OPEN EDIT @E@@@@          E$MI
)@@G@@MSG     ERRMSG            EDIT START OF MSG     @D@@@@          E$DECV  MJ
)@@G@@  ECODE             EDIT ERROR TYPE @E@@@@          TNZ       ECODE+1   MK
)@@G@@        ERROR CODE PRESENT?   @D@@@@          J         ERR200          ML
)@@G@@  NO, PRINT MSG   @D@@@@          E$MSGR    .                 CONTINUE MMM
)@@G@@SG    @D@@@@          E$OCTF    12,ECODE+1        EDIT ERROR CODE @C@@@@MN
)@@G@@ERR200    P$RINT    POUT              PRINT MSG @C@@@@          L       MO
)@@G@@  A0,X11            GET X11   @F@@@@          SSL       A0,18           MP
)@@G@@  ISOLATE DIRECERR RTN SAVE   @D@@@@          LXI,U     X11,0           MQ
)@@G@@  PREVENT LOOPS   @ @@@@          AN,U      A0,LNKRTN @F@@@@          SRMR
)@@G@@        R15,BMI1          MARK AS BAD MAIN ITEM SEC 1 @F@@@@          JZMS
)@@G@@        A0,CHK220         TO 'CHK220' IF FROM 'LNKRTN'@C@@@@          J MT
)@@G@@        MFD700            ELSE EXIT @#@@@@          END     ___O, USE OLMU
)@@G@@D COPY OF MFD, IF ANY   @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,DIREND$       YES,MV
)@@G@@ RESET FOR NEW DGET$ COP*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@$(1)      AXR$      .   @[@@@@MW
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. DYNAMIC SEGMENT MCORE$ ROUTINE - ADAPTED FROM 'DLOAD$' RLIMX
)@@G@@B$ ELEMENT  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DSEG*     LSSL      A1,2              CONVMY
)@@G@@ERT SEGID TO SLT INDEX  @E@@@@          A,U       A1,SLT$           GET MZ
)@@G@@ADDR OF SLT ENTRY @F@@@@          L,S2      A0,,A1            TEST IF SENA
)@@G@@G DEFINED AS DSEG @ @@@@          TE,U      A0,011    @ @@@@          TNNB
)@@G@@E,U     A0,010    @E@@@@          J         $+2               IS A DSEG NC
)@@G@@- CONTINUE  @D@@@@          ER        EABT$             MUST BE A DSEG  ND
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,H1      A0,1,A1           LOAD IBANK ADDR NEEDED@G@@@@NE
)@@G@@          L,S2      A2,SLT$           DETERMINE IF SLT FORMAT COMPLEX   NF
)@@G@@@ @@@@          TNE,U     A2,022    @E@@@@          J         DLOAD0    NG
)@@G@@        IF COMPLEX, DLOAD0    @E@@@@          JZ        A0,$+3          NH
)@@G@@  CHECK FOR VOID SEGMENT@G@@@@          A         A0,(1*/34)        SET NI
)@@G@@PROGRAM-WIDE BIT FOR MCORE    @D@@@@          ER        MCORE$          NJ
)@@G@@  EXPAND IBANK    @E@@@@          L,H1      A0,2,A1           LOAD DBANKNK
)@@G@@ ADDR NEEDED@E@@@@          JZ        A0,DLOAD2         CHECK FOR VOID SNL
)@@G@@EG    @D@@@@          A         A0,(1*/34)        SET PGM-WIDE BIT@D@@@@NM
)@@G@@          ER        MCORE$            EXPAND DBANK    @C@@@@          J NN
)@@G@@        DLOAD2            CONTINUE  @F@@@@DLOAD0    L         A2,A1     NO
)@@G@@        SAVE INITIAL SLT ENTRY ADDR @E@@@@DLOAD1    JZ        A0,$+4    NP
)@@G@@        CHECK FOR VOID SEG    @E@@@@          LXI,T1    A0,2,A2         NQ
)@@G@@  LOAD BDI FOR THIS BANK@D@@@@          A         A0,(1*/34)        SET NR
)@@G@@PGM-WIDE BIT@D@@@@          ER        MCORE$            EXPAND BANK     NS
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,H2      A2,2,A2           LOAD LINK TO NEXT EXTENSION NT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          JZ        A2,DLOAD2         JUMP IF ALL EXTENSIONS DONE NU
)@@G@@@E@@@@          A,U       A2,SLT$           COMPUTE EXTENSION ADDR@E@@@@NV
)@@G@@          L,H1      A0,1,A2           LOAD BANK ADDR NEEDED @F@@@@      NW
)@@G@@    J         DLOAD1            CONTINUE EXPANSION LOOP     @F@@@@DLOAD2NX
)@@G@@    L,U       A2,024            MARK SEG AS OVERLAY SEG     @ @@@@      NY
)@@G@@    S,S2      A2,,A1    @C@@@@          J         0,X11             RETUNZ
)@@G@@RN    @#@@@@          END     ___B@@@@@@@@0586AA*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@. @MFDOA
)@@G@@ HEADING ROUTINE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          AXR$      .   @G@@@@      OB
)@@G@@    CONFIG    .                 DEFINE CONFIGUARTION PARAMETERS   @D@@@@OC
)@@G@@          EQUFS     .                 DEFINE TAGS     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@OD
)@@G@@PRT       FORM      12,6,18           FORMAT T1,S3,H2 @[@@@@.     @D@@@@OE
)@@G@@. VARIABLE-LENGTH TABLE OF HEADING PRINT$ PACKETS     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@OF
)@@G@@P3        . @ @@@@          ON        LEGEND    @A@@@@          PRT     OG
)@@G@@  2,LG1,LEGND1    @A@@@@          PRT       1,LG2,LEGND2    @A@@@@      OH
)@@G@@    PRT       1,LG3,LEGND3    @A@@@@          PRT       1,LG4,LEGND4    OI
)@@G@@@A@@@@          PRT       1,LG5,LEGND5    @A@@@@          PRT       1,LGOJ
)@@G@@6,LEGND6    @A@@@@          PRT       1,LG7,LEGND7    @A@@@@          PROK
)@@G@@T       1,LG8,LEGND8    @A@@@@          PRT       1,LG9,LEGND9    @A@@@@OL
)@@G@@          PRT       1,LG10,LEGND10  @ @@@@P4        PRT       -0,22,LIN5OM
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       LEGEND    @ @@@@          ON        LEGEND=0  ON
)@@G@@@ @@@@P4        PRT       2,22,LIN5 @ @@@@          OFF       LEGEND=0  OO
)@@G@@@ @@@@          PRT       1,22,LIN6 @ @@@@          PRT       1,22,LIN7 OP
)@@G@@@F@@@@P4L       EQU       $-P4              NUMBER OF HEADING LINES     OQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@P3L       EQU       $-P3              SAME, INCLUDING LEGEND LINESOR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        LEGEND    @D@@@@LEGND1    'SPECIALOS
)@@G@@ CHARACTER MEANINGS (COLS. 42,43)'  @ @@@@LG1       EQU       $-LEGND1  OT
)@@G@@@A@@@@LEGND2    +'  @ : '+(WRNCHR*/18)    @A@@@@          'WARNING ONLY OU
)@@G@@DISABLED'   @ @@@@LG2       EQU       $-LEGND2  @A@@@@LEGND3    +'  @ : OV
)@@G@@'+(HDWCHR*/18)    @ @@@@          'HARDWARE DISABLED' @ @@@@LG3       EQOW
)@@G@@U       $-LEGND3  @A@@@@LEGND4    +'  @ : '+(BBTCHR*/18)    @ @@@@      OX
)@@G@@    'BAD BACKUP TAPE'   @ @@@@LG4       EQU       $-LEGND4  @A@@@@LEGND5OY
)@@G@@    +'  @ : '+(BMICHR*/18)    @A@@@@          'BAD MAIN ITEM SECTOR 1'  OZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@LG5       EQU       $-LEGND5  @A@@@@LEGND6    +'  @ : '+(LPSCHR*/1PA
)@@G@@8)    @A@@@@          'LAPSE ENTRIES EXIST'     @ @@@@LG6       EQU     PB
)@@G@@  $-LEGND6  @A@@@@LEGND7    +'  @ : '+(NOBCHR*/18)    @ @@@@          'NPC
)@@G@@O BACKUP EXISTS'  @ @@@@LG7       EQU       $-LEGND7  @A@@@@LEGND8    +'PD
)@@G@@  @ : '+(BNCCHR*/18)    @ @@@@          'BACKUP NOT CURRENT'@ @@@@LG8   PE
)@@G@@    EQU       $-LEGND8  @A@@@@LEGND9    +'  @ : '+(DELCHR*/18)    @B@@@@PF
)@@G@@          'FILE MARKED FOR DELETION OR'   @ @@@@LG9       EQU       $-LEPG
)@@G@@GND9  @D@@@@LEGND10   '      ASSIGNED WITH ''U'' OR ''C'' OPTIONS'@ @@@@PH
)@@G@@LG10      EQU       $-LEGND10 @ @@@@          OFF       LEGEND    @C@@@@PI
)@@G@@LIN5      'MAX               NO.   LAST  HIGHES'@C@@@@          'T TOTALPJ
)@@G@@                             '@C@@@@          '                         PK
)@@G@@ CATALOG   '@A@@@@          'BACKUP TAPE    CREATED  '@C@@@@LIN6      'GPL
)@@G@@RAN   OPT EQUP   ASG   REF.      TR'@C@@@@          'ACK              FIPM
)@@G@@LENAME           '@C@@@@          '  ACCOUNT       PROJECT     DATE   N'PN
)@@G@@@A@@@@          'UMBER POS BLK DATE TIME '@]@@@@LIN7      . @A@@@@      PO
)@@G@@    DO        22 , '------'   @]@@@@/$(1)     . @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ENTRPP
)@@G@@Y POINT FOR INITIAL HEADING, WITH LEGEND IF CONFIGURED.     @#@@@@. CALLPQ
)@@G@@ED BY INIT2.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@HDG100*   LR,U      R1,P3L-1          NUMBPR
)@@G@@ER OF HEADING LINES - 1 @E@@@@.                                        IPS
)@@G@@NCLUDING LEGEND   @E@@@@          LA,U      A3,P3             FIRST LINEPT
)@@G@@ OF HEADING @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,HDG300        PRINT THE HEADINPU
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@          L$OAD     INSEG,IN2200,1    RETURN TO INITIALIZATIPV
)@@G@@ON ROUTINE  @ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ENTRPW
)@@G@@Y POINT USED BY 'PRINT' ROUTINE TO REPRINT THE HEADING IF   @E@@@@. 'BREPX
)@@G@@AK' WAS SPECIFIED AND THE SORT KEY VALUE HAS CHANGED. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@PY
)@@G@@HDG200*   LR,U      R1,P4L-1          NUMBER OF HEADING LINES - 1 @E@@@@PZ
)@@G@@.                                        EXCLUDING LEGEND   @E@@@@      QA
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,P4             FIRST LINE OF HEADING @E@@@@          LMQB
)@@G@@J       X11,HDG300        PRINT THE HEADING     @F@@@@          L$OAD   QC
)@@G@@  CHEKPRTSG,PR0095,1  . RETURN TO PRINT ROUTINE @ @@@@          OFF     QD
)@@G@@  BRKOK     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. SUBROUTINE TO PRINT HEADING @[@@@@.     QE
)@@G@@@ @@@@. ENTER VIA:  LMJ  X11,HDG300 @C@@@@.      WITH:  R1 = NUMBER OF LQF
)@@G@@INES TO PRINT (-1)@C@@@@.             A3 = ADDRESS OF FIRST PRINT PACKETQG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@HDG300    JNZ       LONGLIST,HDG310   LONG LISTING?   QH
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                                     YES, HDG310     @C@@@@      QI
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,12             NO, SHORT @F@@@@          LA,U      A1,PQJ
)@@G@@4L-1          NUMBER OF HEADING LINES - 1 @F@@@@          SA,S3     A2,PQK
)@@G@@4,A1          SHORTEN EACH LINE OF HEADING@E@@@@          JGD       A1,$QL
)@@G@@-1               FROM 22 TO 12 WORDS@G@@@@HDG310    LXI,U     A3,1      QM
)@@G@@        SET INCREMENT FOR PRINT LINE INDEX@D@@@@HDG320    LA        A0,,QN
)@@G@@*A3           GET PRINT PACKET@E@@@@          ER        PRINT$          QO
)@@G@@  PRINT LINE OF HEADING @D@@@@          JGD       R1,HDG320         PRINQP
)@@G@@T ALL LINES @D@@@@          J         0,X11             RETURN TO CALLERQQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___       'FILE MARKED FOR DELETION OR'   @ @@@@QR
)@@G@@LG9       EQU       $-LEGND9  @D@@@@LEGND10   ' *[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@@. @MFDQS
)@@G@@ INITIALIZATION - PHASE 2     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          AXR$      .   QT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CONFIG    .                 DEFINE CONFIG PARAMETERS    QU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          EQUFS     .                 DEFINE EQUF'S   @[@@@@.     QV
)@@G@@@D@@@@PRT       FORM      12,6,18           PRINT$ FORM     @[@@@@.     QW
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        PRVOPS    @C@@@@ERR3      'ILLEGAL USE OF PRIVQX
)@@G@@ILEGED OPTION'    @A@@@@ERR3P     PRT       2,$-ERR3,ERR3   @E@@@@OPRIV QY
)@@G@@    +         PRVOPS            PRIVILEGED OPTIONS    @ @@@@          OFQZ
)@@G@@F       PRVOPS    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. REMOTE LOAD TABLE FOR C/Y OPTION SRA
)@@G@@PEC MASK, ETC.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ACLD      LA,S1     A0,0,X2         RB
)@@G@@  GENERAL LOAD TABLE    @ @@@@          LA,S2     A0,0,X2   @ @@@@      RC
)@@G@@    LA,S3     A0,0,X2   @ @@@@          LA,S4     A0,0,X2   @ @@@@      RD
)@@G@@    LA,S5     A0,0,X2   @ @@@@          LA,S6     A0,0,X2   @ @@@@      RE
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A0,1,X2   @ @@@@          LA,S2     A0,1,X2   @ @@@@      RF
)@@G@@    LA,S3     A0,1,X2   @ @@@@          LA,S4     A0,1,X2   @ @@@@      RG
)@@G@@    LA,S5     A0,1,X2   @ @@@@          LA,S6     A0,1,X2   @[@@@@.     RH
)@@G@@@C@@@@. REMOTE STORE TABLE FOR C/Y OPTION SPEC MASK   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@RI
)@@G@@ACST      SZ,S1     ACMASK            PARTIAL SPEC STORE TABLE    @ @@@@RJ
)@@G@@          SZ,S2     ACMASK    @ @@@@          SZ,S3     ACMASK    @ @@@@RK
)@@G@@          SZ,S4     ACMASK    @ @@@@          SZ,S5     ACMASK    @ @@@@RL
)@@G@@          SZ,S6     ACMASK    @ @@@@          SZ,S1     ACMASK+1  @ @@@@RM
)@@G@@          SZ,S2     ACMASK+1  @ @@@@          SZ,S3     ACMASK+1  @ @@@@RN
)@@G@@          SZ,S4     ACMASK+1  @ @@@@          SZ,S5     ACMASK+1  @ @@@@RO
)@@G@@          SZ,S6     ACMASK+1  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        OLDSRP
)@@G@@TUFF  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. LOAD AND STORE TABLES FOR DATE CONVERSION     RQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@DATELD    LA,T1     A0,INDT           FIELDATA MONTH  RR
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LA,T2     A0,INDT           DAY @B@@@@          LA,T3   RS
)@@G@@  A0,INDT           YEAR@D@@@@DATEST    SA,S5     A0,DATREF         BINART
)@@G@@RY MONTH    @B@@@@          SA,S6     A0,DATREF         DAY @B@@@@      RU
)@@G@@    SA,S4     A0,DATREF         YEAR@[@@@@.     @C@@@@INDT      RES     RV
)@@G@@  1                 INPUT DATE@ @@@@NOOP      NOP       0,0,0     @E@@@@RW
)@@G@@PPKT      PRT       1,1,INDT          ECHO PRINT PACKET     @G@@@@TPKT  RX
)@@G@@    PRT       1,2,DMSG          REQUEST DATE (OR PARAMTERS) PKT   @A@@@@RY
)@@G@@          +         DATERR,INDT     @E@@@@DMSG      'ENTER DATE: '      RZ
)@@G@@        D-OPTION DATE REQUEST @F@@@@RMSG      'PARAMETER:  '            SA
)@@G@@  R-OPTION PARAMETER REQUEST  @ @@@@DATERM    'DATE SPEC ERROR'   @ @@@@SB
)@@G@@PRMERM    'PARAMETER ERROR'   @ @@@@          OFF       OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@SC
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. MCT$ PACKET AND BUFFER (SEE COMMENTS AT TAG 'MCTEQ' IN ELESD
)@@G@@MENT 'MFD'  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MCTPK     +         3,MCT             MCT$SE
)@@G@@ PACKET     @D@@@@          +         030,0             GET WORDS 0-027 SF
)@@G@@@D@@@@MCT       RES       030               MCT$ BUFFER     @C@@@@/$(1),SG
)@@G@@IN2000* .  PHASE 2 OF @MFD INITIALIZATION @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GET USER'SSH
)@@G@@ PCT.  CHECK FOR ILLEGAL USE OF PRIVILEGED OPTIONS    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@SI
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(21,PCT)       SET TO READ PCT @C@@@@          ERSJ
)@@G@@        PCT$              DO IT     @D@@@@          LA,S2     A0,PCT+4  SK
)@@G@@        GET 'ABORT FLAG'@E@@@@          TEP,U     A0,040            IS USL
)@@G@@SER PRIVILEGED?   @F@@@@          SR        R15,PRIVLGD       YES, SET PSM
)@@G@@RIVILEGED FLAG    @G@@@@          LA        A0,(10,PROJPK)    DO FITEM$ SN
)@@G@@OF DIAG$ TO PICK UP REAL@H@@@@.                                     PROJSO
)@@G@@ECT (PCT COULD HAVE @QUAL VALUE)    @E@@@@          ER        FITEM$    SP
)@@G@@        PUTS PROJ IN PCT+2    @ @@@@          ON        PRVOPS    @G@@@@SQ
)@@G@@          LA        A0,OPTWRD         GET OPTION BITS SAVED BY INIT1    SR
)@@G@@@F@@@@          AND       A0,OPRIV          MASK OUT PRIVILEGED OPTIONS SS
)@@G@@@F@@@@          JZ        A1,IN2010         IF NONE BEING USED, GO ON   ST
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TNZ       PRIVLGD           IS USER PRIVILEGED?   @G@@@@SU
)@@G@@          J         IN2410            NO, ISSUE ERROR MESSAGE AND EXIT  SV
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       PRVOPS    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CHECK POLISH TABSW
)@@G@@LE FOR CORRECTNESS@[@@@@.     @]@@@@IN2010    . @^@@@@          ON      SX
)@@G@@  NSSP@ @@@@          ON        POLDBG    @E@@@@          L$OAD     PR2SSY
)@@G@@G,SN900,1     JUMP TO SNAP$ ROUTINE @F@@@@IN2020*   .                   SZ
)@@G@@        SNAP$ ROUTINE RETURNS HERE  @ @@@@          OFF       POLDBG    TA
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TZ        AOX               ANY POLISH SPECS?     @E@@@@TB
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,POLTRAN       CHECK POLISH TABLE    @^@@@@      TC
)@@G@@    OFF       NSSP@ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@TD
)@@G@@. MODIFY CODE IF OPTION REVERSAL IS SET   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          LATE
)@@G@@        A0,NOOP           GET A NOP @E@@@@          TP        TPT       TF
)@@G@@        IS T-OPTION REVERSED? @H@@@@          SA        A0,REVT         TG
)@@G@@  YES, IF NOT TAPE FILE, IGNORE T-OPT     @C@@@@          LA,H1     A0,RTH
)@@G@@EVO           GET JZ    @D@@@@          A,U       A0,0400           CHANTI
)@@G@@GE TO JNZ   @E@@@@          TP        OPT               O-OPTION REVERSETJ
)@@G@@D?    @D@@@@          SA,H1     A0,REVO           YES, PUT IT BACK@ @@@@TK
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,055    @E@@@@          TP        DPT             TL
)@@G@@  D-OPTION REVERSED?    @E@@@@          SA,S1     A0,REVD           YES,TM
)@@G@@ CHANGE TLE TO TG @ @@@@          LA,U      A0,044    @E@@@@          TPTN
)@@G@@        RPT               R-OPTION REVERSED?    @E@@@@          SA,S1   TO
)@@G@@  A0,REVR           YES, CHANGE TOP TO TEP@E@@@@          TP        VPT TP
)@@G@@              V-OPTION REVERSED?    @E@@@@          SA,S1     A0,REVV   TQ
)@@G@@        YES, CHANGE TOP TO TEP@E@@@@          TP        GPT             TR
)@@G@@  G-OPTION REVERSED?    @E@@@@          SA,S1     A0,REVG           YES,TS
)@@G@@ CHANGE TOP TO TEP@ @@@@          LA,U      A0,060    @E@@@@          TPTT
)@@G@@        UPT               U-OPTION REVERSED?    @E@@@@          SA,S1   TU
)@@G@@  A0,UNCHEK         YES, CHANGE TN TO TP  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CHECK FOR TV
)@@G@@D AND R OPTIONS   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TZ        DPT             TW
)@@G@@  D-OPTION SET?   @D@@@@          J         IN2100            YES, HANDLTX
)@@G@@E IT  @C@@@@          TZ        RPT               R-OPTION? @B@@@@      TY
)@@G@@    J         IN2130            YES @D@@@@          J         IN2140    TZ
)@@G@@        NO, SO GO ON    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. D-OPTION ROUTINE - DO TREAD UA
)@@G@@TO PICK UP DATE TO CHECK AGAINST    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN2100    LA,U    UB
)@@G@@  A0,TPKT           GET TREAD PACKET@D@@@@          ER        TREAD$    UC
)@@G@@        ASK FOR DATE    @E@@@@          SA        A0,A1             SAVEUD
)@@G@@ INPUT WORD COUNT @C@@@@          P$RINT    PPKT              ECHO REPLYUE
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,,A1            INPUT WORD COUNT@C@@@@      UF
)@@G@@    TE,U      A0,1              1 WORD?   @E@@@@          J         DATEUG
)@@G@@RR            NO, DATE INPUT ERROR  @D@@@@          LA,U      A2,2      UH
)@@G@@        FOR MM,DD,YY... @G@@@@IN2110    EX        DATELD,A2         CONVUI
)@@G@@ERT FD DATE TO TDATE$ FORMAT  @E@@@@          ANA,U     A0,06060        UJ
)@@G@@  STRIP OFF FIELDATA    @D@@@@          DSL       A0,6              GET UK
)@@G@@UNITS IN A1 @D@@@@          SSL       A1,30             SHIFT THEM DOWN UL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          MSI,U     A0,10             MULTIPLY TENS BY TEN  @C@@@@UM
)@@G@@          AA        A0,A1             ADD UNITS @C@@@@          TNE,U   UN
)@@G@@  A2,2              YEAR?     @D@@@@          ANA,U     A0,64           UO
)@@G@@  YES, MAKE MOD 64@D@@@@          EX        DATEST,A2         STORE IN MUP
)@@G@@AKD   @E@@@@          JGD       A2,IN2110         CONTINUE FOR DD,YY    UQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TZ        RPT               R-OPTION ALSO SET?    @F@@@@UR
)@@G@@          J         IN2130            YES, GO TO R-OPTION ROUTINE @E@@@@US
)@@G@@          J         IN2140            NO, PRINT HEADING     @[@@@@.     UT
)@@G@@@D@@@@DATERR    LA        A0,( PRT 1,3,DATERM)  GET MSG     @E@@@@      UU
)@@G@@    J         MFD900            PRINT IT AND EXIT     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@UV
)@@G@@PRMERR    LA        A0,( PRT 1,3,PRMERM)  GET MSG     @E@@@@          J UW
)@@G@@        MFD900            PRINT IT AND EXIT     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. R-OPUX
)@@G@@TION ROUTINE - REQUEST PARAMETER FOR TYPE OF DISABLE TO CHECK     @[@@@@UY
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@IN2130    LA,U      A0,RMSG           GET ADDR OF PARAMETERSUZ
)@@G@@ MSG  @E@@@@          SA,H2     A0,TPKT           STORE IN TREAD$ PACKETVA
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,PRMERR         GET EOF ADDR    @E@@@@      VB
)@@G@@    SA,H1     A0,TPKT+1         STORE IN TREAD$ PKT   @ @@@@          LAVC
)@@G@@,U      A0,TPKT   @E@@@@          ER        TREAD$            REQUEST PAVD
)@@G@@RAMETERS    @E@@@@          SA        A0,A1             SAVE INPUT WORD VE
)@@G@@COUNT @C@@@@          P$RINT    PPKT              ECHO REPLY@D@@@@      VF
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,,A1            INPUT WORD COUNT@C@@@@          TE,U    VG
)@@G@@  A0,1              ONE WORD? @C@@@@          J         PRMERR          VH
)@@G@@  NO, ERROR @G@@@@          L,H1      A0,INDT           PARAMETER FOR SEVI
)@@G@@ARCH (3 CHARS)    @F@@@@          LR,U      R1,RPRL           REPEAT COUVJ
)@@G@@NT (TABLE LENGTH) @C@@@@          LA        A1,(1,0)          LOAD INDEXVK
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SE,H1     A0,RPR,*A1        TEST FOR PARAMETERS IN TABLEVL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         PRMERR            ILLEGAL PARAMETER     @E@@@@VM
)@@G@@          SA        A1,DISDX          STORE PARAMETER INDEX @ @@@@      VN
)@@G@@    OFF       OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. SET BATCH/DEMAND MODE @[@@@@VO
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@IN2140    SR        R15,LONGLIST      ASSUME LONG LISTING MOVP
)@@G@@DE    @D@@@@          TZ        SPT               IS S-OPTION SET?@G@@@@VQ
)@@G@@          J         IN2150            YES, REVERSE MEANING OF H-OPTION  VR
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TNE,U     A14,4             NOT DEMAND?     @D@@@@      VS
)@@G@@    TZ        LPT               OR L-OPTION SET?@F@@@@          J       VT
)@@G@@  IN2160            YES, LEAVE H-OPTION AS IS   @G@@@@          LA      VU
)@@G@@  A2,OPTWRD         WE'RE DEMAND: GET OPTION WORD     @E@@@@          TEVV
)@@G@@P       A2,(1*/34)        ARE WE BREAKPOINTED?  @F@@@@          J       VW
)@@G@@  IN2160            YES, ASSUME 'BATCH' MODE IF @F@@@@.                 VX
)@@G@@                    NEITHER L NOR S-OPT IS GIVEN@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DEMAVY
)@@G@@ND MODE - SET FOR SHORT LISTING, AND REVERSE MEANING OF H-OPTION  @[@@@@VZ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IN2150    SZ        LONGLIST          SET SHORT-LISTING MODEWA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,HPT            GET USER'S H-OPTION SETTING WB
)@@G@@@C@@@@          XOR,U     A0,1              REVERSE IT@F@@@@          SAWC
)@@G@@        A1,HPT            STORE NEW H-OPTION SETTING  @F@@@@IN2160    TNWD
)@@G@@Z       HPT               H-OPTION (NO HEADING) SET?  @E@@@@          TZWE
)@@G@@        JPT               NO, TEST FOR J-OPTION @G@@@@          J       WF
)@@G@@  IN2200            H OR J OPTION, SO DON'T PRINT     @H@@@@          ONWG
)@@G@@        WOPTOK            **************************************  @G@@@@WH
)@@G@@          JNZ       LONGLIST,IN2170   LONG LISTING? YES, PRINT HEADING  WI
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TZ        WPT               DEMAND WITH W-OPTION? @E@@@@WJ
)@@G@@          TZ        SPT               BUT S-OPTION SET?     @E@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    J         IN2170            YES, PRINT HEADING    @D@@@@          J WL
)@@G@@        IN2200            NO, SKIP HEADING@H@@@@          OFF       WOPTWM
)@@G@@OK            **************************************  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@WN
)@@G@@. PRINT HEADING   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN2170    L$OAD     HDGSEG,HDG100,1 WO
)@@G@@  LOAD HDGSEG AND PRINT THE HEADING @E@@@@.                             WP
)@@G@@        (RETURN TO IN2200)    @]@@@@/IN2200*  . @ @@@@          ON      WQ
)@@G@@  OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SELECT SECONDARY ATTRIBUTE CHECK ROUTINEWR
)@@G@@ BASED ON OPTIONS AND SPEC2   @F@@@@. SIZE, IF GIVEN.  STORE ROUTINE ADDWS
)@@G@@RESS IN 'SZOPT', AND SIZE, IF @^@@@@. GIVEN, IN 'SZOPT+1'.  @[@@@@.     WT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TNZ       SIZFLG            SPEC2 (TRACK SIZE) GIVEN?   WU
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         IN2220            NO  @D@@@@          LA,U    WV
)@@G@@  A0,2              SET FOR SPEC 2  @D@@@@          SA        A0,SPECN  WW
)@@G@@        STORE FOR SPECER@F@@@@          L         A1,SIZFLG         GET WX
)@@G@@NO. OF CHARS IN SPEC2   @D@@@@          AN,U      A1,1              LESSWY
)@@G@@ 1 FOR JGD  @F@@@@          L         X1,(1,0)          INITIALIZE EX REWZ
)@@G@@MOTE INDEX  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NORMALLY, ALL FILES WHICH ARE AT LEAST <XA
)@@G@@SPEC2> TRACKS IN SIZE WILL    @H@@@@. BE LISTED, BUT IF FIRST CHAR OF SPXB
)@@G@@EC2 IS '-', THEN TEST SHOULD BE REVERSED. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LAXC
)@@G@@,S1     A0,SIZE           GET 1ST CHAR OF SAVED SPEC2 @F@@@@          TEXD
)@@G@@,U      A0,'-'            WANT TO DO SIZE <= SPEC2?   @G@@@@          J XE
)@@G@@        IN2210            NO, HANDLE NORMAL SIZE > SPEC2    @G@@@@      XF
)@@G@@    TNZ       A1                IS THE '-' THE ONLY CHARACTER?    @D@@@@XG
)@@G@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        YES, SPEC ERROR @G@@@@          ANXH
)@@G@@,U      A1,1,*X1          -1 TO IGNORE DASH, AND INC X1     @E@@@@      XI
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A2,SZLOD          GET SZLOD OPCODE (TG) @F@@@@          LAXJ
)@@G@@,S1     A3,SZBAK          GET SZBAK OP CODE (TLE)     @E@@@@          SAXK
)@@G@@,S1     A3,SZLOD          AND SWITCH THEM AROUND@ @@@@          SA,S1   XL
)@@G@@  A2,SZBAK  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CONVERT SIZE SPEC FROM DECIMAL FIELDATA XM
)@@G@@TO BINARY   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN2210    L,U       X2,SIZE           X2 =XN
)@@G@@ ADDR OF SAVED SPEC2    @E@@@@          LA,U      A3,0              INITXO
)@@G@@IALIZE ACCUMULATOR@C@@@@IN2215    EX        ACLD,*X1          GET A CHARXP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AN,U      A0,060            STRIP OFF FIELDATA    @D@@@@XQ
)@@G@@          TP        A0                IS IT A NUMBER? @D@@@@          LMXR
)@@G@@J       X10,SPECER        NO, SPEC ERROR  @D@@@@          MSI,U     A3,1XS

)@@G@@  VALUE TO BINARY @ @@@@          JGD       A1,IN2215 @F@@@@          LAXU
)@@G@@,U      A2,SZCHK          SET FOR SIZE CHECK ROUTINE  @C@@@@          J XV
)@@G@@        IN2230            GO ON     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. CHECK FOR U-OPTIXW
)@@G@@ON.  IF SET, SECONDARY CHECK ROUTINE = UNOPT,   @^@@@@. IF NOT, = NSZOPTXX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN2220    LA,U      A2,NSZOPT         ASSUME NO XY
)@@G@@SIZE, ETC., CHECK @D@@@@          TZ        UPT               U-OPTION SXZ

)@@G@@ADED TEST   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. STORE SECONDARY ROUTINE ADDR (AND CONVERYB
)@@G@@TED SIZE, IF SPEC'D)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN2230    DS        A2,SZOPT  YC

)@@G@@              (AND SIZE, IF APPLICABLE)   @ @@@@          OFF       OLDSYE
)@@G@@TUFF  @D@@@@          TZ        YPT               IS Y-OPTION SET?@E@@@@YF
)@@G@@          SR        R15,CPT           YES, ASSUME C-OPTION  @[@@@@.     YG
)@@G@@@D@@@@. IF SINGLE-FILE MODE IS SET, HANDLE IT.  OTHERWISE,  @H@@@@. SEARYH
)@@G@@CH OPTION TABLE FOR FIRST PRIMARY ATTRIBUTE OPTION WHICH IS SET, AND    YI
)@@G@@@H@@@@. JUMP TO THE APPROPRIATE ROUTINE.  IF OPTION IS NOT SET, OR IF ITYJ
)@@G@@ IS NOT     @C@@@@. A PRIMARY ATTRIBUTE OPTION, CONTINUE SEARCH.  @F@@@@YK
)@@G@@. IF NO PRIMARY ATTRIBUTE OPTIONS ARE SET, SOMETHING IS WRONG.    @[@@@@YL
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@          TZ        SFMODE            SINGLE-FILE MODE?     YM

)@@G@@$             SHOULD NOT GET HERE!  @F@@@@          J         *OPTIONS-1YT

)@@G@@ FOR CHECK ROUTINE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. IF THE QUALIFIER AND FILENAME TO BAU

)@@G@@@B@@@@. Z-OPTION -- LIST ALL FILES IF PRIVILEGED@[@@@@.     @E@@@@ZOPT* BH

)@@G@@@D@@@@. SEE COMMENTS ABOVE TAG 'MCTEQ' IN ELEMENT 'MFD'     @[@@@@.     BN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          L,U       A0,MCTPK          GET MCT$ PKT    @F@@@@      BO
)@@G@@    ER        MCT$              GET A PORTION OF THE MCT    @D@@@@      BP

)@@G@@        RETRIEVE SPECIFIC MNEMONICS @H@@@@IN2385    L$OAD     QFSEG,QF00BY
)@@G@@0,1     LOAD AND JUMP TO SINGLE-FILE SEGMENT    @ @@@@. X-OPTION LIST EXBZ
)@@G@@EC FILES    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XOPT*     LX,U      X9,XXOPT          EXECCA
)@@G@@ FILE ROUTINE     @D@@@@          J         IN2430            START UP DCB
)@@G@@IREC$ @ @@@@          ON        PRVOPS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. NON-PRIVILCC

)@@G@@@D@@@@          TZ,S2     MFD$+1            VERSION GIVEN?  @E@@@@      CK

)@@G@@,U      X9,KKOPT          SET UP PACK I.D. LABEL@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. DIRECM
)@@G@@C$ IS NEEDED, SO WE MUST LOAD SEGMENT DIRSEG AND RELINQUISH CONTROL TO  CN
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THE DIREC$ INITIALIZATION INTERFACE ROUTINE, WHICH RETURNS TO MFCO
)@@G@@D100. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN2430    L,U       A1,DIRSEG         PREPARE FOCP
)@@G@@R LOADING DIREC$ SEG    @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,DSEG          DO NCQ
)@@G@@ECESSARY MCORE    @G@@@@          L$OAD     DIRSEG,DIR000,1   JUMP TO DICR
)@@G@@REC$ INTERFACE ROUTINE  @F@@@@/.    PARTIAL SPEC ROUTINE - $'S IN SPEC FCS
)@@G@@IELD ARE TRANSPARENT    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PARTIAL   LA,U      A1,11     CT
)@@G@@        FOR 12 CHARS    @E@@@@          EX        ACLD,A1           GET CU
)@@G@@1 CHAR OF SPEC    @C@@@@          TNE,U     A0,'$'            IS IT A $?CV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          EX        ACST,A1           YES, STORE ZERO IN MASK     CW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JGD       A1,PARTIAL+1      CONTINUE FOR 12 CHARS @F@@@@CX
)@@G@@          AND       A10,ACMASK+1      MASK OUT UNWANTED CHARS     @ @@@@CY
)@@G@@          AND       A9,ACMASK @F@@@@          DJZ       A10,IN2510      CZ
)@@G@@  DISALLOW SPEC OF ALL $'S    @F@@@@          DS        A10,MFD$+9      DA
)@@G@@  STORE IN SPEC FIELD AGAIN   @C@@@@          J         0,X11           DB
)@@G@@  RETURN    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN2510    LA,U      A0,1              SET DC
)@@G@@FOR SPEC 1  @D@@@@          SA        A0,SPECN          SAVE FOR SPECER DD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        EDIT SPEC ERROR @#@@@@      DE
)@@G@@    END     ___ S         A0,MCTPK+1        SET IN MCT$ PKT @H@@@@      DF
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,MCTEQ          GET ADDR OF BUFFER IN ELEMENT 'MFD'     DG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          S,H2    *[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@          AXR$      .   @G@@@@DH
)@@G@@          CONFIG    .                 DEFINE CONFIGURATION PARAMTERES   DI
)@@G@@@F@@@@FLAP      EQU       0                 NONZERO TO TURN ON FLAP     DJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@PRT       FORM      12,6,18           FORMAT T1,S3,H2 @D@@@@POUT* DK
)@@G@@    PRT       1,22,LINOUT       PRINT PACKET    @D@@@@POUT2*    PRT     DL
)@@G@@  2,22,LINOUT       PRINT PACKET    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LINOUT*   RES     DM
)@@G@@  23                EDIT$ IMAGE BUFFER    @F@@@@PROJPK*   'DIAG$   '    DN
)@@G@@              FITEM$ PKT FOR REAL PROJ    @D@@@@PCT*      RES       21  DO
)@@G@@              PCT$ BUFFER     @E@@@@MFD$*     RES       14              DP
)@@G@@  ELT$ SPEC1 BUFFER     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. ITEMS BETWEEN RECSTART AND RDQ
)@@G@@ECLEN WILL BE SORTED    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@RECSTART* . @D@@@@LIBUF0*   REDR
)@@G@@S       28                LEAD ITEM BUFFER@F@@@@MIBUF0*   RES       28  DS
)@@G@@              BUFFER FOR M.I. SECTOR 0    @F@@@@.                       DT

)@@G@@        MI SEC 1 BUFFER @ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF  @E@@@@SNOITPDW
)@@G@@O*  RES       2                 REVERSE OPTIONS SPEC'D@ @@@@          OFDX
)@@G@@F       OLDSTUFF  @H@@@@OPTWRD*   RES       1                 INIT1-INITDY

)@@G@@  REST OF MI SEC 1 BUFFER     @E@@@@          RES       1               EA
)@@G@@  SAVEAREA - ALSO SORTED@E@@@@          +         0                 FLAGEB
)@@G@@S SORTED WITH FILE@F@@@@RECLEN*   EQU       $-RECSTART        SORT RECOREC
)@@G@@D LENGTH IN WORDS @D@@@@RECCHAR*  EQU       RECLEN*6            AND CHARED
)@@G@@ACTERS@ @@@@          ON        SNAPOK    @E@@@@LI1*      .             EE
)@@G@@              L.I. SEC 1 BUFFER     @ @@@@          OFF       SNAPOK    EF
)@@G@@@E@@@@MI2*      RES       28                M.I. SEC 2-N BUFFER   @^@@@@EG
)@@G@@          ON        NSSP@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. SUPER SPEC REMOTE TEST INSTREH
)@@G@@UCTION TABLE - CREATED BY INIT1, AND EXECUTED   @^@@@@. BY 'CHECK' ROUTIEI
)@@G@@NE.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     FOR SINGLE-WORD SPECS            FOR DOUBLEJ
)@@G@@E-WORD SPECS@E@@@@.     ---------------------            ---------------EK
)@@G@@------@D@@@@.     LA<,J>  A0,<N>,X8                DL    A0,<N>,X8@D@@@@EL
)@@G@@.     LSSL A0,<L> AND SSL A0,<R>       DTE   A0,SSPVAL@^@@@@.     AND   EM
)@@G@@  A0,SSMASK @^@@@@.     LA      A0,SSPVAL @^@@@@.     <TEST>  A0,A1     EN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@SSIZE*    EQU       6                 SPEC TEST ENTRY EO
)@@G@@LENGTH@E@@@@SSTAB*    RES       SSIZE*NSSP        RESERVE TABLE SPACE   EP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@SSLOAD*   EQU       SSTAB+0           'DL' OR 'LA' OF EQ
)@@G@@DIRECTORY INFO    @G@@@@SSHIFT*   EQU       SSTAB+1           SHIFT OR NER
)@@G@@OP (SKIPPED FOR 'DL')   @G@@@@SSTEST*   EQU       SSTAB+2           'TE'ES
)@@G@@ OR 'DTE' WITH SPEC VALUE     @H@@@@SSPVAL*   EQU       SSTAB+3         ET
)@@G@@  SPEC VALUE CONVERTED TO PROPER FORM     @G@@@@SSMASK*   EQU       SSTAEU
)@@G@@B+4           MASK, OR SECOND WORD OF SPEC VALUE@F@@@@SSLINK*   EQU     EV
)@@G@@  SSTAB+5           LINK TO POLISH TABLE ENTRY  @E@@@@.                 EW
)@@G@@                    (FOR RESULT OF TEST)  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. POLISH: POEX
)@@G@@LISH NOTATION TABLE.  INIT1 DECODES THE AND'S, OR'S, AND    @G@@@@.     EY
)@@G@@    XOR'S INTO NUMBERS, AND PLACES THESE NUMBERS IN THE POLISH    @G@@@@EZ
)@@G@@.         TABLE IN THE ORDER IN WHICH THEY ARE ENCOUNTERED.  A BLANK    FA
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         ENTRY IS LEFT FOR EACH ACTUAL TEST SPEC WHICH IS FOUND, FB
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         AND WHEN THE TEST IS PERFORMED, THE RESULT IS PLACED IN FC
)@@G@@THE   @C@@@@.         PROPER LOCATION IN THE POLISH TABLE.  @[@@@@.     FD
)@@G@@@E@@@@POLISH*   RES       NSSP              POLISH NOTATION TABLE @[@@@@FE
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. TRANS: THIS TABLE CONTAINS THE INTERMEDIATE RESULTS OBTAINFF
)@@G@@ED WHILE    @B@@@@.        EVALUATING THE POLISH EXPRESSION.@[@@@@.     FG
)@@G@@@E@@@@TRANS     RES       NSSP              TRANSLATION TABLE     @[@@@@FH

)@@G@@@^@@@@          OFF       NSSP@[@@@@.     @F@@@@USELUT*   +         0   FJ

)@@G@@FD    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. *** K L U D G E    F O L L O W S ***    @[@@@@GX
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@. WHEN THE SINGLE-FILE ROUTINE DOES AN ER FITEM$ FOR A TEMPOGY
)@@G@@RARY FILE, FITEM$ @G@@@@. RETURNS THE OLD EQUIPMENT CODE NUMBERS, WHICH GZ
)@@G@@WE PREFER NOT TO USE    @G@@@@. ANYMORE.  SINCE THE FILE IS ASSIGNED, WEHA
)@@G@@ CAN PICK UP THE EQUIPMENT    @F@@@@. INDEX FROM THE PCT ITEM, AND USE THB
)@@G@@HAT TO PICK UP THE SPECIFIC   @G@@@@. MNEMONIC FOR THE EQUIPMENT INDEX. HC
)@@G@@ THIS IS NOT QUITE WHAT WE WANT,    @F@@@@. SINCE FOR OTHER FILES WE PRIHD
)@@G@@NT THE ASSIGN MNEMONIC, BUT IT SEEMS@G@@@@. TO BE THE BEST WE CAN DO FORHE
)@@G@@ NOW.  ANYHOW, TO DO THIS, WE MUST GET    @F@@@@. THE SPECIFIC MNEMONIC HF
)@@G@@TABLE FROM THE MCT, OR USE THE 'FEQP$'    @ @@@@. SUBFUNCTION OF  ER INFHG
)@@G@@O$... @[@@@@.     @G@@@@MCTEQ*    +         0                 IF YOU HAVHH
)@@G@@E >40 DISTINCT EQUIPMENT@H@@@@          RES       39                TYPEHI
)@@G@@S, YOU'LL HAVE TO INCREASE THIS     @E@@@@.                             HJ
)@@G@@        (SEE ALSO INIT2).     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. *** K L U D G E    P RHK
)@@G@@ E C E D E S ***  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@EDPACK*   E$PKT     23,LHL
)@@G@@INOUT         EDIT$ PACKET    @ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF  @F@@@@HM
)@@G@@DATREF*   +         0                 YY,MM,DD DATE FROM D-OPTION @F@@@@HN

)@@G@@          +         'DIS',DISBTA      DISABLED IN ANY WAY   @E@@@@      HP

)@@G@@        SPEC2 HOLDER    @ @@@@          OFF       OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@.     HV

)@@G@@        0                 2ND LINE FLAGS  @C@@@@FLAG3*    +         0,0,HX

)@@G@@ FLAGS@C@@@@FLAG5*    +         0                 MORE FLAGS@[@@@@.     HZ
)@@G@@@#@@@@. OPTION TABLE    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ZERO ENTRY INDICATES UNDEFINIA
)@@G@@ED OPTION.  @D@@@@. OTHERWISE, H2 = PRIMARY ATTRIBUTE ROUTINE ADDRESS.  IB
)@@G@@@G@@@@. IF OPTION IS NOT A PRIMARY ATTRIBUTE OPTION, 'GOON' SHOULD BE USIC
)@@G@@ED.   @G@@@@. INIT1 WILL SET T1 OF THE ENTRY = 1 IF THE OPTION IS DEFINEID
)@@G@@D AND SET.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF 'OLDSTUFF' IS TURNED ON, S3 = 040 INDIE
)@@G@@ICATES THAT THE OPTION  @F@@@@. IS REVERSIBLE, AND T1 WILL BE SET TO -1 IF
)@@G@@IF THE USER HAS REVERSED@E@@@@. IT BY SPECIFYING THE OPTION IN THE SPEC2IG
)@@G@@ VERSION FIELD.   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF  @E@@@@IH
)@@G@@OLDOP     EQU       (040*/18)+GOON    REVERSIBLE OPTION     @ @@@@      II
)@@G@@    OFF       OLDSTUFF  @ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF=0@D@@@@OLDOP IJ
)@@G@@    EQU       0                 UNDEFINED OPTION@ @@@@          OFF     IK
)@@G@@  OLDSTUFF=0@[@@@@.     @B@@@@OPTIONS*  +         0,AOPT            A   IL
)@@G@@@B@@@@          DO        2 , + 0,GOON      B-C @B@@@@          +       IM
)@@G@@  OLDOP             D   @B@@@@          +         0,GOON            E   IN
)@@G@@@B@@@@          +         0,FOPT            F   @B@@@@          +       IO
)@@G@@  OLDOP             G   @B@@@@          +         0,GOON            H   IP
)@@G@@@B@@@@          +         0,FOPT            I   @B@@@@          +       IQ
)@@G@@  0,GOON            J   @B@@@@          +         0,KOPT            K   IR
)@@G@@@B@@@@          DO        3 , + 0,GOON      L-N @B@@@@          +       IS
)@@G@@  OLDOP             O   @B@@@@          +         0,POPT            P   IT
)@@G@@@B@@@@          +         0,QOPT            Q   @B@@@@          +       IU

)@@G@@  0,GOON            W   @B@@@@          +         0,XOPT            X   IX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          +         0,GOON            Y   @B@@@@          +       IY
)@@G@@  0,ZOPT            Z   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        SORTOK    IZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SORT PARAMETER TABLE, SORTBL, SHOULD CONTAIN EVERYTHJA
)@@G@@ING EXCEPT  @E@@@@. KEY PARAMETERS, WHICH ARE CREATED IN 'TABLE2' BY INIJB
)@@G@@T1.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SORTBL*   R$FILE    'COPY',TABLE2  'RSZW',RECLENJC
)@@G@@ 'FILES','XA','XB' ;    @D@@@@          'FPOC',MFD400 'LPOC',LPOC  'CHECJD
)@@G@@K','D','F'  @D@@@@TABLE2*   +         0,TABLE2          START OF TABLE  JE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          +         06300,0,0         DELETE CONSOLE MESSAGES     JF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SORT KEYS ARE INSERTED IN 'ADDKEYS' DYNAMICALLY BY IJG
)@@G@@NIT1, BASED ON    @G@@@@. SPECS.  IF 'B' OPTION IS USED, SORT KEYS FOR QJH
)@@G@@UALIFIER, FILENAME,     @F@@@@. AND FCYCLE ARE AUTOMATICALLY ADDED AT THJI
)@@G@@E END OF THE LIST.  THE @E@@@@. LIST IS TERMINATED BY AN END-OF-PARAMETEJJ
)@@G@@R-TABLE SENTINEL. @E@@@@. THEREFORE, A MINIMUM OF 7 WORDS IS NEEDED FOR JK
)@@G@@ADDKEYS.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@KEYL      EQU       7+(NSSP<6)*(2*NSSP)+(NJL
)@@G@@SSP>5)*(2*5)@^@@@@ADDKEYS*  RES       KEYL@ @@@@          ON        BRKOJM
)@@G@@K     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. BRKTBL WILL CONTAIN THE NECESSARY INSTRUCTIONSJN
)@@G@@ AND DATA TO PROVIDE THE@H@@@@. SUBTOTAL ('BREAK') FEATURE.  EACH ENTRY JO
)@@G@@IS BRKSIZ WORDS IN LENGTH, BUT THE  @F@@@@. CONTENTS VARY WITH THE SORT JP
)@@G@@KEY TYPE.  BRKTBL IS BUILT BY INIT1.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     SINGLE WORD JQ
)@@G@@             DOUBLE WORD              SINGLE BIT@F@@@@.     ----------- JR
)@@G@@             -----------              ----------@G@@@@.  0  LA<,J> A0,<DJS
)@@G@@>,X8         DL  A0,<D>,X8            LA,<J> A0,<D>,X8@H@@@@.  1  TE    JT
)@@G@@ A0,2,*X5          DTE A0,2,*X5             LMJ    X11,BRKBIT     @H@@@@JU
)@@G@@.  2  +      FORMER VALUE      +   FORMER VALUE         +      FORMER VAJV
)@@G@@LUE   @G@@@@.  3  <UNUSED>                 +   FORMER VALUE         +   JW
)@@G@@   BIT MASK @G@@@@.  4  +      0,<SPEC>          +   0,<SPEC>           JX
)@@G@@  +      0,<SPEC> @H@@@@.  5  SHIFT  LEFT,RIGHT        <UNUSED>         JY
)@@G@@        SHIFT  LEFT,RIGHT     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. WHERE <J> IS THE PARTIJZ
)@@G@@AL WORD DESIGNATOR, IF ANY, AND <D> IS THE OFFSET     @G@@@@. INTO THE SKA
)@@G@@ORT RECORD.  <SPEC> IS THE FIRST 3 CHARACTER OF THE SPEC.   @[@@@@.     KB
)@@G@@@E@@@@BRKSIZ    EQU       6                 SIZE OF BRKTBL ENTRY  @H@@@@KC
)@@G@@BRKPNT*   +         -BRKSIZ,BRKTBL+(BRKMAX*BRKSIZ)  INITIAL BRKTBL POINTKD
)@@G@@ER    @E@@@@BRKTBL*   RES       BRKMAX*BRKSIZ     BRKSIZ-WORD ENTRIES   KE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@BRKLOAD*  EQU       0                 LOAD OF DIRECTORKF
)@@G@@Y INFO@F@@@@BRKTEST*  EQU       1                 TEST VERSUS PREVIOUS VKG
)@@G@@ALUE  @D@@@@BRKVAL*   EQU       2                 PREVIOUS VALUE  @H@@@@KH
)@@G@@BRKMASK*  EQU       3                 MASK FOR SINGLE BIT, OR WORD 2 OF KI
)@@G@@VALUE @D@@@@BRKSPEC*  EQU       4                 BREAK SPEC FLAGS@F@@@@KJ
)@@G@@.                                     S2 = NEW-HEADING-WANTED FLAG@D@@@@KK
)@@G@@.                                     S3 = SPEC NUMBER@F@@@@.           KL
)@@G@@                          H2 = 1ST 3 CHARACTER OF SPEC@F@@@@BRKSHFT*  EQKM
)@@G@@U       5                 LEFT,RIGHT SHIFT COUNTS     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@KN
)@@G@@INVALU*   +         1,1               BREAK INITIAL VALUE FLAGS   @^@@@@KO
)@@G@@BRKCNT*   +         0   @G@@@@BRKSTOP*  +         0                 STARKP
)@@G@@TING BREAK INDEX FOR TOTALS   @ @@@@          OFF       BRKOK     @ @@@@KQ
)@@G@@          OFF       SORTOK    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         DEFINE EQUF TAKR
)@@G@@GS    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          EQUFS     .                 EQUF DEFINKS
)@@G@@ITIONS@ @@@@          ON        OLDSTUFF  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THESE INSTKT

)@@G@@NE, HAVE THEIR TESTS REVERSED BY INIT2    @E@@@@. IF THE CORRESPONDING OKV
)@@G@@PTION IS REVERSED ON THE CALL CARD. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@REVT*     J       KW
)@@G@@  GALI              SELECT (SKIP) TAPE FILES    @G@@@@REVO*     JZ      KX

)@@G@@@H@@@@SZBAK*    TLE       FILESIZE,SZOPT+1  SELECT (SKIP) USING BACKUP BLF
)@@G@@LOCK COUNT  @ @@@@          OFF       OLDSTUFF  @#@@@@/$(1).  BEGIN     LG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LOAD INITIALIZATION SEGMENT (INSEG), WHICH IS COMPOSLH
)@@G@@ED OF INIT1 @G@@@@. AND INIT2 ROUTINES.  INIT1 VALIDATES THE SPEC FIELDSLI
)@@G@@ AND DOES MUCH    @F@@@@. OF THE OPTION CHECKING.  WHEN DONE, INIT1 JUMPLJ
)@@G@@S TO INIT2 TO SET @F@@@@. ROUTINE ADDRESSES, INITIALIZE DIREC$ IF NEEDEDLK
)@@G@@, AND PRINT THE   @D@@@@. HEADING (VIA OVERLAY SEGMENT HDGSEG) IF DESIRELL
)@@G@@D.    @F@@@@. IF SINGLE-FILE MODE WAS NOT SPECIFIED, INIT2 WILL THEN NORLM
)@@G@@MALLY @F@@@@. OVERLAY ITSELF WITH THE CHECK/PRINT SEGMENT (CHEKPRTSG) ANLN
)@@G@@D     @^@@@@. RETURN TO MFD100.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. IF SINGLE-FILE MLO
)@@G@@ODE IS SPECIFIED, INIT2 LOADS AND JUMPS TO QFSEG,     @G@@@@. WHICH LOADLP
)@@G@@S CHEKPRTSG AND RETURNS TO 'MFD100' IF THE DREAD$ GOES OK.  @G@@@@. IF NLQ
)@@G@@OT, IT WILL PRINT AN ERROR MESSAGE, ISSUE A READ$ FOR ANOTHER     @H@@@@LR
)@@G@@. FILE, AND TRY AGAIN.  IF AN @EOF IS ENCOUNTERED, IT WILL RETURN TO 'MFLS
)@@G@@D700'.@F@@@@. IN SINGLE-FILE MODE, THE DIREC$ SEGMENT IS NOT NEEDED, SO LT
)@@G@@QFSEG @B@@@@. AND DIRSEG OCCUPY THE SAME PROGRAM AREA.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@LU
)@@G@@MFD       . @^@@@@          ON        FLAP@^@@@@FSKIP$*   EQU       1   LV
)@@G@@@^@@@@FJUMP$*   EQU       2   @^@@@@FJUMPS$*  EQU       1   @^@@@@U1110TLW

)@@G@@  1   @G@@@@          TEP       A5,(1*/('Z'-'E')) E-OPTION TO TURN ON FLLY
)@@G@@AP OUTPUT   @E@@@@          SLJ       FLOP$             START FLAP OUTPULZ
)@@G@@T     @^@@@@          OFF       FLAP@E@@@@          L$OAD     INSEG,IN10MA
)@@G@@00,1    PERFORM INITIALIZATION@B@@@@. QFSEG RETURNS HERE IF DREAD$ GOES MB
)@@G@@OK.   @C@@@@. INSEG RETURNS HERE AFTER INITIALIZING DIREC$. @[@@@@.     MC
)@@G@@@B@@@@. LOAD SDFO SEGMENT IF W-OPTION IS SET    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@MFD100MD

)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       SORTOK    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. FIND NEXT FILE TMW
)@@G@@O BE LISTED @H@@@@. IF SORT NOT BEING DONE, J MFD400...OTHERWISE, GET NEMX

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. POLISH EXPRESSION EVALUATION ROUTINE    @[@@@@.     OW
)@@G@@@H@@@@. DECODE THE 'POLISH' TABLE, AND RETURN WITH A0 INDICATING WHETHEROX
)@@G@@ OR NOT     @G@@@@. THE EXPRESSION IS TRUE.  INTERMEDIATE RESULTS GO IN OY
)@@G@@'TRANS' TABLE.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@POLTRAN*  TZ        POLNTH          OZ
)@@G@@  IS LENGTH OF POLISH TABLE ZERO?   @G@@@@          TNZ       TESTS     PA
)@@G@@        OR HAVE NO TESTS BEEN SPECIFIED?  @C@@@@          J         POL4PB
)@@G@@00            YES, ERROR@F@@@@          LR        R1,POLNTH         GET PC
)@@G@@LENGTH OF POLISH TABLE  @D@@@@          JGD       R1,$+1            ADJUPD
)@@G@@ST FOR JGD  @G@@@@          LX        X1,(1,0)          INITIALIZE POLISPE
)@@G@@H TABLE INDEX     @F@@@@          LX        X2,(1,0)          INITIALIZEPF
)@@G@@ TRANS TABLE INDEX@G@@@@POL100    LA        A0,POLISH,*X1     PICK UP ITPG
)@@G@@EM FROM POLISH TABLE    @E@@@@          TG,U      A0,TRUE+1         IS IPH
)@@G@@T AN OPERATION?   @F@@@@          J         POL300            YES, STOREPI
)@@G@@ IT IN TRANS TABLE@E@@@@          TNZ,U     0,X2              IS FIRST SPJ
)@@G@@PEC OPERAND?@F@@@@          J         POL400            YES, OPERATION MPK
)@@G@@UST BE FIRST@H@@@@POL200    LA        A1,TRANS-1,X2     OPERAND - GET LAPL
)@@G@@ST ITEM PUT IN TRANS    @F@@@@          SA        A1,A2             SAVEPM
)@@G@@ IN A2 IN CASE OF 'NOT' @F@@@@          TNE,U     A1,NOT            WAS PN
)@@G@@IT A 'NOT' OPERATION?   @E@@@@          J         POL240            YES,PO
)@@G@@ HANDLE IT NOW    @G@@@@          TG,U      A1,TRUE+1         NO, WAS ITPP
)@@G@@ ANOTHER OPERATION?     @H@@@@          J         POL300            YES,PQ
)@@G@@ MUST STORE THIS OPERAND IN TRANS   @F@@@@          LA        A2,TRANS-2PR
)@@G@@,X2     GET LAST OPERATION IN TRANS @E@@@@POL240    ANA,U     A2,TRUE+1 PS
)@@G@@        CONVERT INTO OP INDEX @E@@@@          EX        OP,A2           PT
)@@G@@  DO AND/OR/XOR  A0,A1  @E@@@@          LA        A0,A1             RESUPU
)@@G@@LT IN A0 AGAIN    @E@@@@          ANX,U     X2,1              BACK UP TRPV
)@@G@@ANS INDEX   @F@@@@          TE,U      A2,NOT-(TRUE+1)   WAS THIS A 'NOT'PW
)@@G@@ OPERATION? @F@@@@          ANX,U     X2,1              NO, BACK UP A LIPX
)@@G@@TTLE MORE   @F@@@@          TNZ,U     0,X2              NO OPERATIONS LEPY
)@@G@@FT IN TRANS?@F@@@@          J         POL500            GOOD, SHOULD BE PZ
)@@G@@ALL DONE    @E@@@@          J         POL200            TRY COMBINING AGQA
)@@G@@AIN   @H@@@@POL300    SA        A0,TRANS,*X2      STORE OPERAND OR OPERAQB
)@@G@@TION IN TRANS     @F@@@@          JGD       R1,POL100         CONTINUE UQC
)@@G@@NTIL ALL DONE     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ERROR IN POLISH EXPRESSION  @[@@@@QD
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@POL400    LA        A0,(PRT 1,4,POLERM) . GET 'POLISH NOTATIQE
)@@G@@ON ERROR' MSG     @E@@@@          J         MFD900            PRINT IT, QF
)@@G@@AND EXIT    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. TABLE OF LOGICAL INSTRUCTIONS     @[@@@@QG
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@OP        AND       A0,A1     @ @@@@          OR        A0,AQH
)@@G@@1     @ @@@@          XOR       A0,A1     @G@@@@          XOR,U     A0,TQI
)@@G@@RUE           'NOT' - COMPLEMENT THE OPERAND    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@POL500QJ
)@@G@@    TZ        R1                R1 SHOULD BE ZERO     @F@@@@          J QK
)@@G@@        POL400            IF NOT, SOMETHING'S WRONG   @G@@@@          J QL
)@@G@@        0,X11             RETURN WITH A0 = 0 OR 1 (F OR T)  @^@@@@      QM

)@@G@@T ROUTINE   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. BETTER CONVERT THE CAT AND REF DATES BACSF
)@@G@@K TO TDATE$ FORMAT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          LA,H1     A0,DATLSTASG    SG

)@@G@@ AND BREAK CHECKS @ @@@@          ON        BRKOK=0   @G@@@@          LXSQ
)@@G@@,U      X4,0              NO, ASSUME GRAND TOTALS INDEX     @ @@@@      SR
)@@G@@    OFF       BRKOK=0   @ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @G@@@@      SS

)@@G@@          TZ        BRKCNT            WERE NO BREAKS SPECIFIED, OR@I@@@@SU

)@@G@@E FILE?     @I@@@@          J         COUNT             YES, JUST INCREMSW

)@@G@@  YES, GET BREAK TABLE POINTER AND INDEX  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. PERFORM THSY
)@@G@@E TESTS INDICATED BY EACH 'BREAK' SPECIFICATION TO DETERMINE@H@@@@. WHETSZ
)@@G@@HER THE PARTICULAR SORT KEY FIELDS FOR THIS FILE ARE DIFFERENT FROM     TA
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THOSE OF THE PREVIOUS FILE.  IF THEY'RE ALL THE SAME, COUNT THISTB
)@@G@@ FILE,@H@@@@. AND PRINT THE NORMAL INFORMATION ABOUT IT.  IF DIFFERENT, TC
)@@G@@CHARGE OFF INTO   @H@@@@. THE TOTALS ROUTINE TO PRINT SUBTOTALS.  THEN CTD
)@@G@@OUNT THE FILE AND PRINT IT.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BRKCHK    TNZ       X4  TE
)@@G@@              ARE WE AT THE GRAND TOTALS INDEX? @D@@@@          J       TF
)@@G@@  BRKCHK3           YES, SKIP IT    @F@@@@          EX        BRKLOAD,X5TG
)@@G@@        EXECUTE LOAD INSTRUCTION    @F@@@@          TNZ       BRKSHFT,X5TH
)@@G@@        ANY SHIFTING TO BE DONE?    @B@@@@          J         BRKCHK0   TI
)@@G@@        NO  @E@@@@          LA,H1     A1,BRKSHFT,X5     GET LEFT SHIFT CTJ
)@@G@@OUNT  @C@@@@          LSSL      A0,0,A1           SHIFT LEFT@E@@@@      TK
)@@G@@    LA,H2     A1,BRKSHFT,X5     GET RIGHT SHIFT COUNT @D@@@@          SSTL
)@@G@@L       A0,0,A1           SHIFT RIGHT     @F@@@@BRKCHK0   EX        BRKTTM
)@@G@@EST,X5        EXECUTE TEST INSTRUCTION    @D@@@@          J         DOBRTN
)@@G@@EAK           TEST FAILED     @D@@@@          J         BRKCHK2         TO
)@@G@@  TEST PASSED     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THIS SUBROUTINE IS USED ONLY FOR 'TP
)@@G@@BREAK' SPECS WHERE THE KEY FIELD    @F@@@@. IS A SINGLE-BIT VALUE, AS INTQ
)@@G@@ THE SPECS WITH ASSUMED VALUES.     @F@@@@. THE ABOVE CODE REMOTELY EXECTR
)@@G@@UTES AN 'LMJ X11,BRKBIT' FOR SUCH   @E@@@@. A KEY FIELD, WITH THE VALUE TS
)@@G@@FOR THE CURRENT FILE IN A0.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BRKBIT*   LA        A1,BTT
)@@G@@RKVAL,X5      GET PREVIOUS VALUE    @F@@@@          AND       A1,BRKMASKTU
)@@G@@,X5     MASK OFF ASSUMED VALUE BIT  @G@@@@          AND       A0,BRKMASKTV
)@@G@@,*X5    DO THE SAME WITH CURRENT VALUE    @C@@@@          TE        A1,ATW
)@@G@@2             EQUAL?    @B@@@@          J         0,X11             NO  TX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         1,X11             YES @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. A KETY
)@@G@@Y FIELD FOR THIS FILE IS DIFFERENT FROM THAT OF THE PREVIOUS FILE.@D@@@@TZ
)@@G@@. SET A FLAG, AND SAVE THE BREAK LEVEL FOR LATER USE. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@UA
)@@G@@DOBREAK   SR,H2     R15,INVALU        SET INITIAL VALUE FLAG@G@@@@      UB
)@@G@@    SX        X4,BRKSTOP        SET HIGHEST-LEVEL-BREAK INDICATOR @E@@@@UC
)@@G@@BRKCHK2   JGD       X4,BRKCHK         CHECK ALL BREAK LEVELS@[@@@@.     UD
)@@G@@@G@@@@. IF ANY BREAK LEVEL HAS TRIGGERED A BREAK, PRINT THE SUBTOTALS UPUE
)@@G@@ TO   @B@@@@. THE HIGHEST BREAK LEVEL WHICH DID SO.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@UF

)@@G@@        ARBITRARY DEVICE FILE, OR   @D@@@@          TZ        TAP       XP
)@@G@@        CAT'D TAPE FILE?@F@@@@          J         PR040             YES,XQ
)@@G@@ SKIP MAX GRAN STUFF    @C@@@@          E$DECF    4,MAXGRAN         MAX XR
)@@G@@GRAN  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,'T'            ASSUME TRACK GRANULARIXS
)@@G@@TY    @D@@@@          TP        PCHAR             POSITION GRAN?  @D@@@@XT
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,'P'            YES, SAY SO     @^@@@@          E$XU
)@@G@@CHAR    .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. EDIT CATALOGUE OPTION LETTERS     @[@@@@XV
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@PR040     LA        A1,INHIBITS       GET OPTION BITS @G@@@@XW
)@@G@@          LA        A2,(1,0)          SET TO STORE OPTIONS IN PRINT LINEXX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CHOCK     'P',PBIT          CHECK FOR PUBLIC FILE @C@@@@XY
)@@G@@          CHECK     'R',RONLY         READ-ONLY?@ @@@@          ON      XZ
)@@G@@  GVHUSH>1  @E@@@@          TNZ       PRIVLGD           IS USER PRIVILEGYA
)@@G@@ED?   @G@@@@          J         PR050             NO, SKIP PRINT OF G/V YB
)@@G@@OPTIONS     @ @@@@          OFF       GVHUSH>1  @C@@@@          CHECK   YC
)@@G@@  'V',VBIT          V-OPTION? @C@@@@          CHECK     'G',MI0GBIT     YD
)@@G@@  G-OPTION? @D@@@@PR050     CHECK     'W',WONLY         WRITE-ONLY?     YE
)@@G@@@C@@@@. EDIT A LETTER INDICATING FILE @ASG STATE:     @C@@@@. BLANK - FIYF
)@@G@@LE NOT CURRENTLY ASSIGNED TO ANYONE @C@@@@.     A - FILE ASSIGNED TO AT YG
)@@G@@LEAST ONE RUN     @C@@@@.     X - FILE EXCLUSIVELY ASSIGNED TO SOME RUN YH
)@@G@@@E@@@@.     C - (SINGLE-FILE MODE ONLY) FILE @ASG,C BY THIS RUN   @E@@@@YI
)@@G@@.     U - (SINGLE-FILE MODE ONLY) FILE @ASG,U BY THIS RUN   @G@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@T - (SINGLE-FILE MODE ONLY) TEMPORARY FILE ASSIGNED TO THIS RUN   @[@@@@YK
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          LA        A0,CURASGCNT      GET ASG COUNT   @G@@@@YL
)@@G@@          TZ        SFASG             ASSIGNED FOR SINGLE-FILE DREAD$ ? YM
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AN,U      A0,1              YES, DON'T COUNT IT   @E@@@@YN
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,PR060          ASSIGNED TO ANYONE?   @E@@@@      YO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,'A'            YES, GET SET FOR 'A'  @F@@@@          TEYP
)@@G@@P,U     A1,XUSE           IS IT EXCLUSIVELY ASG'D?    @E@@@@          LAYQ
)@@G@@,U      A0,'X'            YES, CHANGE TO 'X'    @E@@@@          TZ      YR
)@@G@@  UCOPT             @ASG,U OR @ASG,C?     @D@@@@          LA        A0,UYS
)@@G@@COPT          YES, GET LETTER @D@@@@          TZ        TEMP            YT
)@@G@@  TEMPORARY FILE? @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,'T'            YES, GET AYU
)@@G@@ 'T'  @E@@@@          EX        ST,*A2            STORE PROPER CHAR     YV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IF TAPE FILE, EDIT MODE BITS AND EQUIPMENT TYPE     YW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@PR060     TNZ       TAP               CAT'D TAPE FILE?YX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         PR110             NO, GET F-EQUIP TYPE  @D@@@@YY
)@@G@@          LA        A1,TAPEMODES      GET TAPE MODES  @E@@@@          LAYZ
)@@G@@,U      A0,'H'            ASSUME HIGH DENSITY   @D@@@@          TOP,U   ZA
)@@G@@  A1,020            LOW DENSITY?    @ @@@@          TOP,U     A1,010    ZB
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         PR061             NO - JUMP @D@@@@          LAZC
)@@G@@,U      A0,'L'            YES, SET FOR 'L'@C@@@@          J         PR06ZD
)@@G@@3             GO ON     @D@@@@PR061     TEP,U     A1,010            MEDIZE
)@@G@@UM DENSITY? @C@@@@          J         PR062             NO - JUMP @D@@@@ZF
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,'M'            YES, SET FOR 'M'@C@@@@          J ZG
)@@G@@        PR063             GO ON     @E@@@@PR062     TZ        TMSAMODES ZH
)@@G@@        MSA TAPE EQUIPMENT?   @E@@@@          TP        TMSAMODES       ZI
)@@G@@  YES - 1600 DENSITY?   @C@@@@          J         PR063             NO -ZJ
)@@G@@ SKIP @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. BIT 2**35 OF MI0+21 IS USED TO INDICATE 800-FPZK
)@@G@@I MODE FOR DUAL-  @E@@@@. DENSITY 9-TRACK MSA TAPE DRIVES.  IT IS SET FOZL
)@@G@@R 800, CLEAR@E@@@@. FOR 1600.  THIS IS THE ONLY WAY TO CHECK FOR 'V' OPTZM
)@@G@@ION.  @E@@@@. HOWEVER, THIS BIT IS CLEAR FOR 7-TRACK MSA DRIVES, SO WE  ZN
)@@G@@@F@@@@. MUST CHECK FOR 9-TRACK BEFORE ADDING THE 'V'.  I DON'T LIKE     ZO
)@@G@@@D@@@@. THIS, SINCE IT RELIES ON THE 'OLD EQUIPMENT CODE'.  @[@@@@.     ZP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A3,MI0OLDEQP      GET OLD EQUIPMENT CODE@E@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@          TG,U      A3,013            9-TRACK MSA TAPE?     @ @@@@      ZR
)@@G@@    TG,U      A3,016    @D@@@@          J         PR063             NO, ZS
)@@G@@KEEP THE 'H'@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,'V'            SET FOR 'V'     ZT
)@@G@@@E@@@@PR063     EX        ST,*A2            STORE DENSITY LETTER  @E@@@@ZU
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,'O'            ASSUME ODD PARITY     @D@@@@      ZV
)@@G@@    TEP,U     A1,040            EVEN PARITY?    @B@@@@          LA,U    ZW
)@@G@@  A0,'E'            YES @E@@@@          EX        ST,*A2            STORZX
)@@G@@E CORRECT LETTER  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,'I'            SET FOR SOZY
)@@G@@FTWARE TRANSLATE  @F@@@@          TEP,U     A1,04             SOFTWARE TZZ
)@@G@@RANSLATE SET?     @E@@@@          EX        ST,*A2            YES, STOREAA
)@@G@@ I-OPTION   @E@@@@          TNZ       TMSAMODES         MSA TAPE EQUIPMEAB
)@@G@@NT?   @D@@@@          J         PR100             NO, CONTINUE    @D@@@@AC
)@@G@@          LA        A1,TMSAMODES      GET MODE BITS   @D@@@@          CHAD
)@@G@@ECK     'D',0200          DUAL DENSITY?   @D@@@@PR100     LA        A1,TAE
)@@G@@APEJOPT       GET OTHER BITS  @C@@@@          CHECK     'J',040         AF
)@@G@@  J-OPTION? @ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @E@@@@          TZ      AG
)@@G@@  MFD$F             NEW FORMAT MFD FILE?  @E@@@@          J         PR15AH
)@@G@@0             YES, USE ASG MNEMONIC @E@@@@          LA        A0,MI0OLDEAI
)@@G@@QP      GET EQUIPMENT CODE    @E@@@@          LA        A1,TAPEQP-1,A0  AJ
)@@G@@  GET TAPE EQUIP TYPE   @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMFD    @G@@@@      AK
)@@G@@    J         PR150             STORE EQUIP TYPE IN PRINT IMAGE   @[@@@@AL
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. NOT A TAPE FILE - EDIT EQUIPMENT TYPE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@AM
)@@G@@PR110     . @ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @E@@@@          TZ      AN
)@@G@@  MFD$F             NEW FORMAT MFD FILE?  @G@@@@          J         PR14AO
)@@G@@5             YES, USE ASG MNEMONIC OR PACKID   @E@@@@          LA      AP
)@@G@@  A0,MI0OLDEQP      GET EQUIPMENT CODE    @D@@@@          TLE,U     A0,0AQ
)@@G@@40            MASS STORAGE?   @D@@@@          J         PR120           AR
)@@G@@  YES, HANDLE IT  @F@@@@          LA        A1,OTHEQP-040,A0  NO, SOME OAS
)@@G@@THER DEVICE TYPE  @C@@@@          J         PR150             EDIT IT   AT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. MASS STORAGE FILE - TAKE SUBCODE INTO ACCOUNT.  IF RAU
)@@G@@EMOVABLE DISC,    @ @@@@. EDIT THE PACKID INSTEAD.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@AV
)@@G@@PR120     LA        A1,EQUCD-030,A0   GET NORMAL MASS STORAGE EQUIP TYPEAW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TE,U      A0,030            F2/3/60  OR  F14/24 ? @ @@@@AX
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,035    @E@@@@          J         $+2             AY
)@@G@@  YES, CHECK FOR SUBCODE@E@@@@          J         PR140             NO, AZ
)@@G@@NORMAL EQUIP TYPE @D@@@@PR130     TNZ       OLDSUBCOD         SUBCODE PRBA
)@@G@@ESENT?@B@@@@          J         PR140             NO  @D@@@@          L,BB
)@@G@@U       A2,SUB35-1        ASSUME F14/24   @D@@@@          TNE,U     A0,0BC
)@@G@@30            REALLY F2/3/60? @B@@@@          L,U       A2,SUB30-1      BD
)@@G@@  YES @F@@@@          A         A2,OLDSUBCOD      ADD SUBCODE TO GET INDBE
)@@G@@EX    @D@@@@          L         A1,0,A2           LOAD SUBTYPE    @E@@@@BF
)@@G@@PR140     AND       A1,(0757777777777)  CHANGE 'F' TO 'D'   @D@@@@      BG
)@@G@@    L,S1      A0,PCHAR          GET PCHAR FLAGS @G@@@@          TEP,U   BH
)@@G@@  A0,010            BIT 33 SET (WORD ADDRESSABLE)?    @D@@@@          L BI
)@@G@@        A1,A2             GET 'D' VERSION @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMBJ
)@@G@@FD    @E@@@@PR145     JZ        RDISC,PR150       IF FIXED, SKIP PACKID BK
)@@G@@@G@@@@          TNZ       NBRPACKS          SHOULD HAVE A NONZERO PACK CBL
)@@G@@OUNT  @G@@@@          J         PR150             BUT IF IT DOESN'T, SKIBM
)@@G@@P PACKID    @E@@@@          LA        A1,PACKENTRY      PICK UP FIRST PABN
)@@G@@CK ID @D@@@@          J         PR151             EDIT PACKID     @[@@@@BO
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. STORE EQUIPMENT TYPE IN PRINT IMAGE     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@BP
)@@G@@PR150     . @ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @E@@@@          TZ      BQ
)@@G@@  MFD$F             NEW FORMAT MFD FILE?  @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMBR
)@@G@@FD    @G@@@@          LA        A1,MNEMONIC       YES, GRAB THE ASSIGN MBS
)@@G@@NEMONIC     @F@@@@.                                     NO, USE EQUIP COBT
)@@G@@DE IN A1    @A@@@@PR151     LA        A2,('      ')   @ @@@@          DSBU
)@@G@@C       A1,30     @D@@@@          SA,S6     A1,LINOUT+1       STORE EQUIBV
)@@G@@P TYPE@A@@@@          SA        A2,LINOUT+2     @E@@@@          E$COL   BW
)@@G@@  17                LEAVE ROOM FOR PACKID @D@@@@. EDIT TOTAL ASSIGN COUNBX
)@@G@@T AND DATE LAST REFERENCED    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          E$DECF    4,TOBY
)@@G@@TASGCNT       ASG COUNT @^@@@@          E$COL     22  @D@@@@          E$BZ
)@@G@@DAY1    DATLSTASG         DATE LAST REF'D @D@@@@          TZ        TAP CA
)@@G@@              CAT'D TAPE FILE?@F@@@@          J         PR170           CB
)@@G@@  YES, PICK UP REEL NUMBER    @E@@@@          TZ        ARB             CC
)@@G@@  ARBITRARY DEVICE?     @F@@@@          J         PR180             YES,CD
)@@G@@ GO ON TO QUALIFIER     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. EDIT HIGHEST/TOTAL TRACKS (*CE
)@@G@@UNL* IF UNLOADED) @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          E$COL     36  @E@@@@      CF
)@@G@@    TN        DESCFLAGS         IS FILE UNLOADED?     @B@@@@          J CG
)@@G@@        PR160             NO  @ @@@@          ON        DSGUNL    @D@@@@CH
)@@G@@          TZ        PRIVLGD           PRIVILEGED?     @C@@@@          J CI
)@@G@@        PR155             YES, JUMP @E@@@@          E$DECF    4,BKUPTEXTCJ
)@@G@@        SECURE BACKUP BLOCKS  @D@@@@          E$COL     31              CK
)@@G@@  BACK UP A BIT   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,0              ZERO HIGH CL
)@@G@@REFERENCE   @D@@@@          E$DECF    4                 PUT IT IN IMAGE CM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         PR180             SKIP NEXT PART  @]@@@@PR155 CN
)@@G@@    . @ @@@@          OFF       DSGUNL    @D@@@@          E$FD1     ('*UCO
)@@G@@NL* ')        YES, PRINT *UNL*@D@@@@          J         PR180           CP
)@@G@@  GO GET QUALIFIER@E@@@@PR160     E$DECF    4,SAVESIZE        TOTAL LOADCQ
)@@G@@ED TRACKS   @F@@@@          E$COL     31                BACK UP FOR HIGHCR
)@@G@@EST TRACK   @F@@@@          E$DECF    4,HITRACK         HIGHEST TRACK RECS
)@@G@@FERENCED    @F@@@@          J         PR180             GET QUALIFIER, FCT
)@@G@@ILENAME, ETC@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. EDIT REEL NUMBEER FOR CATALOGUED TAPE FICU
)@@G@@LE    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@PR170     TNZ       NBRREELS          ANY REELS?CV
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         PR180             NO, SKIP IT     @D@@@@      CW
)@@G@@    E$COL     31                YES, MOVE OVER  @E@@@@          E$COPY  CX
)@@G@@  6,TAPEREEL1       INSERT REEL NUMBER    @E@@@@. EDIT Q*F(C) PRECEDED BCY
)@@G@@Y A CHAR DENOTING DISABLED STATUS   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@PR180     E$COL   CZ
)@@G@@  42  @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,' '            ASSUME NOT DISABLED   DA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TN        DISABLES          IS FILE DISABLED IN ANY WAY?DB
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         PR190             NO, EDIT A SPACE HERE @E@@@@DC
)@@G@@          LA,S1     A1,DISABLES       YES, GET DISABLE-BITS @F@@@@      DD
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,WRNCHR         ASSUME WARNING-ONLY DISABLED@D@@@@      DE
)@@G@@    TEP,U     A1,DISBTB         BAD BACKUP TAPE?@E@@@@          LA,U    DF
)@@G@@  A0,BBTCHR         YES, GET BAD-TAPE CHAR@F@@@@          TZ        BMI1DG
)@@G@@              BAD MAIN ITEM SECTOR 1?     @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,BDH
)@@G@@MICHR         YES, GET BAD-MI1 CHAR @E@@@@          TEP,U     A1,DISBTH DI
)@@G@@        HARDWARE-DISABLED?    @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,HDWCHR       DJ
)@@G@@  YES, GET CHAR   @E@@@@PR190     E$CHAR    .                 STORE DISADK
)@@G@@BLE-CHAR    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. EXEC FILENAMES MAY HAVE @ SIGNS AND SPACDL
)@@G@@ES IMBEDDED WITHIN@G@@@@. THE QUALIFIER AND FILENAME.  MUST COUNT CHARACDM
)@@G@@TERS, AND USE ECOPY$.   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          DL        A2,QUAL   DN
)@@G@@        GET QUAL  @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,TRAIL         COUNT CHARDO
)@@G@@S - TRAILING BLANKS     @ @@@@          LA,U      A0,QUAL   @F@@@@      DP
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,ECOPY$        EDIT CORRECT NUMBER OF CHAR @C@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    E$CHAR    '*'               ASTERISK  @D@@@@          DL        A2,FDR
)@@G@@ILE           GET FILENAME    @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,TRAIL       DS
)@@G@@  COUNT CHARS - TRALING BLANKS@ @@@@          LA,U      A0,FILE   @F@@@@DT
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,ECOPY$        EDIT CORRECT NUMBER OF CHARS@C@@@@DU
)@@G@@          E$CHAR    '('               OPEN PAREN@C@@@@          E$DECV  DV
)@@G@@  FCYCLE            F-CYCLE   @D@@@@          E$CHAR    ')'             DW
)@@G@@  CLOSE PAREN     @H@@@@          ON        WOPTOK            **********DX
)@@G@@****************************  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. CHECK FOR W-OPTION:  IDY
)@@G@@F SET, WRITE Q*F(C) TO SDF FILE     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TZ      DZ
)@@G@@  WPT               W-OPTION SET?   @G@@@@          J         SDF100    EA
)@@G@@        YES, JUMP TO SDF OUTPUT ROUTINE   @]@@@@PR300*    . @H@@@@      EB
)@@G@@    OFF       WOPTOK            **************************************  EC
)@@G@@@H@@@@          JZ        LONGLIST,PR460    IF SHORT LIST, SKIP ACCT, PRED
)@@G@@OJ, ETC.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LONG LISTING - CONTINUE EDITING: ADD ACCEE
)@@G@@OUNT, PROJ, DATE CAT'D  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          E$COL     72        EF
)@@G@@        SET FOR ACCOUNT @E@@@@          E$COPY    12,ACCOUNT        EDITEG
)@@G@@ ACCOUNT NUMBER   @^@@@@          E$COL     85  @C@@@@          E$COPY  EH
)@@G@@  12,PROJ           PROJECT-ID@^@@@@          E$COL     98  @D@@@@      EI
)@@G@@    TZ        TEMP              TEMPORARY FILE? @D@@@@          J       EJ
)@@G@@  PR310             YES, NO CAT DATE@F@@@@          E$DAY1    DATCATLGD EK
)@@G@@        NO, EDIT CATALOGUE DATE     @C@@@@          J         PR320     EL
)@@G@@        CONTINUE  @E@@@@PR310     E$COPY    6,('<TEMP>')      SAY IT'S TEM
)@@G@@EMPORARY    @]@@@@PR320     . @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. EDIT SECURE BACKUP INFEN
)@@G@@ORMATION    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          JNZ       BACKEDUP,PR430    IF TEO
)@@G@@HERE'S A BACKUP, GO GET IT    @F@@@@          TNZ       BMI1            EP
)@@G@@  BAD MAIN ITEM SECTOR 1?     @D@@@@          J         PR420           EQ
)@@G@@  NO, CONTINUE    @D@@@@          DL        A0,('***BAD MI SE') . GET MSER
)@@G@@G     @E@@@@          DS        A0,LINOUT+18      STORE IN PRINT LINE   ES
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA        A0,('C 1***')     GET END OF MSG  @E@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    SA        A0,LINOUT+20      STORE IN PRINT LINE   @F@@@@          J EU
)@@G@@        PR480             CHECK FOR LAPSES AND PRINT  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EV
)@@G@@. NO BACKUP @[@@@@.     @C@@@@PR420     LA        A0,('*NONE*')     NO BEW
)@@G@@ACKUP @A@@@@          LA        A1,('      ')   @ @@@@          DSC     EX
)@@G@@  A0,30     @A@@@@          SA,S6     A0,LINOUT+17    @D@@@@          SAEY
)@@G@@        A1,LINOUT+18      STORE IN IMAGE  @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,NEZ
)@@G@@OBCHR         GET NO-BACKUP CHAR    @E@@@@          SA,S6     A0,LINOUT+FA
)@@G@@6       STORE IN PRINT LINE   @F@@@@          J         PR480           FB
)@@G@@  CHECK FOR LAPSES AND PRINT  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. MAKE SURE BACKUP EXISTFC
)@@G@@S BEFORE TRYING TO EDIT IT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@PR430     TNZ       BKUPFD
)@@G@@REEL1         IS THERE REALLY A BACKUP?   @B@@@@          J         PR42FE
)@@G@@0             NO  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. EDIT BACKUP REEL NUMBER, FILE POSIFF
)@@G@@TION, BLOCK COUNT, AND CREATION TIME/DATE @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          E$FG
)@@G@@SKIP    1   @ @@@@          ON        PRVSEC    @D@@@@          TNZ     FH
)@@G@@  PRIVLGD           PRIVILEGED?     @B@@@@          J         PR440     FI
)@@G@@        NOPE@ @@@@          OFF       PRVSEC    @D@@@@          E$COPY  FJ
)@@G@@  6,BKUPREEL1       BACKUP REEL     @ @@@@          ON        PRVSEC    FK
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         PR450             SKIP THE SLASHES@F@@@@PR440 FL
)@@G@@    E$COPY    6,('//////')        SLASH OUT REEL NUMBER     @]@@@@PR450 FM
)@@G@@    . @ @@@@          OFF       PRVSEC    @^@@@@          E$COL     114 FN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$DECF    3,BKUPFILE        BACKUP POSITION @^@@@@      FO
)@@G@@    E$COL     117 @C@@@@          E$DECF    4,BKUPTEXT        SEC TRACKSFP
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ON        DCFZ@^@@@@          E$SKIP    1   @C@@@@      FQ
)@@G@@    E$DCFZ    2,BKUPTIME,,S1    EDIT MONTH@D@@@@          E$DCFZ    2,BKFR
)@@G@@UPTIME,,S2    EDIT BACKUP DATE@^@@@@          OFF       DCFZ@ @@@@      FS
)@@G@@    ON        DCFZ<1    @^@@@@          LA,U      A0,0@F@@@@          LAFT
)@@G@@,S1     A1,BKUPTIME       MONTH TAPE WRITTEN (TDATE$) @E@@@@          DIFU
)@@G@@,U      A0,10             GET FD DECIMAL NUMBER @ @@@@          AA,U    FV
)@@G@@  A0,'0'    @D@@@@          SA,S3     A0,LINOUT+20      FOR OUTPUT IMAGEFW
)@@G@@@ @@@@          AA,U      A1,'0'    @A@@@@          SA,S4     A1,LINOUT+FX
)@@G@@20    @F@@@@          LA,S2     A1,BKUPTIME       DAY TAPE WRITTEN (TDATFY
)@@G@@E$)   @^@@@@          LA,U      A0,0@E@@@@          DI,U      A0,10     FZ
)@@G@@        GET FD DECIMAL NUMBER @ @@@@          AA,U      A0,'0'    @D@@@@GA
)@@G@@          SA,S5     A0,LINOUT+20      FOR OUTPUT IMAGE@ @@@@          AAGB
)@@G@@,U      A1,'0'    @A@@@@          SA,S6     A1,LINOUT+20    @ @@@@      GC
)@@G@@    OFF       DCFZ<1    @^@@@@          E$COL     127 @F@@@@          E$GD
)@@G@@TIME    BKUPTIME          EDIT IN TIME TAPE WRITTEN   @G@@@@. ADD CHAR TGE
)@@G@@O PRINT LINE INDICATING WHETHER BACKUP IS CURRENT OR NOT    @[@@@@.     GF
)@@G@@@H@@@@PR460     LA,U      A0,NOBCHR         ASSUME NO BACKUP - GET NO-BAGG
)@@G@@CKUP CHAR   @E@@@@          JZ        BACKEDUP,PR470    IF NO BACKUP, SAGH
)@@G@@Y SO  @C@@@@          TP        DESCFLAGS         UNLOADED? @F@@@@      GI
)@@G@@    J         PR480             YES, BACKUP MUST BE CURRENT @F@@@@      GJ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,BNCCHR         GET BACKUP NOT CURRENT CHAR @G@@@@      GK
)@@G@@    TZ        TIM1STWRT         UPDATED SINCE BACKUP CREATED?     @E@@@@GL
)@@G@@PR470     SA,S6     A0,LINOUT+6       STORE BACKUP STATUS   @[@@@@.     GM
)@@G@@@ @@@@. CHECK FOR LAPSE ENTRIES     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PR480     LA      GN
)@@G@@  A1,DESCFLAGS      GET DESCRIPTOR FLAGS  @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,LGO
)@@G@@PSCHR         GET LAPSE CHAR  @E@@@@          TEP,U     A1,LPSBIT       GP
)@@G@@  BIT 32 (LAPSE) SET?   @F@@@@          SA,S6     A0,LINOUT+6       YES,GQ
)@@G@@ ADD CHAR TO OUTPUT LINE@E@@@@          LA,U      A0,DELCHR         GET GR
)@@G@@TO-BE-DROPPED CHAR@F@@@@          TEP,U     A1,DROPBIT        BIT 24 SETGS
)@@G@@ (TO BE DROPPED)? @F@@@@          SA,S6     A0,LINOUT+6       YES, STOREGT
)@@G@@ IN OUTPUT IMAGE  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. THE TIME HAS COME TO PRINT THE INFGU
)@@G@@ORMATION    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          P$RINT    POUT              PRINGV
)@@G@@T LINE@F@@@@          SZ        LINE2             CLEAR NRP,NTP,NLPS,NSBGW
)@@G@@ FLAGS@ @@@@          ON        EXTRA     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DETERMINE GX
)@@G@@WHETHER OR NOT ADDITIONAL PRINT LINES ARE NEEDED TO EDIT    @#@@@@. MOREGY
)@@G@@ STUFF.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          TNZ       TAP               TAPEGZ
)@@G@@?     @B@@@@          J         PR500             NO  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@HA
)@@G@@. TAPE FILE:  SECOND LINE NEEDED IF >1 REEL IN DIRECTORY    @[@@@@.     HB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A0,NBRREELS       GET NUMBER OF REELS CATALOGUHC
)@@G@@ED    @D@@@@          JZ        A0,PR520          SKIP IF NONE    @C@@@@HD
)@@G@@          AN,U      A0,1              LESS ONE  @G@@@@          SA      HE
)@@G@@  A0,NTP            SET NUMBER OF REELS LEFT TO DO    @C@@@@          J HF
)@@G@@        PR520             CONTINUE  @E@@@@PR500     TZ        BMI1      HG
)@@G@@        BAD MAIN ITEM SEC 1?  @D@@@@          J         PR520           HH

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK            OPEN EDIT @C@@@@QS

)@@G@@PRINT SEG   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@PM900     L$OAD     CHEKPRTSG,PR600,1 RETUUG
)@@G@@RN TO MAIN PRINT SEG    @^@@@@/.  EDITING SUBROUTINE  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@UH
)@@G@@EDSUB     E$CHAR    ','               EDIT A COMMA    @F@@@@          E$UI
)@@G@@SKIP    1                 AND SPACE TO SEPARATE ITEMS @D@@@@          E$UJ
)@@G@@COLN    .                 GET CURRENT COL @E@@@@          L,U       A1,CUK
)@@G@@OL3           ASSUME LONG LISTING   @D@@@@          TNZ       LONGLIST  UL
)@@G@@        SHORT LISTING?  @E@@@@          L,U       A1,COL4           YES,UM
)@@G@@ SHORTER LINE     @E@@@@          TLE       A0,A1             ROOM FOR AUN
)@@G@@NOTHER ITEM?@B@@@@          J         EDSUB2            YES @E@@@@      UO
)@@G@@    P$RINT    POUT              NO, PRINT THIS LINE   @E@@@@          E$UP

)@@G@@  COL2              POSITION  @D@@@@EDSUB2    E$FD1     MI2,X4          UR
)@@G@@  EDIT NEXT ITEM  @D@@@@          AN,U      A8,1              ONE LESS TUS
)@@G@@O DO  @F@@@@          JZ        A8,1,X10          IF NO MORE, RETURN TO UT
)@@G@@1,X10 @F@@@@          LA        A0,X10            GET LIMIT AND RETURN AUU
)@@G@@DDR   @D@@@@          SSL       A0,18             ISOLATE LIMIT   @F@@@@UV
)@@G@@          TLEM      X4,A0             REACHED END OF THIS SECTOR? @D@@@@UW
)@@G@@          J         EDSUB             NO, KEEP GOING  @E@@@@          J UX
)@@G@@        0,X10             YES, RETURN TO 0,X10  @C@@@@/.  SUBROUTINE TO UY
)@@G@@READ UP NEXT DIRECTORY ITEM   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@GETNXT    TZ        SFMOUZ
)@@G@@DE2           SINGLE-FILE MODE?     @G@@@@          J         DREAD     VA
)@@G@@        YES, DO DREAD$ FOR DESIRED SECTOR @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. SINGLE-FILVB
)@@G@@E MODE NOT SET:  USE DIRLNK TO GET NEXT SECTOR  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@      VC
)@@G@@    LA        A1,,A0            GET LINK WORD IN A1   @F@@@@          JNVD
)@@G@@        A1,,X10           ERR RTN IF LINK IS NEGATIVE @E@@@@          LAVE
)@@G@@,U      A0,MI2            GET MI2 BUFFER ADDRESS@E@@@@          LMJ     VF
)@@G@@  X11,DIRLNK$       LINK TO DESIRED SECTOR@D@@@@          J         0,X1VG
)@@G@@0             ERROR RETURN    @D@@@@          J         1,X10           VH
)@@G@@  NORMAL RETURN   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SINGLE-FILE MODE IS SET:  GET NEXTVI
)@@G@@ SECTOR VIA DREAD$@[@@@@.     @E@@@@DREAD     TP        0,A0            VJ
)@@G@@  LINK WORD NEGATIVE?   @E@@@@NORTN     J         0,X10             YES,VK
)@@G@@ ERROR RETURN     @E@@@@          TNE,U     A0,MI2            FIRST TIMEVL
)@@G@@ THROUGH?   @F@@@@          J         DREAD1            NO, PACKET ALREAVM
)@@G@@DY SET UP   @D@@@@          LXI,U     A1,03401          GET MAIN ITEMS, VN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TNE,U     A0,MI0            UNLESS LINK WORD IS MI0+0,  VO
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LXI,U     A1,03402          IN WHICH CASE, GET GRANULE IVP
)@@G@@TEMS  @E@@@@          LXM,U     A1,MI2            FOR TAPE REEL NUMBERS VQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A1,RDPKT+3        STORE IN MSCON$ PACKET@F@@@@VR
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,2              ASSUME START WITH SECTOR 2  @E@@@@VS
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,MI0            GETTING GRANULE ITEMS?@F@@@@      VT
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,0              YES, START WITH SECTOR 0    @C@@@@      VU
)@@G@@    J         DREAD2            CONTINUE  @F@@@@DREAD1    L,T1      A1,RVV
)@@G@@DPKT+4        GET PREVIOUS STARTING SECTOR@F@@@@          A,U       A1,1VW
)@@G@@              INCREMENT TO NEXT SECTOR    @F@@@@DREAD2    SA,T1     A1,RVX
)@@G@@DPKT+4        AND STORE IN MSCON$ PACKET  @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,RVY
)@@G@@DPKT          GET ADDR OF PACKET    @D@@@@          ER        MSCON$    VZ
)@@G@@        DO THE DREAD$   @E@@@@          JP        A0,1,X10          IF OWA
)@@G@@K, NORMAL RETURN  @F@@@@          J         0,X10             OTHERWISE,WB
)@@G@@ ERROR RETURN     @#@@@@          END     ___OSITION  @D@@@@EDSUB2    E$WC
)@@G@@FD1     MI2,X4            EDIT NEXT ITEM  @D@@@@          AN,U      A8,1WD
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@. @MFD SINGLE FILE DREAD$ / FITEM$ ROUTINE@[@@@@.     WE
)@@G@@@^@@@@          AXR$      .   @G@@@@          CONFIG    .               WF
)@@G@@  DEFINE CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS   @D@@@@          EQUFS     .         WG
)@@G@@        DEFINE TAGS     @F@@@@QFEP      E$PKT     14,RBUFF        . @USEWH
)@@G@@ IMAGE EDIT$ PACKET     @^@@@@USEIM     '@USE   USE$,'@E@@@@RBUFF     REWI
)@@G@@S       15                EXTERNAL FILENAME     @D@@@@PRT       FORM    WJ
)@@G@@  12,6,18           PRINT$ PKT FORM @A@@@@ERR4      'ILLEGAL FILENAME SYWK
)@@G@@NTAX' @E@@@@ASGIM     '@ASG,AQYZ USE$ . '         DREAD$ FILE ASG IMAGE WL
)@@G@@@C@@@@FREIM*    '@FREE,A   USE$ . '         FREE IMAGE@E@@@@RDPKT*    + WM
)@@G@@        DREAD$            PACKET FOR MSCON$     @C@@@@          'USE$   WN
)@@G@@  '                 FILENAME  @E@@@@          +         03400,RECSTART  WO
)@@G@@  BUFFER SIZE AND ADDR. @D@@@@          +         0                 SECTWP
)@@G@@OR START    @D@@@@FITEM*    'USE$      '                FITEM$ PACKET   WQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@          RES       11  @B@@@@          ON        (CHKPCT>0)**(FATWR
)@@G@@SIZ>0)@G@@@@FATBL     RES       FATSIZ            INFO RETURNED BY MSALLWS
)@@G@@$ PUT HERE  @E@@@@FATPK     +         1,MSALL$          FLAG AS 5-WORD PWT
)@@G@@ACKET @F@@@@          +         FATSIZ,FATBL      LENGTH AND ADDR OF BUFWU
)@@G@@FER   @E@@@@          +         0                 (FILLED BY MSCON$)    WV
)@@G@@@C@@@@          +         0                       ''  @C@@@@          + WW
)@@G@@        0                       ''  @F@@@@MSBEG     EQUF      FATPK+3,,HWX
)@@G@@1       MS EQUIP - BEGINNING INDEX  @F@@@@MSEND     EQUF      FATPK+3,,HWY
)@@G@@2       MS EQUIPMENT - LAST INDEX   @F@@@@DSCBEG    EQUF      FATBL+4,,HWZ
)@@G@@1       DISC EQUIP - BEGINNING INDEX@F@@@@DSCEND    EQUF      FATPK+4,,HXA
