)@@G@@**(FATSIZ>0)@B@@@@          ON        (CHKPCT>0)**(LDJOK=0) @D@@@@PCTBUFXC
)@@G@@    RES       01000             PCT$ BUFFER     @^@@@@PCTNAM    +       XD
)@@G@@  0   @B@@@@          OFF       (CHKPCT>0)**(LDJOK=0) @ @@@@          ONXE
)@@G@@        CHKPCT    @F@@@@PCTDADN*  +         0                 POINTER TOXF
)@@G@@ NEXT PCT DAD/GTB @F@@@@.                                     ITEM, FOR XG
)@@G@@TEMP FILE DAD SNAP@ @@@@          OFF       CHKPCT    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@XH
)@@G@@. ER ERRPR$ PACKET@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ERRPKT    +         040,0,0,0,0,0   XI
)@@G@@  FOR FACILITY ERROR MESSAGES @^@@@@          +         0   @F@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    +         0                 FAC STATUS BITS GO HERE     @#@@@@/$(1),XK
)@@G@@QF000*  .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SINGLE-FILE MODE WAS SPECIFIED, SO WE'LLXL
)@@G@@ GET THE    @E@@@@. INFORMATION ABOUT A PARTICULAR FILE WITHOUT DOING A XM
)@@G@@DGET$.@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. 1. FIRST, ATTACH AN INTERNAL NAME TO THE SPECIXN
)@@G@@FIED FILE.  @F@@@@. 2. NOW TRY AN ER FITEM$ ON THAT FILE.  IF IT DOES NOXO
)@@G@@T WORK,     @G@@@@.    ASSIGN THE FILE, AND GO ON TO STEP 4.  IF THE FITXP
)@@G@@EM$ DOES WORK,    @B@@@@.    THE FILE IS ASSIGNED BY THE USER.    @F@@@@XQ
)@@G@@. 3. USING INFO FROM FITEM$, CHECK FOR TAPE FILE, TEMPORARY FILE, @G@@@@XR
)@@G@@.    ARBITRARY DEVICE FILE (NOT TAPE OR MS), ETC., AND SET APPROPRIATE  XS
)@@G@@@F@@@@.    FLAGS.  IF FILE IS NOT TEMPORARY OR ARBITRARY DEVICE, GO ON  XT
)@@G@@@E@@@@.    TO STEP 4.  IF FILE IS TEMPORARY OR ARB DEVICE, CREATE @G@@@@XU
)@@G@@.    FAKE LEAD ITEM AND MAIN ITEM BASED ON INFORMATION FROM FTIEM$.     XV
)@@G@@@ @@@@.    THEN GO ON TO STEP 5.    @F@@@@. 4. FILE IS CATALOGUED MASS SXW
)@@G@@TORAGE OR TAPE FILE, AND MAY OR MAY @F@@@@.    NOT BE ASSIGNED BY THE USXX
)@@G@@ER.  AN ER MSCON$ IS NOW DONE, USING@G@@@@.    THE DREAD$ FUNCTION, TO OXY
)@@G@@BTAIN THE DIRECTORY INFORMATION FOR THIS  @F@@@@.    FILE.  FIRST THE LEXZ
)@@G@@AD ITEM IS READ, AND THEN THE MAIN ITEM.  @G@@@@.    CHECKS ARE MADE TO YA
)@@G@@DETERMINE WHETHER THE FILE IS REMOVABLE DISC,   @D@@@@.    TAPE, OR G-OPYB
)@@G@@TION, AND APPROPRIATE FLAGS ARE SET.@G@@@@. 5. IF THE FILE IS NOT ASSIGNYC
)@@G@@ED BY THE USER, OR IF IT IS A TAPE FILE,  @H@@@@.    THIS STEP IS SKIPPEYD
)@@G@@D.  IF NOT, WE LOAD THE RUN'S PCT BANK, VIA AN LDJ    @H@@@@.    (OR ER YE
)@@G@@PCT$), AND FIND THE FILE DESCRIPTION ENTRY FOR THIS FILE.  THIS   @F@@@@YF
)@@G@@.    IS THE ONLY WAY TO FIND THE GRANULE COUNTS AND PACKIDS FOR   @G@@@@YG
)@@G@@.    TEMPORARY FIXED AND REMOVABLE MASS STORAGE FILES, AND SOMETIMES    YH
)@@G@@@F@@@@.    PROVIDES MORE UP-TO-DATE GRANULE COUNTS FOR CATALOGUED FILES,YI
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    AS WELL.  AFTER GATHERING AS MUCH INFORMATION AS IS USEFUL FOYJ
)@@G@@R THE @D@@@@.    SPECIFIC CASE, WE LDJ BACK TO THE NORMAL DBANK.  @G@@@@YK
)@@G@@.    FOR TEMPORARY REMOVABLE DISC FILES, ADDITIONAL CODE IS NEEDED TO   YL
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    OBTAIN A COPY OF THE FASTRAND-FORMAT MASS STORAGE AVAILABILTYYM
)@@G@@ TABLE@F@@@@.    (FATBL), BECAUSE THE PCT ONLY HAS SUBSYSTEM AND UNIT NUYN
)@@G@@MBERS @F@@@@.    FOR THE DISC DRIVES INVOLVED, NOT THE PACKIDS.  FATBL MYO
)@@G@@UST BE@E@@@@.    SEARCHED AND CHECKED AGAINST THE PCT 'PACKID' TABLE.   YP
)@@G@@@F@@@@. 6. IF THE FILE IS TEMPORARY OR ARBITRARY DEVICE, THE @USE NAME  YQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@.    IS NOW FREED.@G@@@@.    IF NOT, WE DETERMINE WHETHER OR NOT TYR
)@@G@@O FREE THE @USE RELATIONSHIP  @F@@@@.    NOW.  IF A SECOND PRINT LINE WIYS
)@@G@@LL BE NECESSARY FOR THE FILE, @F@@@@.    THEN WE WON'T FREE IT NOW:  ROUYT
)@@G@@TINE 'PRINT2' WILL FREE IT.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          L$OAD     CHEKYU
)@@G@@PRTSG,,1      LOAD CHECK/PRINT SEGMENT    @F@@@@. ******  SR        R15,YV
)@@G@@SFMODE        SET SINGLE-FILE MODE FLAG   @G@@@@          SR        R15,YW
)@@G@@SFMODE2       SET OTHER SINGLE-FILE MODE FLAG   @G@@@@          LA      YX
)@@G@@  A0,(0100000,QF700)  . SET UP CONTINGENCY ROUTINE    @D@@@@          ERYY
)@@G@@        IALL$             REGISTER IT     @D@@@@          TZ,S2     MFD$YZ
)@@G@@              FILENAME GIVEN? @F@@@@          J         QF004           ZA
)@@G@@  YES, NO ELEMENT SUBSTITUTION@F@@@@          LA,S1     A0,MFD$+1       ZB
)@@G@@  GET CHARS IN ELEMENT NAME   @H@@@@          JZ        A0,QF910        ZC
)@@G@@  IF NOTHING THERE EITHER, ASSUME TPF$    @F@@@@          SA,S2     A0,MZD
)@@G@@FD$           STORE AS CHARS IN FILENAME  @D@@@@          DL        A0,MZE
)@@G@@FD$+9         GET ELEMENT NAME@F@@@@          DS        A0,MFD$+4       ZF
)@@G@@  STORE IN FILENAME FIELD     @F@@@@          LA,S3     A0,MFD$+1       ZG
)@@G@@  GET ELEMENT CYCLE CHAR COUNT@F@@@@          SA,S3     A0,MFD$         ZH
)@@G@@  STORE AS F-CYCLE CHAR COUNT @D@@@@          JZ        A0,QF004        ZI
)@@G@@  IF NONE, GO ON  @D@@@@          LA        A0,MFD$+13        GET ELT CYZJ
)@@G@@CLE   @D@@@@          SA        A0,MFD$+6         STORE AS FCYCLE @[@@@@ZK
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. COMPOSE @USE IMAGE FROM FILENAME IN SPEC FIELD@[@@@@.     ZL
)@@G@@@E@@@@QF004     E$DIT     QFEP              OPEN @USE IMAGE EDIT  @D@@@@ZM
)@@G@@          TZ,S1     MFD$              QUAL GIVEN?     @B@@@@          J ZN
)@@G@@        QF006             YES @E@@@@          TNZ,S6    MFD$            ZO
)@@G@@  IMPLIED QUALIFIER?    @B@@@@          J         QF010             NO  ZP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$FD2     PCT+021           PICK UP LATEST @QUAL  @C@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@          J         QF008             CONTINUE  @D@@@@QF006     E$FD2   ZR
)@@G@@  MFD$+2            ADD QUALIFIER   @D@@@@QF008     E$CHAR    '*'       ZS
)@@G@@        AND AN ASTERISK @D@@@@QF010     E$FD2     MFD$+4            ADD ZT
)@@G@@FILENAME    @C@@@@          TNZ,S3    MFD$              F-CYCLE?  @B@@@@ZU
)@@G@@          J         QF012             NO  @^@@@@          E$CHAR    '(' ZV
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$FD1     MFD$+6            ADD FCYCLE@^@@@@          E$ZW
)@@G@@CHAR    ')' @C@@@@QF012     TNZ,S4    MFD$              READ KEY? @B@@@@ZX
)@@G@@          J         QF014             NO  @^@@@@          E$CHAR    '/' ZY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$COPY    6,MFD$+7          ADD READ KEY    @C@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@    TNZ,S5    MFD$              WRITE KEY?@B@@@@          J         QF01AA
)@@G@@8             NO  @E@@@@          J         QF016             READ AND WAB
)@@G@@RITE KEYS   @C@@@@QF014     TNZ,S5    MFD$              WRITE KEY?@B@@@@AC
)@@G@@          J         QF018             NO  @E@@@@          E$CHAR    '/' AD
)@@G@@              ONE FOR THE READ KEY, @F@@@@QF016     E$CHAR    '/'       AE
)@@G@@        AND ONE FOR THE WRITE KEY   @D@@@@          E$COPY    6,MFD$+8  AF
)@@G@@        ADD WRITE KEY   @D@@@@QF018     E$COPY    4,('. .   ')      TERMAG
)@@G@@INATE IMAGE @E@@@@. NOW HAVE @USE IMAGE, EITHER COMPOSED FROM SPEC FIELDAH
)@@G@@ OR   @F@@@@. CREATED BY PUTTING '@USE USE$' IN FRONT OF IMAGE READ VIA AI
)@@G@@READ$.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@QF020     LA        A0,(16,USEIM)     GET IMAGE AJ
)@@G@@ADDR AND MAX LENGTH     @D@@@@          ER        CSF$              PERFAK
)@@G@@ORM @USE    @D@@@@          JNZ       A0,QF430          HANDLE ERROR    AL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. TRY ER FITEM$.  IF IT WORKS, FILE IS ASG'ED TO USER,AM
)@@G@@ AND MAY BE @G@@@@. TEMPORARY FILE.  IF NOT, MUST BE CATALOGUED FILE:  WAN
)@@G@@E MUST ASG IT     @#@@@@. TO DO DREAD$.   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          SZAO
)@@G@@        FLAG4             ZERO SFASG,SFITEM,ARB,UCOPT,TEMP FLAGS  @E@@@@AP
)@@G@@          SZ        FITEM+10          INITIALIZE SUBCODE    @G@@@@      AQ
)@@G@@    SZ        FITEM+11          CLEAR TAPE REELS IN CASE LEFT     @E@@@@AR
)@@G@@          SZ        FITEM+12          BY PRVIOUS FITEM$     @B@@@@      AS
)@@G@@    LA        A0,(0377777,FITEM)  . @D@@@@          ER        FITEM$    AT
)@@G@@        GET FILE INFO   @E@@@@          TNZ,S1    FITEM+6           IS FAU
)@@G@@ILE ASSIGNED?     @E@@@@          J         QF070             NO, ASG ANAV
)@@G@@D DO DREAD$ @E@@@@          SR        R15,SFITEM        YES, SET FITEM FAW
)@@G@@LAG   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CHECK FOR @ASG,C OR @ASG,U  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@AX
)@@G@@          LA,S1     A0,FITEM+6        GET EQUIP CODE  @E@@@@          TGAY
)@@G@@,U      A0,070            COMMUNICATIONS STUFF? @D@@@@          J       AZ
)@@G@@  FIT005            YES, SKIP THIS  @D@@@@          L         A1,FITEM+7BA
)@@G@@        GET OPTION BITS @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,0              ASSUBB
)@@G@@ME NOT C OR U     @D@@@@          TEP       A1,(1*/('Z'-'C')) C-OPTION UBC
)@@G@@SED?  @D@@@@          L,U       A2,'C'            YES, GET FD 'C' @D@@@@BD
)@@G@@          TEP,U     A1,1*/('Z'-'U')   U-OPTION USED?  @D@@@@          L,BE
)@@G@@U       A2,'U'            YES, GET FD U   @F@@@@          S         A2,UBF
)@@G@@COPT          STORE ZERO OR CHAR IN FLAG  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. CHECK FOR BG
)@@G@@ARBITRARY DEVICE FILE (NOT TAPE OR MASS STORAGE)@[@@@@.     @E@@@@FIT005BH
)@@G@@    TLE,U     A0,040            TAPE OR MASS STORAGE? @F@@@@          J BI
)@@G@@        FIT010            YES, CHECK FOR TEMP FILE    @D@@@@          SRBJ
)@@G@@        R15,ARB           YES, SET FLAG   @E@@@@          J         FIT0BK
)@@G@@20            SKIP TEMP FILE CHECK  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CHECK FOR TEMPORBL
)@@G@@ARY FILE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@FIT010    LA,S1     A0,FITEM+7        GET BM
)@@G@@DESC BITS   @D@@@@          TOP,U     A0,020            TEMPORARY FILE? BN
)@@G@@@G@@@@          J         QF080             NO, DO DREAD$ FOR CATALOGUEDBO
)@@G@@ FILE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. TEMPORARY FILE:  CREATE FAKE LEAD/MAIN ITEMS UBP
)@@G@@SING INFO FROM FITEM$   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@FIT020    SR        R15,TEMP  BQ
)@@G@@        SET TEMP FILE FLAG    @ @@@@          L,U       R1,28*3   @A@@@@BR
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(1,RECSTART) @ @@@@          LA,U      A1,(0)    BS
)@@G@@@F@@@@          BT        A0,,*A1           ZERO-FILL LI0, MI0, AND MI1 BT
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @F@@@@          SR        R15,MFD$F BU
)@@G@@        ASSUME NEW-FORMAT 'MFD'     @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMFD    BV
)@@G@@@C@@@@          DL        A0,FITEM+4        QUALIFIER @ @@@@          DSBW
)@@G@@        A0,QUAL   @ @@@@          DS        A0,MI0QUAL@C@@@@          DLBX
)@@G@@        A0,FITEM+2        FILENAME  @ @@@@          DS        A0,FILE   BY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          DS        A0,MI0FILE@C@@@@          DL        A0,PCT+2  BZ
)@@G@@        PROJECT-ID@ @@@@          DS        A0,PROJ   @ @@@@          DSCA
)@@G@@        A0,MI0PROJ@C@@@@          DL        A0,PCT+023        ACCOUNT   CB
)@@G@@@ @@@@          DS        A0,ACCOUNT@C@@@@          LA,S1     A0,FITEM+6CC
)@@G@@        EQUIP CODE@E@@@@          TG,U      A0,020            WORD ADDRECD
)@@G@@SSABLE?     @ @@@@          TG,U      A0,026    @B@@@@          J       CE
)@@G@@  $+2               NO  @F@@@@          A,U       A0,012            YES,CF
)@@G@@ CHANGE TO F-TYPE CODE  @F@@@@          SA        A0,MI0OLDEQP      SET CG
)@@G@@OLD EQUIP CODE IN MI0   @F@@@@          SZ        FLAGS             CLEACH
)@@G@@R TAP,GFIL,VFIL,BMI1    @D@@@@          SZ        RDISC             CLEACI
)@@G@@R RDISC FLAG@G@@@@          L         A1,('F     ')     ASSUME NORMAL MACJ
)@@G@@SS STORAGE EQUIP  @F@@@@          S         A1,MNEMONIC       STORE AS ACK
)@@G@@SSIGN MNEMONIC    @G@@@@.                                     AT THIS POCL
)@@G@@INT, FILTYP = MSTYP (0) @C@@@@          TG,U      A0,020            TAPECM
)@@G@@ FILE?@C@@@@          J         FIT030            NO, GO ON @D@@@@      CN
)@@G@@    SR        R15,TAP           YES, SET FLAG   @F@@@@          L,U     CO
)@@G@@  A1,TAPTYP         GET TAPE FILE TYPE INDICATOR@C@@@@          S       CP
)@@G@@  A1,FILTYP         SET IN LI0@E@@@@          L         A1,('T     ')   CQ
)@@G@@  GET TAPE EQUIP TYPE   @F@@@@          S         A1,MNEMONIC       STORCR
)@@G@@E AS ASSIGN MNEMONIC    @C@@@@FIT030    LA,T3     A1,FITEM+6        GET CS
)@@G@@FCYCLE@E@@@@          TLE,U     A0,040            TAPE OR MASS STORAGE? CT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A1,FCYCLE         YES, STORE FCYCLE IN MI0    CU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,S6     A1,FITEM+10       GET SUBCODE     @D@@@@      CV
)@@G@@    TG,U      A0,030            MASS STORAGE?   @ @@@@          TG,U    CW
)@@G@@  A0,040    @B@@@@          J         FIT100            NO  @[@@@@.     CX
)@@G@@@ @@@@. TEMPORARY MASS STORAGE FILE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          SA      CY
)@@G@@  A1,OLDSUBCOD      YES, STORE SUBCODE IN LI0   @E@@@@          DL      CZ
)@@G@@  A0,FITEM+8        INITIAL GRAN,MAX GRAN @G@@@@.                       DA
)@@G@@              AND HIGHEST TRK,HIGHEST GRAN NBR  @D@@@@          SA      DB
)@@G@@  A0,MAXGRAN        STORE MAX GRAN  @E@@@@          SSL       A0,18     DC
)@@G@@        ISOLATE INITIAL GRAN  @C@@@@          SA        A0,INITRESV     DD
)@@G@@  STORE IT  @E@@@@          SA        A1,HIGRANULE      STORE HIGHEST GRDE
)@@G@@AN NBR@F@@@@          SSL       A1,18             ISOLATE HIGHEST TRACK DF
)@@G@@REF   @C@@@@          SA        A1,HITRACK        STORE IT  @G@@@@      DG
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A1,PCHAR          PCHAR (ASSUMED = 0 AT THIS POINT) @E@@@@DH
)@@G@@          TZ,S3     FITEM+6           POSITION GRANULARITY? @E@@@@      DI
)@@G@@    AA,U      A1,POSBIT         YES, SET BIT FOR PCHAR@E@@@@          LADJ
)@@G@@,S2     A0,FITEM+6        GET FILE MODE BITS    @E@@@@          TEP,U   DK

)@@G@@ADBIT         YES, SET BIT FOR PCHAR@G@@@@          SA,S1     A1,PCHAR  DM
)@@G@@        STORE PCHAR BITS IN MAIN ITEM     @E@@@@FIT100    L,S1      A0,FDN
)@@G@@ITEM+6        A0 = EQUIPMENT CODE   @D@@@@          TG,U      A0,070    DO

)@@G@@ NO ASG OPTIONS   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. TAPE OR MASS STORAGE  @[@@@@.     DQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A0,FITEM+7        A0 = ASSIGN OPTIONS   @D@@@@DR
)@@G@@          TOP       A0,(1*/('Z'-'G')) G-OPTION FILE?  @B@@@@          J DS
)@@G@@        FIT110            NO  @D@@@@          SR        R15,GFIL        DT

)@@G@@S (ASSUMED=0 AT THIS POINT)   @E@@@@          AA,U      A1,LI0GBIT      DV

)@@G@@-OPTION INDICATOR @C@@@@          J         FIT111            GO ON     DZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@FIT110    LA        A1,INHIBITS       INHIBIT BITS (ASSUMED=0 NOW)EA
)@@G@@@E@@@@FIT111    TOP,U     A0,1*/('Z'-'P')   ASG'D WITH P-OPTION?  @E@@@@EB
)@@G@@          AA,U      A1,PBIT           NO, SET PRIVATE BIT   @C@@@@      EC
)@@G@@    TEP,U     A0,1*/('Z'-'R')   READ ONLY?@E@@@@          AA,U      A1,RED
)@@G@@ONLY          YES, SET READ ONLY BIT@D@@@@          TEP,U     A0,1*/('Z'EE
)@@G@@-'W')   WRITE ONLY?     @D@@@@          AA,U      A1,WONLY          YES,EF
)@@G@@ SET BIT    @E@@@@          SA        A1,INHIBITS       STORE INHIBIT BIEG
)@@G@@TS    @C@@@@          TNZ       TAP               TAPE FILE?@B@@@@      EH
)@@G@@    J         FIT120            NO  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. TAPE FILE:  SET EI
)@@G@@MODE BITS   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LA,H2     A0,FITEM+8        GET EJ
)@@G@@MODE BITS   @E@@@@          L         A1,MI0OLDEQP      GET OLD EQUIPMENEK
)@@G@@T CODE@D@@@@          TG,U      A1,011            MSA TAPE DEVICE?@ @@@@EL
)@@G@@          TG,U      A1,016    @D@@@@          J         FIT118          EM
)@@G@@  NO, NON-MSA TAPE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. TEMPORARY TAPE FILE ON MSA TAPE DEEN
)@@G@@VICE: @E@@@@. UNIVAC'S DOCUMENTATION SAYS THAT THE NON-MSA TAPE MODES   EO
)@@G@@@F@@@@. CELL IN MI0+21,,S4 IS ZERO FOR MSA TAPES, BUT THIS IS NOT TRUE. EP

)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         $+3               NO, 9-TRACK     @E@@@@      EV

)@@G@@,U      A2,040            YES, SET EVEN PARITY BIT    @G@@@@          SAEX

)@@G@@  A2,00200          ASSUME QUARTER-WORD TRANSFER@D@@@@          TEP,U   FA

)@@G@@        YES @D@@@@          TEP,U     A0,1*/16          6-BIT PACKED?   FC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LA,U      A2,00400          YES @F@@@@          TG,U    FD

)@@G@@  FIT114            NO, 9-TRACK UNIT@E@@@@          TOP,U     A0,1*/13  FF

)@@G@@  AND GO ON @D@@@@FIT114    .                           9-TRACK UNIT    FJ

)@@G@@  FIT120            AND GO ON @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. TEMPORARY TAPE FILE ONFN
)@@G@@ NON-MSA DEVICE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@FIT118    . @D@@@@          SSL     FO
)@@G@@  A0,9              ADJUST THEM     @C@@@@          SA        A0,TAPEMODFP
)@@G@@ES      STORE THEM@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ALL TEMPORARY FILES:  SET TIME/DATFQ
)@@G@@E OF ASG, ASG COUNT     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@FIT120    ER        TDATE$    FR
)@@G@@        GET CURRENT TIME/DATE @E@@@@          SA        A0,DATLSTASG    FS
)@@G@@  STORE AS LAST ASG TIME@D@@@@          SR        R15,TOTASGCNT     TOTAFT
)@@G@@L ASSIGNS   @G@@@@          SR        R15,CURASGCNT     NUMBER OF RUNS AFU
)@@G@@SG'D TO THIS FILE @G@@@@          J         QF090             DON'T DO DFV
)@@G@@READ$ FOR TEMP/ARB FILE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. CATALOGUED FILE - DO MSCON$ FW
)@@G@@DREAD$ FOR DIRECTORY INFORMATION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@QF070     LA,U    FX
)@@G@@  A0,ASGIM          MUST FIRST ASSIGN THE FILE  @^@@@@          ER      FY
)@@G@@  CSF$@E@@@@          JN        A0,QF410          HANDLE ASSIGN ERROR   FZ

)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A0,(03400,RECSTART) . SET UP DREAD$ FOR LEAD IGC

)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,RDPKT          GET DREAD$ PKT ADDR   @D@@@@          ERGE
)@@G@@        MSCON$            DREAD$ FOR LI0  @D@@@@          JN        A0,QGF

)@@G@@RT+28) . RESET DREAD$ FOR MI0 & 1   @E@@@@          SA        A0,RDPKT+3GH

)@@G@@FD FLAG     @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMFD    @F@@@@          LA      GZ

)@@G@@VABLE DISC FILE?  @D@@@@          SR        R15,RDISC         YES, SET FHE
)@@G@@LAG   @ @@@@          ON        CHKPCT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE USEHF
)@@G@@R HAS ASSIGNED THE FILE (RATHER THAN @MFD ITSELF,     @G@@@@. TO DO THE HG
)@@G@@DREAD$), THEN WE CAN GET ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON THE FILE @G@@@@. FROMHH
)@@G@@ THE USER'S PCT.  IF THE FILE IS A TEMPORARY REMOVABLE DISC FILE, @F@@@@HI
)@@G@@. FOR INSTANCE, THIS IS THE ONLY WAY WE WILL GET THE PACKID(S).   @G@@@@HJ
)@@G@@. ALSO, SINCE THE DIRECTORY IS NOT UPDATED UNTIL THE USER FREES THE     HK
)@@G@@@G@@@@. FILE, THE DREAD$ MAY NOT PROVIDE UP-TO-DATE INFORMATION ON SUCH HL

)@@G@@CURRENT     @D@@@@. IN THE PCT, IF THE INFORMATION IS NOT IN EXPOOL.    HN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@QF090     TZ        SFASG             ASG'D BY SINGLE-HO
)@@G@@FILE MODE ROUTINE?@E@@@@          J         PCT700            YES, DON'THP

)@@G@@T FOR USE BY 'PRINT' ROUTINE IF DAD/GTB SNAP IS WANTED@^@@@@. FOR A TEMPII

)@@G@@$(0).                                 THESE INSTRUCTIONS IN IBANK @]@@@@IN
)@@G@@PCT100    . @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CHECK FOR 1108 OR 1110, AND GET PROPER PIO
)@@G@@CT ADDRESS  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          LX,U      X4,RPCTA$-1       X4 =IP

)@@G@@        LDJOK=0   @E@@@@          L,U       A0,PCTBUF         GET ADDR OIU

)@@G@@T BLOCK     @^@@@@          ER        PCT$@F@@@@          L,U       A0,0IW
)@@G@@777241        FAKE ADDR OF PCTNAM, SINCE  @F@@@@          S         A0,PIX
)@@G@@CTNAM         LINKS WILL BE RELATIVE TO IT@E@@@@          LX,U      X4,PIY

)@@G@@ADN           YES: FIRST TIME FOR THIS FILE?    @F@@@@          J       JD

)@@G@@          DL        A4,FITEM          GET FILENAME    @F@@@@PCT200    L JF
)@@G@@        X3,X4             X3 = ADDR OF PCTNAM BUFFER  @F@@@@          LXJG

)@@G@@          AN,U      A0,1              ADJUST FOR JGD  @G@@@@          S JK
)@@G@@        A0,R1             R1 = NUMBER OF FILES-1 FOR LOOP   @[@@@@.     JL
)@@G@@@G@@@@. SINCE WE JUST DID A @USE, WE SHOULD FIND THE FILENAME ON FIRST TJM
)@@G@@RY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@PCT300    DTE       A4,1,X3           CHECK FILEJN
)@@G@@NAME VS. NAME IN BUFFER @G@@@@          J         PCT400            NO MJO

)@@G@@  MATCH - PICK UP DESC TABLE INDEX  @D@@@@          A         A0,X4     JQ
)@@G@@        ADD PCTNAM ADDR @F@@@@          DO LDJOK=0 , LMJ A3,PCTLNK  OBTAJR
)@@G@@IN CORRECT PCT BLOCK    @D@@@@          TNZ       X10               PCTDJS
)@@G@@AD CALL?    @C@@@@          J         PCT305            NO, GO ON @G@@@@JT
)@@G@@          LA,H2     A1,0,A0           GET LINK TO FIRST DAD/GTB ITEM    JU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LXI,U     A1,0,A0           GET DESC ITEM ADDR ALSO     JV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A1,PCTDADN        UPDATE NEXT ITEM ADDR @E@@@@JW
)@@G@@          J         PCTDAD2           HANDLE SUBROUTINE CALL@[@@@@.     JX
)@@G@@@B@@@@. NO GRANULE COUNTS FOR TAPE/ARB FILES    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@PCT305JY
)@@G@@    TNZ       TAP               TAPE FILE?@D@@@@          TZ        ARB JZ
)@@G@@              OR ARB DEVICE?  @F@@@@          J         PCT320          KA
)@@G@@  YES, SKIP GRANULE COUNTS    @C@@@@          LA,S3     A1,3,A0         KB
)@@G@@  GET PCFIND@E@@@@          TNE,U     A1,1              EXPOOL ITEM EXISKC
)@@G@@TS?   @H@@@@          J         PCT320            YES, WON'T FIND GRANULKD
)@@G@@E COUNTS HERE     @G@@@@          L         A3,A0             SET FOR TRKE
)@@G@@ANSFER OF GRANULE COUNTS@E@@@@          LXI,U     A3,-1             FROMKF
)@@G@@ DESC TABLE TO MI0@^@@@@          L,U       A1,7@F@@@@          LXM,U   KG
)@@G@@  X3,GRANULES+7     POINT TO LAST GRANULE ENTRY @C@@@@          LXI,U   KH
)@@G@@  X3,-1             SET INC   @ @@@@PCT310    L,H2      A2,016,*A3@E@@@@KI
)@@G@@          SA,H2     A2,0,*X3          STORE GRANULE COUNTS  @G@@@@      KJ
)@@G@@    JGD       A1,PCT310         GET COUNTS FOR EQUIP TYPES 030-037@F@@@@KK
)@@G@@          LA,H1     A1,012,A0         GET HIGHEST TRACK WRITTEN   @E@@@@KL
)@@G@@          SA        A1,HITRACK        STORE IN MAIN ITEM    @[@@@@.     KM
)@@G@@@C@@@@. SEE COMMENTS AT TAG 'MCTEQ' IN ELEMENT 'MFD'  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@KN
)@@G@@PCT320    TNZ       TEMP              TEMPORARY FILE? @F@@@@          J KO
)@@G@@        PCT600            NO, NO NEED FOR MSALL$, ETC.@H@@@@          TNKP
)@@G@@Z       MCTEQ             ANYTHING IN SPECIFIC MNEMONIC TABLE?    @C@@@@KQ
)@@G@@          J         PCT325            NO, GO ON @H@@@@          L,T1    KR
)@@G@@  X3,1,A0           YES, PICK UP EQUIP INDEX FROM PCT ITEM  @E@@@@      KS
)@@G@@    L         A1,MCTEQ-1,X3     GET SPECIFIC MNEMONIC @F@@@@          S KT
)@@G@@        A1,MNEMONIC       STORE IN MAIN ITEM SECTOR 0 @C@@@@          J KU
)@@G@@        PCT330            GO ON     @]@@@@PCT325    . @ @@@@          ONKV
)@@G@@        OLDMFD    @G@@@@          SZ        MFD$F             WELL, CAN'KW
)@@G@@T BE NEW FORMAT 'MFD'   @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMFD    @C@@@@PCT330KX
)@@G@@    TNZ       TAP               TAPE FILE?@D@@@@          TZ        ARB KY
)@@G@@              OR ARB DEVICE?  @E@@@@          J         PCT600          KZ
)@@G@@  YES, ALL DONE WITH PCT@ @@@@          ON        FATSIZ=0  @D@@@@      LA
)@@G@@    J         PCT600            RETURN TO NORMAL@ @@@@          OFF     LB
)@@G@@  FATSIZ=0  @ @@@@          ON        FATSIZ    @H@@@@          TNZ,H1  LC
)@@G@@  014,A0            TEMP FILE WITH PACKID LINK (REMOVABLE)  @E@@@@      LD
)@@G@@    J         PCT600            NO, NO NEED FOR MSALL$@[@@@@.     @F@@@@LE
)@@G@@. IT'S A TEMPORARY REMOVABLE DISC FILE - GET FATBL TO FIND PACKIDS@[@@@@LF
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@          S         A0,X4             STORE DESC ITEM ADDR ILG
)@@G@@N X4  @E@@@@          L,U       A0,FATPK          GET MSCON$ PACKET     LH
)@@G@@@C@@@@          ER        MSCON$            DO MSALL$ @E@@@@          JNLI
)@@G@@        A0,PCT600         IF NO GOOD, FORGET IT @F@@@@          L       LJ
)@@G@@  X3,MSBEG          GET STARTING MS DEVICE INDEX@F@@@@          AN,T1   LK
)@@G@@  X3,1,X4           - EQUIP INDEX FOR THIS FILE @E@@@@.                 LL
)@@G@@                    = INDEX INTO FATBL    @ @@@@          ON        OLDMLM
)@@G@@FD    @D@@@@          TZ        MSBEG             NEW-TYPE FATBL? @C@@@@LN
)@@G@@          J         $+3               YES, GO ON@F@@@@          L,S1    LO
)@@G@@  X3,1,X4           NO, GET OLD EQUIPMENT CODE  @E@@@@          AN,U    LP
)@@G@@  X3,030            ADJUST FOR FATBL INDEX@ @@@@          OFF       OLDMLQ
)@@G@@FD    @F@@@@          L,H1      A0,014,X4         GET REL LINK TO PACKIDLR
)@@G@@ TABLE@E@@@@          A         A0,X4             ADD CURRENT ITEM ADDR LS
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO LDJOK=0 , LMJ A3,PCTLNK  OBTAIN CORRECT PCT BLOCK    LT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          S         A0,X4             X4 = ADDR OF PACKID TABLE   LU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A1,X3             A1 = EQUIP INDEX INTO FATBL LV
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        OLDMFD    @D@@@@          TZ        MSBEG     LW
)@@G@@        NEW-TYPE FATBL? @C@@@@          J         $+3               YES,LX
)@@G@@ GO ON@G@@@@          TNZ,H1    FATBL,A1          ANY OF THESE DISCS CONLY
)@@G@@FIGURED?    @F@@@@          J         PCT600            NO, FORGET THE WLZ
)@@G@@HOLE THING  @ @@@@          OFF       OLDMFD    @G@@@@          L,H1    MA
)@@G@@  X3,FATBL,A1       YES, GET LINK TO STATUS TABLE     @H@@@@          A,MB
)@@G@@U       X3,FATBL          X3 = ABS LOC OF STATUS TBL IN FATBL     @E@@@@MC
)@@G@@          L,T1      R3,,X3            R3 = NUMBER OF UNITS  @D@@@@      MD
)@@G@@    JGD       R3,$+1            ADJUST FOR JGD  @G@@@@          A       ME
)@@G@@  X3,(5,3)          SET INC, MOVE UP TO UNIT INFO     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@MF
)@@G@@. FOR EACH DISC UNIT IN FATBL, CHECK TO SEE IF THIS UNIT IS IN    @ @@@@MG
)@@G@@. THE FILE'S PACKID TABLE.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@FAT100    L,H2      A0,,MH
)@@G@@X4            GET NUMBER OF PACKS THIS FILE     @D@@@@          TG,U    MI
)@@G@@  A0,11             MORE THAN 10?   @D@@@@          L,U       A0,10     MJ
)@@G@@        YES, LIMIT TO 10@G@@@@          S         A0,R1             SET MK
)@@G@@SEARCH REPEAT COUNT IN R1     @E@@@@          L,H1      A0,1,X3         ML
)@@G@@  GET SS/U FROM FATBL   @G@@@@          L,U       A1,1,X4           GET MM
)@@G@@ADDR OF 1ST SS/U IN TABLE     @D@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1            MN
)@@G@@  ONE-WORD ENTRIES@F@@@@          SE,H1     A0,,*A1           IS THIS UNMO
)@@G@@IT ONE OF THEM?   @E@@@@          J         FAT200            NO, TRY NEMP
)@@G@@XT UNIT     @E@@@@          S         R15,RDISC         YES, SET REM DISMQ
)@@G@@C FLAG@E@@@@          LA        A1,NBRPACKS       BUMP PACK COUNT IN MI1MR
)@@G@@@^@@@@          A,U       A1,1@A@@@@          SA        A1,NBRPACKS     MS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A0,4,X3           GET PACKID FROM FATBL @E@@@@MT
)@@G@@.                                     AND STORE IT IN MI1   @F@@@@      MU
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,PACKENTRY-1    POINT TO PACKID ENTRIES     @E@@@@      MV
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,,A1            ADD CURRENT INDEX     @G@@@@          S MW
)@@G@@        A0,0,A2           NOTE: WE ARE STORING UP TO 10     @G@@@@.     MX
)@@G@@                                PACKIDS, IN ONE-WORD ENTRIES,     @G@@@@MY
)@@G@@.                                     WHEREAS NORMAL FORMAT IS UP TO 5  MZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@.                                     IN 2-WORD ENTRIES     @G@@@@NA
)@@G@@.                                     PRINT2 ROUTINE WILL HAVE TO CHECK NB
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                                     FOR TEMP FILE, AND CHANGE THNC
)@@G@@INGS  @D@@@@.                                     ACCORDINGLY.    @E@@@@ND
)@@G@@FAT200    NOP       0,0,*X3           INC TO NEXT UNIT ENTRY@D@@@@      NE
)@@G@@    JGD       R3,FAT100         CHECK ALL UNITS @C@@@@          J       NF
)@@G@@  PCT600            ALL DONE  @ @@@@          OFF       FATSIZ    @[@@@@NG
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@. HAVE NOT YET FOUND CORRECT PCT ITEM   ...CONTINUE LOOKING NH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@PCT400    NOP       0,0,*X3           INDEX TO NEXT ENNI
)@@G@@TRY IN PCTNAM BUFFER    @G@@@@          JGD       R1,PCT300         CHECNJ
)@@G@@K ALL ENTRIES IN THIS BUFFER  @G@@@@PCT500    .                         NK
)@@G@@ REACHED END OF THIS PCTNAM BUFFER  @F@@@@          TNZ,H2    0,X4      NL
)@@G@@        DOES ANOTHER BUFFER EXIST?  @D@@@@          J         PCT600    NM
)@@G@@        NO, THAT'S ALL  @H@@@@          L,H2      A0,,X4            YES,NN
)@@G@@ GET LINK TO NEXT PCTNAM BUFFER     @F@@@@          A         A0,X4     NO
)@@G@@        ADD ADDR OF CURRENT BUFFER  @F@@@@          DO LDJOK=0 , LMJ A3,NP
)@@G@@PCTLNK  OBTAIN CORRECT PCT BLOCK    @G@@@@          S         A0,X4     NQ
)@@G@@        X4 = ADDR OF NEW PCTNAM BUFFER    @G@@@@          J         PCT2NR
)@@G@@00            SEARCH NEW BUFFER FOR FILENAME    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     NS
)@@G@@@G@@@@. CONTINUATION OF 'PCTDAD' SUBROUTINE.  FINDS NEXT DAD/GRANULE ITENT
)@@G@@M     @E@@@@. (FOR A PARTICULAR FILE) IN THE PCT, AND RETURNS IT TO THE NU
)@@G@@@F@@@@. CALLER IN MI0.  THE ONLY CALLER AT THE TIME OF THIS WRITING     NV
)@@G@@@F@@@@. IS THE 'PRINT' ROUTINE, WHICH USES IT TO SNAP THE DAD/GTB OF    NW
)@@G@@@#@@@@. TEMPORARY FILES.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@PCTDAD2   LA,H2     A0,PCTDADNNX
)@@G@@        PICK UP DAD/GTB ITEM LINK   @F@@@@          JZ        A0,PCT600 NY
)@@G@@        IF NO MORE, RETURN 0,X10    @G@@@@          AA,H1     A0,PCTDADNNZ
)@@G@@        IT'S RELATIVE TO PREVIOUS ITEM    @F@@@@          DO LDJOK=0 , LOA
)@@G@@MJ A3,PCTLNK  OBTAIN CORRECT PCT BLOCK    @E@@@@          SA,H1     A0,POB
)@@G@@CTDADN        STORE ADDR OF NEW ITEM@E@@@@          LA,H2     A1,0,A0   OC
)@@G@@        GET LINK TO NEXT ITEM @F@@@@          SA,H2     A1,PCTDADN      OD
)@@G@@  AND STORE IT FOR NEXT CALL  @F@@@@          LA,H1     A2,1,A0         OE
)@@G@@  GET GRANULE # OF 1ST GRAN   @F@@@@.                                   OF
)@@G@@  IN ITEM ***OLDMFD ONLY***   @G@@@@          AA,U      A0,3            OG
)@@G@@  BUMP TO START OF DAD/GTB INFO     @D@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1      OH
)@@G@@        SET INC FOR BT  @F@@@@          LXM,U     A1,MI0            SET OI
)@@G@@BT DESTINATION AS MI0   @D@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1              SET OJ
)@@G@@INC FOR BT  @E@@@@          LR,U      R1,28             BT ONE DAD/GTB IOK
)@@G@@TEM   @D@@@@          BT        A1,,*A0           DO THE TRANSFER @E@@@@OL
)@@G@@          LX,U      X10,1,X10         SET TO RETURN TO 1,X10@E@@@@.     OM
)@@G@@                                FALL THRU TO PCT600 TO@G@@@@.           ON
)@@G@@                          RETRIEVE DBANK & RTN TO CALLER    @C@@@@/. ALLOO
)@@G@@ THROUGH WITH PCT   ...RELOAD MFD'S DBANK @[@@@@.     @H@@@@PCT600    . OP
)@@G@@                          NO MORE BUFFERS, OR GOT WHAT WE WANTED  @E@@@@OQ
)@@G@@          DO LDJOK>0 , LDJ X11,PCT610 RELOAD PROGRAM DBANK  @G@@@@$(1). OR
)@@G@@                                THESE INSTRUCTIONS IN DBANK AGAIN @F@@@@OS
)@@G@@PCT610    TZ        X10               WAS THIS A PCTDAD SUB CALL? @E@@@@OT
)@@G@@          J         0,X10             YES, RETURN TO CALLER @ @@@@      OU
)@@G@@    OFF       CHKPCT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PCT700    TZ        ARB       OV
)@@G@@        ARBITRARY DEVICE?     @E@@@@          J         QF400           OW
)@@G@@  YES, FREE THE USE NAME@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF FILE HAS MORE THAN ONE TAOX
)@@G@@PE REEL, OR MORE THAN ONE PACKID, OR@G@@@@. MORE THAN ONE BACKUP REEL (IOY
)@@G@@N BATCH MODE), THEN A SECOND LINE WILL    @G@@@@. BE PRINTED WITH THIS IOZ
)@@G@@NFORMATION.  ROUTINE 'PRINT2' WILL DO DREAD$'S, @E@@@@. SO WE SHOULD NOTPA
)@@G@@ FREE THE FILE HERE IF THIS IS THE CASE.  @F@@@@. ALSO, NO FREE SHOULD BPB
)@@G@@E DONE NOW IF A SNAP$ IS REQUESTED FOR THE@G@@@@. GRANULE (DAD) ITEMS, LPC
)@@G@@EAD ITEM SECTOR 1, OR MAIN ITEM SECTORS 2-N.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@      PD
)@@G@@    ON        SNAPOK    @D@@@@          LA        A0,SNAP           GET PE
)@@G@@SNAP BITS   @E@@@@          AND,U     A0,SNGT+SNL1+SNM2 FUNNY SNAP$ WANTPF
)@@G@@ED?   @F@@@@          JNZ       A1,QF500          YES, DON'T FREE THE FIPG
)@@G@@LE YET@ @@@@          OFF       SNAPOK    @C@@@@          TZ        TEMPPH
)@@G@@              TEMP FILE?@E@@@@          J         QF400             YES,PI
)@@G@@ FREE THE USE NAME@C@@@@          TNZ       TAP               TAPE FILE?PJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         QF100             NO  @F@@@@          LA      PK
)@@G@@  A0,NBRREELS       YES, GET NUMBER OF REELS    @D@@@@          TG,U    PL
)@@G@@  A0,2              MORE THAN ONE?  @F@@@@          J         QF500     PM
)@@G@@        YES, DON'T FREE FILE (PRINT2@D@@@@.                             PN
)@@G@@        WILL DO IT).    @E@@@@          TZ        TMSAMODES         MSA PO
)@@G@@TAPE EQUIPMENT?   @E@@@@          J         QF500             YES, DON'TPP
)@@G@@ FREE FILE  @F@@@@QF100     JZ        RDISC,QF200       REMOVABLE?  NO,QPQ
)@@G@@F200  YES   @E@@@@          LA        A0,NBRPACKS       GET NUMBER OF PAPR
)@@G@@CKS   @D@@@@          TG,U      A0,2              MORE THAN ONE?  @E@@@@PS
)@@G@@          J         QF500             YES, DON'T FREE FILE  @E@@@@QF200 PT
)@@G@@    LA        A1,DESCFLAGS      GET DESCRIPTOR BITS   @G@@@@          JZPU
)@@G@@        LONGLIST,QF400    IF SHORT LISTING, DON'T WORRY     @F@@@@.     PV
)@@G@@                                  ABOUT BACKUPS OR LAPSES   @C@@@@      PW
)@@G@@    TOP,U     A1,BAKBIT         BACKED UP?@B@@@@          J         QF30PX
)@@G@@0             NO  @F@@@@          LA        A0,BKUPREELS      GET NUMBERPY
)@@G@@ OF BACKUP REELS  @D@@@@          TG,U      A0,2              MORE THAN PZ
)@@G@@ONE?  @E@@@@          J         QF500             YES, DON'T FREE FILE  QA
)@@G@@@C@@@@QF300     TEP,U     A1,LPSBIT         LAPSES?   @E@@@@          J QB
)@@G@@        QF500             YES, DON'T FREE FILE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FREEQC
)@@G@@ THE @USE RELATIONSHIP.  IF THE USER ALREADY HAD THE FILE   @G@@@@. ASSIQD
)@@G@@GNED, JUST FREE THE INTERNAL NAME 'USE$'.  OTHERWISE, FREE THE    @E@@@@QE
)@@G@@. NAME AND THE FILE (BUT RETAIN ANY OTHER @USE RELATIONS).  @[@@@@.     QF
)@@G@@@D@@@@QF400     LA,U      A0,' '            ASSUME @FREE,A  @G@@@@      QG
)@@G@@    TZ        SFASG             ASG'D BY SINGLE-FILE MODE ROUTINE?@F@@@@QH
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,'R'            YES, DO @FREE,AR INSTEAD    @E@@@@QI
)@@G@@          SA,S2     A0,FREIM+1        STORE CORRECT OPTION  @D@@@@      QJ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,FREIM          GET FREE IMAGE  @C@@@@          ER      QK
)@@G@@  CSF$              DO CSF$   @B@@@@          JZ        A0,QF500        QL
)@@G@@  OK  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ERROR ASSIGNING (OR FREEING) THE FILE   @[@@@@QM
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@QF410     S         A0,ERRPKT+2       STORE FAC ERROR BITS FQN
)@@G@@OR ERRPR$   @D@@@@          LA,U      A0,FREIM          GET @FREE IMAGE QO
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ER        CSF$              FREE USE NAME   @E@@@@      QP
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,ERRPKT         POINT TO ERRPR$ PACKET@H@@@@QF415     ERQQ
)@@G@@        ERRPR$            EDIT THE INFO (IF ERRPR$ IS UNDEFINED,  @I@@@@QR
)@@G@@.                                     WE AUTOMATICALLY REVERT TO THE OLDQS
)@@G@@ METHOD)    @F@@@@          JZ        A0,QF900          IF OK, TRY ANOTHQT
)@@G@@ER DATA CARD@E@@@@QF416     LX,U      X10,('FAC: &')    GET ADDR OF ERROQU
)@@G@@R MSG @F@@@@          LA        A0,ERRPKT+2       RESTORE FAC REJECT CODQV
)@@G@@E     @D@@@@          J         QF440             PRINT ERROR CODE@[@@@@QW
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. ERROR DOING MSCON$ DREAD$   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@QF420     LXQX
)@@G@@,U      X10,('MSCON ERR: &') . GET MSG ADDR     @C@@@@          J       QY
)@@G@@  QF440             PRINT IT  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ERROR TRYING TO DO A 'QZ
)@@G@@@USE USE$,Q*F(C). ' ??? @[@@@@.     @D@@@@QF430     LX,U      X10,('USE:RA
)@@G@@ &')    GET MSG ADDR    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. PRINT CORRECT ERROR MSG     RB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@QF440     SA        A0,ECODE+1        HANG ON TO ERRORRC
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK            OPEN EDIT @C@@@@          E$RD
)@@G@@MSG     0,X10             EDIT MSG  @D@@@@          E$OCTF    12,ECODE+1RE
)@@G@@        EDIT ERROR CODE @D@@@@QF450     P$RINT    POUT              PRINRF
)@@G@@T ERROR MSG @E@@@@          J         QF900             TRY AGAIN VIA RERG
)@@G@@AD$   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF RUN IS PRIVILEGED AND QFK OPTIONS ARE SET, RH
)@@G@@PRINT KEYS ONLY   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@QF500     TZ        KPT             RI
)@@G@@  K-OPTION SET?   @E@@@@          TNZ       PRIVLGD           AND RUN PRRJ
)@@G@@IVILEGED?   @E@@@@          J         MFD100            NO, DO NORMAL STRK
)@@G@@UFF   @D@@@@          E$DIT     EDPACK            YES, OPEN EDIT  @C@@@@RL
)@@G@@          E$FD2     QUAL              QUALIFIER @^@@@@          E$CHAR  RM
)@@G@@  '*' @C@@@@          E$FD2     FILE              FILENAME  @^@@@@      RN
)@@G@@    E$CHAR    '(' @C@@@@          E$DECV    FCYCLE            F-CYCLE   RO
)@@G@@@^@@@@          E$CHAR    ')' @^@@@@          E$CHAR    '/' @C@@@@      RP
)@@G@@    E$COPY    6,RDKEY           READ KEY  @^@@@@          E$CHAR    '/' RQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$COPY    6,WRKEY           WRITE KEY @C@@@@          J RR
)@@G@@        QF450             PRINT IT  @B@@@@/         ON        (CHKPCT>0)RS
)@@G@@**(LDJOK=0) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS SUBROUTINE IS FOR USE WHEN LDJ OF PRT
)@@G@@CT BANK IS NOT DESIRED  @F@@@@. (LDJOK EQU 0).  IT CONVERTS THE RELATVIERU
)@@G@@ PCT BUFFER ADDRESS     @G@@@@. INTO AN ADDRESS USABLE BY  ER PCT$, AND RV
)@@G@@LOADS THE PROPER PCT BLOCK.   @G@@@@. UPON EXIT, A0 CONTAINS THE ADDRESSRW
)@@G@@ WITHIN PCTBUF CORRESPONDING TO     @A@@@@. THE DESIRED PCT RELATIVE ADDRX
)@@G@@RESS. @[@@@@.     @H@@@@PCTLNK    TG,U      A0,PCTBUF+01000   ADDR IN CURY
)@@G@@RRENTLY-LOADED PCT BLOCK?     @B@@@@          J         NOTCUR          RZ
)@@G@@  NO  @E@@@@          L         A1,A0             YES, GET ADDR IN A1   SA
)@@G@@@H@@@@          AN        A1,X4             SUBTRACT REL PCTBUF ADDR, LESB
)@@G@@AVING LINK  @F@@@@          A         A1,PCTNAM         ADD CURRENT ITEMSC
)@@G@@ BASE ADDR  @E@@@@          S         A1,PCTNAM         STORE NEW BASE ASD
)@@G@@DDR   @H@@@@          J         0,A3              RETURN WITH A0=REL ADDSE
)@@G@@R WITHIN PCTBUF   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. DESIRED BLOCK NOT IN PCTBUF @[@@@@SF
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@NOTCUR    AN        A0,X4             SUBTRACT REL PCTBUF ADSG
)@@G@@DR, LEAVING LINK  @E@@@@          A,H2      A0,PCTNAM         ADD CURRENSH
)@@G@@T ITEM BASE @D@@@@          S,H2      A0,PCTNAM         STORE NEW BASE  SI
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AND,U     A0,0777000        ISOLATE BLOCK NUMBER  @D@@@@SJ
)@@G@@          A,U       A1,01000          ADJUST FOR PCT$ @D@@@@          LXSK
)@@G@@I,U     A1,01000          GET 1 PCT BLOCK @D@@@@          S         A0,ASL
)@@G@@2             SAVE REL ADDR   @E@@@@          L,U       A0,PCTBUF       SM
)@@G@@  GET ADDR OF PCT BUFFER@D@@@@          ER        PCT$              GET SN
)@@G@@PCT BLOCK   @D@@@@          L         A0,A2             RETRIEVE ADDR   SO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AND,U     A0,0777           MASK OUT BLOCK INFO   @F@@@@SP
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,PCTBUF,A1      FORM REL ADDR INTO PCTBUF   @C@@@@SQ
)@@G@@          J         0,A3              RETURN    @B@@@@          OFF     SR
)@@G@@  (CHKPCT>0)**(LDJOK=0) @F@@@@/. CSF$ CONTINGENCY ROUTINE FOR BAD FILENASS
)@@G@@ME INPUT VIA READ$.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@QF700     +         0D  @F@@@@ST
)@@G@@          LA,T1     A0,QF700          GET ERROR TYPE AND CODE     @F@@@@SU
)@@G@@          TE,U      A0,0440           SYNTAX ERROR ON CSF$ CALL?  @F@@@@SV
)@@G@@          J         QF710             NO, CHECK SOME MORE THINGS  @D@@@@SW
)@@G@@          P$RINT    (PRT 1,4,ERR4)    PRINT ERROR MSG @F@@@@          J SX
)@@G@@        QF900             AND TRY ANOTHER DATA CARD   @E@@@@QF710     TESY
)@@G@@,U      A0,0401           ER INDEX OUT OF RANGE?@E@@@@          TNE,U   SZ
)@@G@@  A0,0403              OR NOT IN USE?     @G@@@@          J         $+2 TA
)@@G@@              YES, MAY BE ATTEMPT AT ER ERRPR$  @F@@@@          ER      TB
)@@G@@  EABT$             NO, BETTER LUCK NEXT TIME   @E@@@@          LA,H2   TC
)@@G@@  A0,QF700          GET ERROR ADDRESS     @E@@@@          TE,U      A0,QTD
)@@G@@F415          ER ERRPR$ ROUTINE?    @E@@@@          ER        EABT$     TE
)@@G@@        NO, SOMEBODY GOOFED   @E@@@@          J         QF416           TF
)@@G@@  YES, DO IT THE OLD WAY@B@@@@. USE READ$ TO GET ANOTHER FILE TO DO     TG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@QF900*    SR        R15,SFMODE        RESET SINGLE-FILTH
)@@G@@E MODE INDICATOR  @D@@@@          LA        A0,(MFD700,RBUFF) GET READ$ TI
)@@G@@PACKET@D@@@@          ER        READ$             READ A CARD     @C@@@@TJ
)@@G@@          J         QF920             GO AHEAD  @D@@@@QF910     LA      TK
)@@G@@  A0,('TPF$  ')     NO, ASSUME TPF$ @D@@@@          SA        A0,RBUFF  TL
)@@G@@        PUT IT IN IMAGE @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,1              FUDGTM
)@@G@@E FOR 1 WORD READ @G@@@@QF920     LA,U      A1,' . '          GET SET TOTN
)@@G@@ TERMINATE THE IMAGE    @G@@@@          TZ,U      0,A0              SKIPTO
)@@G@@ IF REPEATING PREVIOUS FILE   @G@@@@          SA,H1     A1,RBUFF,A0     TP
)@@G@@  TERMINATE WITH SPACE-PERIOD-SPACE @D@@@@          J         QF020     TQ
)@@G@@        DO THE @USE     @#@@@@          END     ___     A0,X4           TR
)@@G@@  SUBTRACT REL PCTBUF ADDR, LEAVING LINK  @E@@@@          A,H2      A0,PTS
)@@G@@CTNAM         ADD CURRENT ITEM BASE @D@@@@      *[S@@@*SDFF*@ @@@@. @MFDTT
)@@G@@ SORT INTERFACE ROUTINES@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. M.I. SEC 0 WORDSTU
)@@G@@ 18-19, WHICH CONTAIN THE DATE/TIME OF LAST REFERENCE @G@@@@. AND OF CATTV
)@@G@@ALOGUING, ARE MODIFIED SO THAT THEY ARE MORE EASILY SORTED. @[@@@@.     TW
)@@G@@@H@@@@.     ------------------------------------------------------------TX
)@@G@@-------     @H@@@@.     :   YEAR   :   MON    :   DAY    :              TY
)@@G@@TIME              :     @H@@@@.     ------------------------------------TZ
)@@G@@-------------------------------     @B@@@@.     :                       UA
)@@G@@         :  @B@@@@.     :<--  THIS PORTION IS SORTED  -->:  @[@@@@.     UB
)@@G@@@G@@@@. TWO EXTRA WORDS ARE SORTED ALONG WITH LI0/MI0/MI1, TO SAVE FLAGSUC
)@@G@@, ETC.@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     ------------------------------------------UD
)@@G@@-------------------------     @H@@@@.     :          :   BAK    :  RDISCUE
)@@G@@   :       TOTAL SIZE               :     @H@@@@.     ------------------UF
)@@G@@-------------------------------------------------     @H@@@@.     :     UG
)@@G@@                        FLAGS                               :     @H@@@@UH
)@@G@@.     ------------------------------------------------------------------UI
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. 'BAK' IS BACKED-UP FLAG IN A13, AND 'RDISC'   UJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. IS REMOVABLE-DISC FLAG IN A14.  TOTAL SIZE IS NUMBER ACCUMULATEDUK
)@@G@@@ @@@@. IN A15 BY 'CHECK' ROUTINE.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          AXR$    UL
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@          CONFIG    .                 DEFINE CONFIGURATION PUM
)@@G@@ARAMETERS   @D@@@@          EQUFS     .                 DEFINE TAGS     UN
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        SORTOK    @E@@@@NREC      +         NFILES/2  UO
)@@G@@        NUMBER OF RECORDS     @E@@@@NCHAR     +         RECCHAR         UP
)@@G@@  CHARACTERS PER RECORD @[@@@@.     @B@@@@$(1). CALL SORTF TO ASSIGN SORUQ
)@@G@@T FILES     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@OPNSRT*   SR        R15,SORTED        MARKUR
)@@G@@ SORT-SEG-LOADED  @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,NFILES         GET NUMBERUS
)@@G@@ OF FILES   @G@@@@          TZ        ZPT               PRIVILEGED AND DUT
)@@G@@OING EVERYTHING?  @F@@@@          SA        A0,NREC           YES, BETTEUU
)@@G@@R INCREASE NREC   @D@@@@          DO        SRTDBG , P$RINT (0101,('SORTUV
)@@G@@F ')) @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,SORTF         ASSIGN SORT FILES     UW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          +         NREC              NUMBER OF RECORDS     @F@@@@UX
)@@G@@          +         NCHAR             NUMBER OF CHAR PER RECORD   @B@@@@UY
)@@G@@          +         0                 WB  @F@@@@NOSORTF*  R$OPN     SORTUZ
)@@G@@BL            OPEN SORT, RETURN TO FPOC   @F@@@@. DON'T NEED PARAMETER CVA
)@@G@@ARD PROCESSING, SO REPLACE KPARCD WITH:   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ROPN$*    LMVB
)@@G@@J       X1,RSTRG$ @#@@@@          'ROPN$ '@ @@@@          J         RBPNVC
)@@G@@$     @]@@@@RTMIN$*   . @]@@@@RTMAX$*   . @]@@@@RTPT$*    . @]@@@@RTST$*VD
)@@G@@    . @]@@@@RTMT$*    . @]@@@@RLBLK$*   . @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. RELEASE REVE
)@@G@@CORD TO SORT@[@@@@.     @]@@@@GOTREC*   . @G@@@@          SA        BACKVF
)@@G@@EDUP,SAVEBAK  SAVE RDISC AND BACKED-UP FLAGS    @A@@@@          SA      VG
)@@G@@  RDISC,SAVERDISC @D@@@@          DO        SRTDBG , P$RINT (0101,('RRELVH
)@@G@@$ ')) @E@@@@          L,U       A0,RECSTART       PASS THIS FILE TO SORTVI
)@@G@@@^@@@@          R$REL     .   @G@@@@          J         CHK000          VJ
)@@G@@  GET NEXT FILE (SEG IS LOADED)     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. DIRSEC EOF HAS OVK
)@@G@@CCURRED; DO THE SORT    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DOSORT*   . @D@@@@          DOVL
)@@G@@        SRTDBG , P$RINT (0101,('RSORT$')) @F@@@@          R$SORT    .   VM
)@@G@@              DO THE SORT, RETURN TO LPOC @]@@@@LPOC*     . @D@@@@      VN
)@@G@@    DO        SRTDBG , P$RINT (0101,('LPOC  ')) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GET VO
)@@G@@NEXT RECORD FROM SORT, AND JUMP TO PRINT ROUTINE WITH IT    @[@@@@.     VP
)@@G@@@]@@@@SRTNXT*   . @D@@@@          DO        SRTDBG , P$RINT (0101,('RRETVQ
)@@G@@$ ')) @H@@@@          R$RET     SRTEOF          . GET NEXT RECORD - IF EVR
)@@G@@OF, GO TO SRTEOF  @F@@@@          LX,U      X8,,A0            POINT TO LVS
)@@G@@I0/MI0/MI1 ETC.   @F@@@@          LA        BACKEDUP,SAVEBAK  RETRIEVE RVT
)@@G@@DISC, BAK FLAGS   @A@@@@          LA        RDISC,SAVERDISC @D@@@@      VU
)@@G@@    LA        FILESIZE,SAVESIZE RETRIEVE SIZE   @H@@@@          J       VV
)@@G@@  PR000             JUMP TO PRINT ROUTINE (SEG IS LOADED)   @[@@@@.     VW
)@@G@@@A@@@@. EOF STATUS RECEIVED FROM SORT     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SRTEOF    TNVX
)@@G@@Z       SFMODE2           SINGLE-FILE MODE?     @E@@@@          J       VY
)@@G@@  MFD600            NO, RETURN TO MAIN SEG@F@@@@          J         QF90VZ
)@@G@@0             YES, RETURN FOR ANOTHER FILE@ @@@@          OFF       SORTWA
)@@G@@OK    @#@@@@          END     ___ERS PER RECORD @[@@@@.     @B@@@@$(1). WB
)@@G@@CALL SORTF TO ASSIGN SOR*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@          AXR$      .   @[@@@@WC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         SORTF - FORTRAN CALLABLE ROUTINE TO ASSIGN SORT FIWD
)@@G@@LES   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ORIGINALLY BY WALT GILBERT (UOM)@D@@@@WE
)@@G@@.         UPDATED BY R. DUFF KURLAND (ISD) TO PROVIDE:@[@@@@.     @B@@@@WF
)@@G@@.           - EXEC LEVEL 33 COMPATABILITY @C@@@@.           - REMOVABLE WG
)@@G@@DISC USAGE FOR XB FILE  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IF AN 'XB' FILE IS NWH
)@@G@@EEDED, IT WILL BE ASSIGNED ON TYPE <FIXTYPE>,   @G@@@@.         UNLESS TWI
)@@G@@HE MAXIMUM DRUM FILE SIZE (XBMAXF) IS EXCEEDED, OR THE@H@@@@.         REWJ
)@@G@@QUIRED NUMBER OF POSITIONS EXCEEDS THE AMOUNT CURRENTLY AVAILABLE.@G@@@@WK
)@@G@@.         IN THIS CASE, 'XB' WILL BE ASSIGNED ON A REMOVABLE DISC, USINGWL
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         EQUIPMENT TYPE <REMTYPE>, AND PACKID <REMPACK>.  IF NO RWM
)@@G@@EMOVABLE    @G@@@@.         DISC ASSIGNS ARE DESIRED, <REMTYPE> SHOULD BWN
)@@G@@E SET TO ZERO.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IF A REMOVABLE ASSIGN OF 'WO
)@@G@@XB' IS ATTEMPTED AND FAILS (DUE TO THE    @G@@@@.         DRIVE NOT BEINWP
)@@G@@G AVAILABLE, ETC.), SORTF WILL REVERT TO A FIXED@H@@@@.         ASSIGN, WQ
)@@G@@BUT WITHOUT THE INITIAL RESERVE.  FURTHERMORE, IF THE FILE  @H@@@@.     WR
)@@G@@    IS LESS THAN <XBREVP> POSITIONS, TRACK GRANULARITY WILL BE USED.    WS
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THIS IS ALL TO MINIMIZE THE SYSTEM IMPACT OF A SORT WHENWT
)@@G@@ MASS @B@@@@.         STORAGE AVAILABILITY IS LOW.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@WU
)@@G@@REMTYPE   EQU       0                 TYPE FOR REMOVABLE XB ASGS  @E@@@@WV
)@@G@@.                                     MUST BE 3 CHARS, RJSF @G@@@@FIXTYPWW
)@@G@@E   EQU       'F40'             TYPE TO USE FOR FIXED XB ASGS     @D@@@@WX
)@@G@@.                                     (3 CHARS, RJSF) @H@@@@REMPACK   EQWY
)@@G@@U       'TEMP00'          PACKID FOR REMOVABLE XB ASGS (LJSF)     @F@@@@WZ
)@@G@@.                                     IGNORED IF REMTYPE = 0.     @H@@@@XA
)@@G@@XBMAXF    EQU       0                 MAX SIZE OF FIXED XB FILE (POSITIOXB
)@@G@@NS)   @F@@@@.                                     IGNORED IF REMTYPE = 0XC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@XBMAX     EQU       150               MAX XB SIZE, ANY ASG TXD
)@@G@@YPE   @F@@@@.                                     (ONLY TO PREVENT ABUSEXE
)@@G@@)     @F@@@@MSIZE     EQU       300               MSALL$ FATBL BUFFER SIXF
)@@G@@ZE    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@RTYPE     EQU       ('.,'*/24)+(REMTYPE*/6)+'/' XG
)@@G@@@C@@@@FTYPE     EQU       ('.,'*/24)+(FIXTYPE*/6)+'/' @[@@@@.     @A@@@@XH
)@@G@@.         ALL FILES ARE FREED FIRST @[@@@@.     @^@@@@FREXA     '@FREE XXI
)@@G@@A    '@^@@@@FREXB     '@FREE XB    '@^@@@@FRECOR    '@FREE R$CORE'@[@@@@XJ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.         XA FILE ASSIGN IMAGE@[@@@@.     @A@@@@ASGXA     '@XK
)@@G@@ASG,T    XA.,F///******'@ @@@@ASGXAL    EQU       $-ASGXA   @[@@@@.     XL
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         XB FILE ASSIGN IMAGES     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@XM
)@@G@@.         NORMAL (FIXED) XB ASSIGN, EXTENDED FOR REMOVABLE ASSIGN IF    XN
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         CONFIGURED AND NECESSARY. @[@@@@.     @B@@@@ASGXB     '@XO
)@@G@@ASG,T    XB.,FXX/***/POS/*** '@G@@@@ASGXBL    EQU       $-ASGXB         XP
)@@G@@  LENGTH OF NORMAL XB ASSIGN IMAGE  @ @@@@          ON        REMTYPE   XQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@XBPACK    +         REMPACK           PACKID TAGGED ONTO END OF XBXR
)@@G@@ ASG IMAGE  @G@@@@DISC      +         0                 NONZERO IF REMOVXS
)@@G@@ABLE ASG NEEDED   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         REMOTE EXECUTE TABLE TO STXT
)@@G@@UFF COMMA AFTER MAX GRANS     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@COMMA     S,S2      A0,AXU
)@@G@@SGXB+4        FOR MAX = INITIAL = 1 DIGIT @F@@@@          S,S4      A0,AXV
)@@G@@SGXB+4        FOR MAX = INITIAL = 2 DIGITS@F@@@@          S,S6      A0,AXW
)@@G@@SGXB+4        FOR MAX = INITIAL = 3 DIGITS@[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         XBXX
)@@G@@ ASSIGN IMAGE USED WHEN REMOVABLE ASSIGN FAILS. @[@@@@.     @B@@@@ASGXB2XY
)@@G@@    '@ASG,T    XB.,FXX//POS/ ******'@ @@@@ASGXB2L   EQU       $-ASGXB2  XZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@XBREVP    EQU       10                POINT AT WHICH TYA
)@@G@@O STOP SWITCHING  @E@@@@.                                     TO TRACK GYB
)@@G@@RANULARITY  @ @@@@          OFF       REMTYPE   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.     YC
)@@G@@    R$CORE ASSIGN IMAGE @[@@@@.     @A@@@@ASGCOR    '@ASG,T R$CORE.,F2//YD
)@@G@@/**  '@ @@@@ASGCORL   EQU       $-ASGCOR  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         MSYE
)@@G@@ALL$ PACKET @[@@@@.     @G@@@@MSPKT     +         1,MSALL$          LEVEYF
)@@G@@L-33 FORMAT MSCON$/MSALL$ CALL@E@@@@          +         MSIZE,MSBUF     YG
)@@G@@  BUFFER LENGTH, ADDRESS@D@@@@          +         0                 FILLYH
)@@G@@ED BY MSCON$@D@@@@          +         0                 FILLED BY MSCON$YI
)@@G@@@D@@@@          +         0                 FILLED BY MSCON$@[@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@MSBEG     EQUF      MSPKT+3,,H1       STARTING MS DEVICE INDEX    YK
)@@G@@@E@@@@MSEND     EQUF      MSPKT+3,,H2       LAST MS DEVICE INDEX  @F@@@@YL
)@@G@@DSCBEG    EQUF      MSPKT+4,,H1       STARTING DISC DEVICE INDEX  @E@@@@YM
)@@G@@DSCEND    EQUF      MSPKT+4,,H2       LAST DISC DEVICE INDEX@[@@@@.     YN
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         MSALL$ FATBL BUFFER @[@@@@.     @F@@@@MSBUF     RES     YO
)@@G@@  MSIZE             RESERVE SPACE FOR FATBL     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SAV   YP
)@@G@@    RES       1                 SAVE AREA FOR A10     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@YQ
)@@G@@E(1)      'RECORD SIZE NEGATIVE OR ZERO'. @C@@@@E(2)      'NUMBER OF RECYR
)@@G@@ORDS NEGATIVE OR ZERO'. @D@@@@E(3)      'XXXXXX POSITIONS IS TOO LARGE FYS
)@@G@@OR SORTF'.  @E@@@@E(4)      'SORT FILE ASSIGN REJECTED:    XXXXXXXXXXXX'YT
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@E(5)      ' ONLY XXXXXX TRACKS OF STORAGE  REMAIN,   SORT NEYU
)@@G@@EDS  XXXXXX'@E@@@@E(6)      ' ONLY XXXXXX POSITIONS REMAIN, SORT NEEDS XYV
)@@G@@XXXXX'@D@@@@E(7)      'SORTF ERROR - MSALL$ BUFFER IS TOO SMALL.' @B@@@@YW
)@@G@@E(8)      'SORTF MSCON$ ERROR CODE XX'    @]@@@@E(9)      . @^@@@@I     YX
)@@G@@    DO        8 ,;@F@@@@EE(I)     + 0200+E(I+1)-E(I),E(I).    GENERATE PYY
)@@G@@RINT CONTROL WORDS@F@@@@XA        +         0                 XA (SMALL)YZ
)@@G@@ FILE SIZE, TRK   @F@@@@XB        +         0                 XB (LARGE)ZA
)@@G@@ FILE SIZE, POS   @G@@@@CORE      +         0                 CORE SIZE,ZB
)@@G@@ THOUSANDS OF WORDS     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         MERGE POWER LLOKUP TZC
)@@G@@ABLE  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@MGPS      +         2                 4   @B@@@@ZD
)@@G@@          +         5                 5   @B@@@@          +         9   ZE
)@@G@@              6   @B@@@@          +         17                7   @B@@@@ZF
)@@G@@          +         26                8   @B@@@@          +         37  ZG
)@@G@@              9   @B@@@@          +         53                10  @B@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          +         72                11  @B@@@@          +         94  ZI
)@@G@@              12  @B@@@@          +         121               13  @B@@@@ZJ
)@@G@@          +         153               14  @B@@@@          +         190 ZK
)@@G@@              15  @B@@@@          +         232               16  @B@@@@ZL
)@@G@@          +         280               17  @B@@@@          +         335 ZM
)@@G@@              18  @B@@@@          +         395               19  @B@@@@ZN
)@@G@@          +         460               20  @B@@@@          +         530 ZO
)@@G@@              21  @F@@@@NMGPS     EQU       $-MGPS.           NUMBER OF ZP
)@@G@@ENTRIES IN TABLE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@RETURN    +         0               ZQ
)@@G@@  RETURN ADDRESS STORE HERE   @[@@@@/$(1).@]@@@@SORTF*    . @ @@@@      ZR
)@@G@@    S         A10,SAV   @G@@@@          L,U       A1,'WJG'          LOADZS
)@@G@@ @SORTF CALL IDENTITY FLAG    @H@@@@          SZ        A4              ZT
)@@G@@  SET FLAG. 0=SUBROUTINE CALL, _0=@SORTF  @G@@@@          TNE,H2    A1,2ZU
)@@G@@,X11          IS THIS SORTF-DRIVER CALLING?     @H@@@@          L       ZV
)@@G@@  A4,2,X11          YES, LOAD ENTIRE WORD TO GET SIGN FLAG  @H@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@    JN        A4,NOCSF          DON'T ISSUE CSF$'S IF 'X' OPTION ON     ZX
)@@G@@@H@@@@          L         A0,(2,FREXA)      FREE ALL OF THE FILES: XA, XZY
)@@G@@B, R$CORE   @^@@@@          ER        CSF$@A@@@@          L         A0,(ZZ
)@@G@@2,FREXB)    @^@@@@          ER        CSF$@A@@@@          L         A0,(AA
)@@G@@2,FRECOR)   @^@@@@          ER        CSF$@E@@@@NOCSF     L,U       A0,3AB
)@@G@@,X11          GET RETURN ADDRESS    @C@@@@          S,H2      A0,RETURN AC
)@@G@@        SAVE IT.  @F@@@@          L         A1,*1,X11         LOAD RECORAD
)@@G@@D SIZE IN CHARS   @E@@@@          JN        A1,ERR2           ERROR IF NAE
)@@G@@EGATIVE     @ @@@@          A,U       A1,11 .   @^@@@@          SZ      AF
)@@G@@  A0  @E@@@@          DI,U      A0,6              CONVERT TO WORD COUNT AG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          MSI       A0,*0,X11         TIMES NUMBER OF RECORDS     AH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JN        A0,ERR1           ERROR IF NEGATIVE     @E@@@@AI
)@@G@@          MI,U      A0,11             ADD 10% SAFETY FACTOR @ @@@@      AJ
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,10     @ @@@@          DSL       A0,36     @D@@@@      AK
)@@G@@    S         A1,A2             SAVE VALUE.     @E@@@@          DI,U    AL
)@@G@@  A0,114688         GET FILE SIZE IN POS  @F@@@@          JZ        A0,SAM
)@@G@@MALL          JUMP IF LESS THAN 1 POSITION@D@@@@          A,U       A0,1AN
)@@G@@              ROUND UPWARD    @F@@@@          S         A0,XB           AO
)@@G@@  STORE XB SIZE, POSITIONS    @E@@@@          TG,U      A0,XBMAX+1      AP
)@@G@@  MAX XB SIZE EXCEEDED? @E@@@@          J         ERR3              YES,AQ
)@@G@@ PRINT ERROR MSG  @F@@@@          L,U       R1,NMGPS          SEARCH MERAR
)@@G@@GE-POWER TABLE    @ @@@@          L         A2,(1,3)  @H@@@@          SGAS
)@@G@@,H2     A0,MGPS-3,*A2     LOOKUP XB SIZE IN MERGE-POWER TABLE     @D@@@@AT
)@@G@@          J         ERR3              MUCH TOO BIG!   @G@@@@          L,AU
)@@G@@U       A1,0,A2           RESULT, MGP (MERGE-POWER) IN A2   @H@@@@      AV
)@@G@@    MSI,U     A1,1792           FIND AMOUNT OF CORE USING 1792-WD BUFFERAW
)@@G@@@G@@@@          A,U       A1,2791           2791=1792+999 = 1TRK + ROUNDAX
)@@G@@ING   @^@@@@          SZ        A0  @ @@@@          DI,U      A0,1000   AY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          S         A0,CORE           CORE REQUIRED IN THOUSANDS. AZ
)@@G@@@H@@@@          MI,U      A0,15000          15 (1.5) IS DEFAULT BIAS, 10BA
)@@G@@00 TO GET WD@H@@@@          AN,U      A1,80640          CALC. EXPECTED SBB
)@@G@@TRING SIZE,  3*15*1792  @H@@@@          DI,U      A0,19712          11*1BC
)@@G@@792 TO GET TRKS, 11 = 10 ALMOST     @C@@@@          S         A0,A3     BD
)@@G@@        SAVE VALUE@E@@@@          L         A0,XB             NOW CALCULBE
)@@G@@ATE XA SIZE @E@@@@          DSL       A0,30             (CONV POS TO TRKBF
)@@G@@)     @H@@@@          DI,U      A0,0,A2           XA = XB/(MGP)+1 ROUNDEBG
)@@G@@D UP TO STRING SIZ@H@@@@          AU        A0,A3             NOW ROUND BH
)@@G@@UP TO WHOLE EXPECTED ST. SIZE.@^@@@@          SZ        A0  @ @@@@      BI
)@@G@@    DI        A0,A3     @ @@@@          MSI       A0,A3     @E@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@    S         A0,XA             STORE XA SIZE, TRKS   @ @@@@          ONBK
)@@G@@        REMTYPE   @F@@@@          L         A0,XB             LOAD XB SIBL
)@@G@@ZE, IN POSITIONS  @F@@@@          TLE,U     A0,XBMAXF+1       MAX FIXED BM
)@@G@@POS EXCEEDED?     @F@@@@          J         MAVCHK            NO, CHECK BN
)@@G@@MS AVAILABILITY   @F@@@@DISCON    L,U       A0,1              YES, SET RBO
)@@G@@EMOVABLE ASG FLAG @ @@@@          S         A0,DISC   @G@@@@          J BP
)@@G@@        CHEKD             TRY ASSIGNING XB ON REMOBAVLE PACK@ @@@@      BQ
)@@G@@    OFF       REMTYPE   @C@@@@MAVCHK    L,U       A0,MSPKT          GET BR
)@@G@@FATBL @ @@@@          ER        MSCON$    @F@@@@          JN        A0,EBS
)@@G@@RR7           IF NO GOOD, HANDLE ERROR    @F@@@@          SZ        A10 BT
)@@G@@              CLEAR TOTAL TRACKS AVAILABLE@G@@@@          SZ        A1  BU
)@@G@@              CLEAR TOTAL POSITIONS AVAILLABLE  @F@@@@          L       BV
)@@G@@  A2,MSEND          GET LAST MS DEVICE INDEX    @E@@@@          AN      BW
)@@G@@  A2,MSBEG          GET # OF MS TYPES - 1 @D@@@@          TNZ       MSBEBX
)@@G@@G             NEW-TYPE FATBL? @F@@@@          L,U       A2,7            BY
)@@G@@  NO, GET OLD LENGTH OF FATBL @F@@@@FATLOOP   L,H1      A0,MSBUF,A2     BZ
)@@G@@  GET INDEX TO STATUS TABLE   @D@@@@          TNZ       MSBEG           CA
)@@G@@  NEW-TYPE FATBL? @F@@@@          JZ        A0,FATEND         NO, IF ZERCB
)@@G@@O, NONE CONFIGURED@F@@@@          A,H2      A1,MSBUF+2,A0     BUMP AVAILCC
)@@G@@ABLE POSITIONS    @E@@@@          L         A0,MSBUF+1,A0     GET POSITICD
)@@G@@ONS AVAIL   @F@@@@          LSSL      A0,12             GET RID OF  ROT CE
)@@G@@POINTER     @ @@@@          SSL       A0,12     @E@@@@          A       CF
)@@G@@  A10,A0            BUMP AVAILABLE TRACKS @E@@@@FATEND    JGD       A2,FCG
)@@G@@ATLOOP        HANDLE ALL MS DEVICES @G@@@@          TLE       A1,XB     CH
)@@G@@        ENOUGH POSITIONS FOR THE XB FILE? @E@@@@          DO REMTYPE=0 ,CI
)@@G@@ J ERR6       NO, PRINT ERROR MSG   @F@@@@          DO REMTYPE>0 , J DISCJ
)@@G@@CON     NO, SWITCH TO REMOVABLE ASG @F@@@@          L         A1,XB     CK
)@@G@@        GET POSITIONS NEEDED FOR XB @E@@@@          LSSL      A1,6      CL
)@@G@@        CONVERT TO TRACKS     @F@@@@          A         A1,XA           CM
)@@G@@  ADD TRACKS REQUIRED FOR XA  @B@@@@          A,U       A1,1248         CN
)@@G@@  ??? @F@@@@          TLE       A10,A1            ARE ENOUGH TRACKS AVAICO
)@@G@@LABLE?@E@@@@          J         ERR5              NO, PRINT ERROR MSG   CP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         ASSIGN THE XB FILE  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@CHEKD CQ
)@@G@@    L         A0,XB     @F@@@@          JZ        A0,CVXA           SKIPCR
)@@G@@ IF NO XB FILE NEEDED   @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,CV            CONVCS
)@@G@@ERT TO FIELDATA DECIMAL @^@@@@          SZ        A0  @ @@@@          L CT
)@@G@@        A1,A2     @E@@@@          LDSL      A0,0,A3           MOVE INIT CU
)@@G@@RESV TO A0  @A@@@@          L         A1,('/POS/ ')   @G@@@@          DSCV
)@@G@@L       A0,6              MOVE LAST CHAR OF INIT RESV TO A1 @G@@@@      CW
)@@G@@    AN,U      A3,6              DECREMENT SHIFT COUNT BY 1 CHAR   @F@@@@CX
)@@G@@          DSL       A1,0,A3           SHIFT X/POS/ AND MAX GRAN   @H@@@@CY
)@@G@@          SSC       A0,0,A3           ADJUST REMAINING CHARS OF INIT RESCZ
)@@G@@V     @G@@@@          A         A1,A0             ADD REMAINING INIT RESDA
)@@G@@V CHARS     @G@@@@          DS        A1,ASGXB+3        STORE XXX/POS/XXDB
)@@G@@X IN ASG IMAGE    @F@@@@          LA        A0,(FTYPE)        GET FIXED DC
)@@G@@XB EQUIP TYPE     @E@@@@          SA        A0,ASGXB+2        STORE IN ADD
)@@G@@SG IMAGE    @E@@@@          L         A1,(ASGXBL,ASGXB) GET IMAGE LENGTHDE
)@@G@@, ADDR@ @@@@          ON        REMTYPE   @F@@@@          TNZ       DISCDF
)@@G@@              AH!  SHOULD WE DO REM ASG?  @E@@@@          J         DOITDG
)@@G@@              NO, ASSIGN AS FIXED   @F@@@@          L         A2,(RTYPE)DH
)@@G@@        GET DESIRED REM EQUIP TYPE  @E@@@@          S         A2,ASGXB+2DI
)@@G@@        STORE IN ASG IMAGE    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         ADD A COMMA FODJ
)@@G@@R PACKID CLAUSE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          SZ        A2              DK
)@@G@@  A3=INIT RESV BIT COUNT - 6  @E@@@@          DI,U      A2,6            DL
)@@G@@  CONVERT TO CHAR COUNT @D@@@@          L,U       A0,','            GET DM
)@@G@@A COMMA     @F@@@@          EX        COMMA,A2          STORE COMMA IN ADN
)@@G@@SG IMAGE    @G@@@@          LNA       A1,(ASGXBL+1,ASGXB) . INDICATE WE DO
)@@G@@CHECK THE STATUS  @ @@@@          OFF       REMTYPE   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@DP
)@@G@@DOIT      LMJ       A3,ISSUE          ASSIGN THE XB FILE    @ @@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    ON        REMTYPE   @D@@@@          JP        A0,CVXA           IF ODR
)@@G@@K, GO ASG XA@E@@@@          TNZ       DISC              WAS THIS A DISC DS
)@@G@@ASG?  @F@@@@          J         ISSUE3            NO, PRINT ERROR MSG ANDT
)@@G@@D EXIT@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         MAYBE PACK CAN'T BE MOUNTED.  REVERT TDU
)@@G@@O FIXED ASSIGN,   @E@@@@.         WITHOUT INITIAL RESERVE.  IF FILE IS SDV
)@@G@@MALL ENOUGH @F@@@@.         (LESS THAN <XBREVP> POSITIONS) USE TRACK GRADW
)@@G@@NULARITY.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          JZ        A4,SKIPIT         IF NDX
)@@G@@OT SORTF-DRIVER, SKIP MSG     @D@@@@          LMJ       A3,ERR4         DY
)@@G@@  FORM ERROR MSG  @C@@@@          P$RINT    EE(4)             PRINT MSG DZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@SKIPIT    SZ        DISC              CLEAR REMOVABLE-ASG FLAG    EA
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LA        A0,(FTYPE)        GET CONFIGURED FIXED EQUIPMEEB
)@@G@@NT TYPE     @E@@@@          SA        A0,ASGXB2+2       SET IN ASSIGN IMEC
)@@G@@AGE   @F@@@@          LA        A0,XB             GET XB SIZE IN POSITIOED
)@@G@@NS    @H@@@@          TG,U      A0,XBREVP+1       WILL WE ZONK THE GUY'SEE
)@@G@@ PCT WITH GRANULE @H@@@@.                                     ITEMS IF WEF
)@@G@@E USED TRACK GRANULARITY?     @H@@@@          J         XBPOS           EG
)@@G@@  YES, SO REMAIN IN POSITION GRANULARITY  @F@@@@          LA        A1,(EH
)@@G@@'/TRK/ ')     YES, SO CHANGE ASSIGN IMAGE @E@@@@          SA        A1,AEI
)@@G@@SGXB2+3       TO TRACK GRANULARITY  @G@@@@          LSSL      A0,6      EJ
)@@G@@        AND CONVERT POSITIONS TO TRACKS   @G@@@@XBPOS     LMJ       X11,EK
)@@G@@CV            CONVERT SIZE TO FIELDATA DECIMAL  @F@@@@          SA      EL
)@@G@@  A2,ASGXB2+4       AND STORE IN ASSIGN IMAGE   @B@@@@          LA      EM
)@@G@@  A1,(ASGXB2L,ASGXB2)   @H@@@@          LMJ       A3,ISSUE          ASSIEN
)@@G@@GN THE XB FILE ON FIXED STORAGE     @ @@@@          OFF       REMTYPE   EO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         ASSIGN XA FILE@[@@@@.     @ @@@@CVXA      L EP
)@@G@@        A0,XA     @H@@@@          LMJ       X11,CV            CONVERT XAEQ
)@@G@@ SIZE TO FIELDATA DECIMAL     @F@@@@          S         A2,ASGXA+3      ER
)@@G@@  STORE MAX GRAN IN ASG IMAGE @F@@@@          L         A1,(ASGXAL,ASGXAES
)@@G@@) GET IMAGE LENGTH AND ADDRESS@G@@@@          LMJ       A3,ISSUE        ET
)@@G@@  DISPLAY & ISSUE @ASG,T XA. CARD   @F@@@@          L         A0,CORE   EU
)@@G@@        GET AMOUNT OF CORE NEEDED   @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,CV    EV
)@@G@@        CONVERT TO FD DECIMAL @ @@@@          SSC       A2,24     @E@@@@EW
)@@G@@          S,T2      A2,ASGCOR+3       STORE IN ASG IMAGE    @B@@@@      EX
)@@G@@    L         A1,(ASGCORL,ASGCOR) . @G@@@@          LMJ       A3,ISSUE  EY
)@@G@@        DISPLAY & ISSUE @ASG,T R$CORE CARD@ @@@@          L         A10,EZ
)@@G@@SAV   @F@@@@          J         *RETURN           RETURN TO CALLING PROGFA
)@@G@@RAM   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SUBROUTINE TO DISPLAY AND ISSUE CSF$ RFB
)@@G@@EQUEST@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         ENTER WITH A1 = IMAGE LENGTH,ADDRESS  FC
)@@G@@ OR   -(IMAGE LENGTH,ADDRESS) @H@@@@.         A1 NEGATIVE INDICATES THATFD
)@@G@@ CALLER WISHES TO CHECK STATUS HIMSELF.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ISSUE     LMFE
)@@G@@A       A0,A1             RETRIEVE IMAGE LENGTH, ADDR @F@@@@          JZFF
)@@G@@        A4,ISSUE2         JUMP IF NOT SORTF-DRIVER USE@F@@@@          A FG
)@@G@@        A0,(2,0,0)        SET IN DOUBLE-LINE SPACING  @D@@@@          ERFH
)@@G@@        PRINT$            PRINT @ASG CARD @G@@@@          JN        A4,0FI
)@@G@@,A3           DON'T ER CSF$ IF 'X' OPTION IS SET@F@@@@          LMA     FJ
)@@G@@  A0,A1             RETRIEVE IMAGE LENGTH, ADDR @F@@@@ISSUE2    ER      FK
)@@G@@  CSF$              ISSUE THE @ASG CARD IMAGE   @F@@@@          JN      FL
)@@G@@  A1,0,A3           RETURN IF CALLER WANTS TO   @E@@@@.                 FM
)@@G@@                    CHECK STATUS HIMSELF  @F@@@@          JP        A0,0FN
)@@G@@,A3           OTHERWISE, RETURN IF OK.    @D@@@@ISSUE3    LMJ       A3,EFO
)@@G@@RR4           FORM ERROR MSG  @E@@@@          J         ERR4B           FP
)@@G@@  PRINT IT AND EXIT     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         CSF$ ERROR ENCOUNTERFQ
)@@G@@ED    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ERR4      L,U       A2,5              WOOPS, AN FR
)@@G@@ERROR @H@@@@          DSL       A0,3              CONVERT STATUS TO OCTAFS
)@@G@@L FOR MESSAGE.    @^@@@@          SSL       A1,3@ @@@@          JGD     FT
)@@G@@  A2,$-2    @A@@@@          A         A1,('000000')   @C@@@@          JZFU
)@@G@@        A0,ERR4A          DONE?     @E@@@@          S         A1,E(4)+6 FV
)@@G@@        SET IN RIGHT HALF     @^@@@@          J         ERR4@D@@@@ERR4A FW
)@@G@@    S         A1,E(4)+5         SET IN LEFT HALF@D@@@@          J       FX
)@@G@@  0,A3              RETURN TO CALLER@[@@@@.     @ @@@@ERR4B     L       FY
)@@G@@  A0,EE(4)  @D@@@@          J         PRTERR            PRINT ERROR MSG FZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         BINARY TO FIELDATA DECIMAL CONVERSION ROUTINGA
)@@G@@E:  INPUT IN A0,  @H@@@@.         OUTPUT LEFT-JUSTIFIED, SPACE FILLED INGB
)@@G@@ A2.  A3 = CHAR COUNT * 6.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@CV        SZ        A3  GC
)@@G@@              CONVERT FROM BINARY TO FIELDATA DECIMAL @A@@@@          L GD
)@@G@@        A2,('      ')   @ @@@@CV1       DSL       A0,36     @ @@@@      GE
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,10     @ @@@@          A,U       A1,060    @^@@@@      GF
)@@G@@    DSL       A1,6@^@@@@          A,U       A3,6@ @@@@          JNZ     GG
)@@G@@  A0,CV1    @ @@@@          J         0,X11     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     GH
)@@G@@    HANDLE REQUIREMENTS OF SMALL SORT     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@SMALL     JZGI
)@@G@@        A2,ERR0   @^@@@@          SZ        A1  @D@@@@          A,U     GJ
)@@G@@  A2,1791           ROUND UPWARD    @E@@@@          DI,U      A1,1792   GK
)@@G@@        CALC. XA SIZE IN TRKS @G@@@@          S         A1,XA           GL
)@@G@@  THIS IS THE XA FILE SIZE IN TRACKS@G@@@@          TG,U      A1,6      GM
)@@G@@        TEST FOR FEWER THAN 6 TRACKS.     @G@@@@          J         SM0 GN
)@@G@@              FILE IS GREATER THAN 5 TRACKS     @G@@@@          LSSL    GO
)@@G@@  A1,1              A1 NOW CONTAINS 2, 4, 6, 8, OR 10.@G@@@@          L,GP
)@@G@@U       A0,01226          0,2,2,1,1,2 (FORM 26,2,2,2,2,2)   @H@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@    SSC       A0,0,A1           SELECT CORE SIZE FOR 1,2,3,4, & 5 TRK XAGR
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SSL       A0,34             (IF XA IS 1 TRK, DO IN-CORE GS
)@@G@@SORT) @^@@@@          J         SM2 @E@@@@SM0       MI,U      A1,1792   GT
)@@G@@        GET CORE EQUIVALENT   @E@@@@          DI,U      A1,1000         GU
)@@G@@  WHAT IS THAT IN K?    @F@@@@          L,U       A0,1              (STAGV
)@@G@@RT WITH 2K OF CORE)     @H@@@@          L         A2,A1             NOW GW
)@@G@@FIND CORE NEEDED BY TRIAL AND ERROR @G@@@@SM1       AU,U      A0,1,A0   GX
)@@G@@        (A0) = CORE IN K -1K, (A1) = 2*C-1@H@@@@          MSI,U     A1,1GY
)@@G@@,A0           (A1) = C*(2*C-1).  ASSUMING DRUM BUFFER @F@@@@          A,GZ
)@@G@@U       A0,1                   OF 500 WORDS ( = 1/2 K)@H@@@@          TLHA
)@@G@@E       A1,A2             IS DRUM FOR THIS AMNT OF CORE ENOUGH?   @G@@@@HB
)@@G@@          J         SM1               NO, INCREASE CORE & TRY AGAIN.    HC
)@@G@@@B@@@@SM2       S         A0,CORE           YES.@F@@@@          J       HD
)@@G@@  CVXA              GO GENERATE @ASG,T CARDS    @D@@@@ERR0      TNZ     HE
)@@G@@  *0,X11            IS NREC = 0?    @^@@@@          J         ERR2@ @@@@HF
)@@G@@ERR1      L         A0,EE(1)  @ @@@@          J         PRTERR    @ @@@@HG
)@@G@@ERR2      L         A0,EE(2)  @ @@@@          J         PRTERR    @[@@@@HH
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.         XB MAX SIZE EXCEEDED@[@@@@.     @ @@@@ERR3      LMHI
)@@G@@J       X11,CV    @ @@@@          S         A2,E(3)   @ @@@@          L HJ
)@@G@@        A0,EE(3)  @ @@@@          J         PRTERR    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@HK
)@@G@@.         SORT REQUIREMENTS EXCEED AVAILABLE TRACKS   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@HL
)@@G@@ERR5      L         A0,A1     @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,CV    @ @@@@HM
)@@G@@          S         A2,E(5)+9 @ @@@@          L         A0,A10    @ @@@@HN
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,CV    @ @@@@          S         A2,E(5)+1 @ @@@@HO
)@@G@@          L         A0,EE(5)  @ @@@@          J         PRTERR    @[@@@@HP
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@.         XB REQUIREMENTS EXCEED AVAILABLE POSITIONS  @[@@@@HQ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@ERR6      L         A0,A1     @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,HR
)@@G@@CV    @ @@@@          S         A2,E(6)+1 @ @@@@          L         A0,XHS
)@@G@@B     @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,CV    @ @@@@          S         A2,EHT
)@@G@@(6)+7 @ @@@@          L         A0,EE(6)  @D@@@@          J         PRTEHU
)@@G@@RR            PRINT ERROR MSG @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ER MSCON$ (MSAHV
)@@G@@LL$) ERROR  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ERR7      SSL       A0,18             MOVEHW
)@@G@@ ERROR CODE TO S6 @F@@@@          AND,U     A0,077            MASK OFF EHX
)@@G@@XTRANEOUS BITS    @G@@@@          LA        A0,EE(7)          ASSUME MSAHY
)@@G@@LL$ BUFFER IS TOO SMALL @F@@@@          TNE,U     A1,027            IS THZ
)@@G@@HAT REALLY THE ERROR?   @E@@@@          J         PRTERR            YES,IA
)@@G@@ PRINT ERROR MSG  @F@@@@          LDSL      A0,33             MOVE UPPERIB
)@@G@@ DIGIT INTO A0    @E@@@@          LSSL      A0,3              ADJUST IN IC
)@@G@@SIXTH-WORD  @F@@@@          LDSL      A0,3              MOVE LOWER DIGITID
)@@G@@ INTO A0    @G@@@@          AA,U      A0,'00'           CONVERT ERROR COIE
)@@G@@DE TO FIELDATA    @D@@@@          SA,T1     A0,E(8)+4         STORE IN MIF
)@@G@@ESSAGE@F@@@@          LA        A0,EE(8)          GET ALTERNATE ERROR MSIG
)@@G@@G     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         PRINT ERROR MSG     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@IH
)@@G@@PRTERR    ER        PRINT$    @ @@@@          L         A10,SAV   @^@@@@II
)@@G@@          ER        ERR$@E@@@@          END.                        WALTIJ
)@@G@@ER GILBERT 7/4/71 ___1,1,A0           (A1) = C*(2*C-1).  ASSUMING DRUM BIK
)@@G@@UFFER @F@@@@          A,U       A0,1                   OF 500 WORDS ( = IL
)@@G@@1/2 K)@H@@@@          TL*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@@. @MFD SUMMARY PRINTING ROUTINIM
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. CALLED AT TERMINATION UNLESS SINGLE-FILE MODE IN
)@@G@@IS SET.     @G@@@@. ALSO CALLED BY 'PRINT' ROUTINE IF THE 'BREAK' FEATURIO
)@@G@@E IS TURNED ON    @G@@@@. AND THE NEW FILE DIFFERS FROM THE PREVIOUS FILIP
)@@G@@E IN THE SPECIFIED WAY. @G@@@@. IN THAT CASE, WE PRINT EACH LEVEL OF SUBIQ
)@@G@@TOTALS UP TO THE LEVEL AT     @ @@@@. WHICH THE BREAK OCCURRED.   @[@@@@IR
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@          AXR$      .   @G@@@@          CONFIG    .         IS
)@@G@@        DEFINE CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS   @D@@@@          EQUFS     .   IT
)@@G@@              DEFINE TAGS     @F@@@@TOTM01    'TRKS&:  FIXED=&'         IU
)@@G@@  TOTAL FIXED STORAGE ON-LINE @B@@@@TOTM02    '  REMOV=&  V-OPT=&  G-OPTIV
)@@G@@=&'   @B@@@@TOTM03    '  TOTAL BACKUP TAPE BLOCKS=&'  @E@@@@TOTM04    'FIW
)@@G@@ILES: TOTAL=&'            TOTAL FILES PRINTED   @F@@@@TOTM05    '  TAPESIX
)@@G@@=&'                 TOTAL CAT'D TAPES PRINTED   @ @@@@          ON      IY
)@@G@@  DSGUNL    @ @@@@UNL       '  UNL=&  TOTAL=&'  @ @@@@          OFF     IZ
)@@G@@  DSGUNL    @D@@@@PRT       FORM      12,6,18           PRINT$ FORM     JA
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @D@@@@GRAND     'GRAND TOTALS:'     JB
)@@G@@        FOR GRAND TOTALS@A@@@@GRANDP    PRT       2,$-GRAND,GRAND @^@@@@JC
)@@G@@TOTALS    'TOTALS FOR &'@#@@@@NON       'NON-&' @^@@@@WHAT      '??     JD
)@@G@@     '@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      2   @^@@@@BRK*      NAME    JE
)@@G@@  .   @ @@@@          +         P(1,1)    @ @@@@          J         P(2,JF
)@@G@@1)    @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@TOTTAB    BRK       'QUAJG
)@@G@@LIFIER   ' TOTFD2 @B@@@@          BRK       'FILENAME    ' TOTFD2 @B@@@@JH
)@@G@@          BRK       'PROJECT     ' TOTFD2 @B@@@@          BRK       'ACCJI
)@@G@@OUNT     ' TOTFD2 @B@@@@          BRK       'TYPE        ' TOTFD1 @B@@@@JJ
)@@G@@          BRK       'REEL        ' TOTFD1 @B@@@@          BRK       'BACJK
)@@G@@KUP      ' TOTFD1 @B@@@@          BRK       'PACKID      ' TOTFD1 @B@@@@JL
)@@G@@          BRK       'ASG-COUNT   ' TOTDECV@B@@@@  DO OLDMFD>0 , BRK 'EQUJM
)@@G@@IPMENT   ' TOTOCTV@B@@@@          BRK       'FCYCLE      ' TOTDECV@B@@@@JN
)@@G@@          BRK       'REF-DATE    ' TOTDATE@B@@@@          BRK       'CATJO
)@@G@@-DATE    ' TOTDATE@B@@@@          BRK       'DISABLED    ' TOTBIT @B@@@@JP
)@@G@@          BRK       'UNLOADED    ' TOTUNL @B@@@@MASSMSG   BRK       'MASJQ
)@@G@@S-STORAGE' TOTMASS@B@@@@TAPEMSG   BRK       'TAPE        ' TOTTAPE@B@@@@JR
)@@G@@          BRK       'REMOVABLE   ' TOTREM @B@@@@          BRK       'GOPJS
)@@G@@T        ' TOTBIT @B@@@@          BRK       'VOPT        ' TOTBIT @B@@@@JT
)@@G@@PRIMSG    BRK       'PRIVATE     ' TOTPRI @B@@@@PUBMSG    BRK       'PUBJU
)@@G@@LIC      ' TOTPUB @A@@@@TOTTABL   EQU       ($-TOTTAB)/3    @^@@@@FIXMSGJV
)@@G@@    'FIXED       '@#@@@@NONEMSG   '<NONE>'@^@@@@LODMSG    'LOADED      'JW
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       BRKOK     @#@@@@/$(1),TOT000* .   @ @@@@      JX
)@@G@@    ON        BRKOK=0   @H@@@@          LX,U      X4,0              BE SJY
)@@G@@URE WE'RE LOOKING AT GRAND TOTALS   @ @@@@          OFF       BRKOK=0   JZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @G@@@@          LX        X4,BRKCNT KA
)@@G@@        START WITH LOWEST LEVEL BREAK     @E@@@@          TNZ       BRKCKB
)@@G@@NT            ANY BREAKS SPECIFIED? @B@@@@          J         TOT100    KC
)@@G@@        NO  @]@@@@TOT010    . @D@@@@          TNZ       X4              KD
)@@G@@  GRAND TOTALS?   @B@@@@          J         TOT090            YES @C@@@@KE
)@@G@@          E$DIT     EDPACK            OPEN EDIT @D@@@@          E$MSG   KF
)@@G@@  TOTALS            START MESSAGE   @D@@@@          LA        A0,BRKCNT KG
)@@G@@        GET BREAK COUNT @G@@@@          ANA       A0,X4             NUMBKH
)@@G@@ER OF LOWER LEVELS TO SKIP    @G@@@@          MSI,H1    A0,BRKPNT       KI
)@@G@@  MULTIPLY BY LENGTH OF ENTRIES     @E@@@@          LX        X5,BRKPNT KJ
)@@G@@        GET TABLE POINTER     @G@@@@          AX        X5,A0           KK
)@@G@@  SKIP PROPER NUMBER OF ENTRIES     @G@@@@          LR        R4,X4     KL
)@@G@@        MOVE CURRENT BREAK LEVEL TO R4    @E@@@@          JGD       R4,$KM
)@@G@@+1            ADJUST FOR LOOP COUNT @F@@@@TOT020    LA,H2     A0,BRKSPECKN
)@@G@@,X5     GET 1ST 3 CHARS OF SPEC     @H@@@@          LX        X10,(3,TOTKO
)@@G@@TAB-3)  INITIALIZE SEARCH INDEX AND INCREMENT   @E@@@@          LR,U    KP
)@@G@@  R1,TOTTABL        SET SEARCH LENGTH     @E@@@@          SE,H1     A0,3KQ
)@@G@@,*X10         FIND SPEC IN TABLE?   @C@@@@          J         TOTWHAT   KR
)@@G@@        NO, USE ??@G@@@@          LA        A0,BRKVAL,X5      LOAD FORMEKS
)@@G@@R CONTENTS OF FIELD     @F@@@@          EX        2,X10             YES,KT
)@@G@@ JUMP TO PROPER ROUTINE @]@@@@TOTWHAT   . @G@@@@          TP        BRKLKU
)@@G@@OAD,X5        IS VALUE TWO FIELDATA WORDS (DL ?)@D@@@@          J       KV
)@@G@@  TOTWHAT3          YES, HANDLE IT  @B@@@@          E$FD1     ('SPEC  ')KW
)@@G@@        NO  @D@@@@          E$DECV    BRKSPEC,X5,S3     EDIT SPEC NUMBERKX
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$COPY    3,(' =    ')      SPACE OVER@G@@@@          DLKY
)@@G@@        A0,BRKVAL,X5      PICK UP VALUE AND MASK (IF ANY)   @D@@@@      KZ
)@@G@@    JZ        A1,TOTWHAT2       SKIP IF NO MASK @E@@@@          AND     LA
)@@G@@  A0,A1             MASK OFF PROPER BIT   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,0LB
)@@G@@              ASSUME BIT WAS NOT SET@D@@@@          TZ        A1        LC
)@@G@@        WELL, WAS IT?   @B@@@@          LA,U      A0,1              YES LD
)@@G@@@C@@@@TOTWHAT2  E$OCTV    .                 EDIT VALUE@E@@@@          J LE
)@@G@@        TOT060            GO ON TO NEXT LEVEL   @D@@@@TOTWHAT3  LX,U    LF
)@@G@@  X10,WHAT          POINT TO '??'   @H@@@@          J         TOTFD2    LG
)@@G@@        WE DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS, BUT PRINT IT  @]@@@@TOTFD2    . @E@@@@LH
)@@G@@          E$FD2     0,X10             EDIT KEY FIELD NAME   @C@@@@      LI
)@@G@@    E$SKIP    1                 SPACE OVER@E@@@@          E$FD2     BRKVLJ
)@@G@@AL,X5         EDIT FIELD CONTENTS   @C@@@@          J         TOT060    LK
)@@G@@        GO ON     @]@@@@TOTFD1    . @E@@@@          E$FD2     0,X10     LL
)@@G@@        EDIT KEY FIELD NAME   @C@@@@          E$SKIP    1               LM
)@@G@@  SPACE OVER@E@@@@          LA        A0,BRKVAL,X5      PICK UP FIELD VALN
)@@G@@LUE   @A@@@@          TE        A0,('      ')   @D@@@@          TNZ     LO
)@@G@@  A0                BUT IS IT ZERO? @E@@@@          LA        A0,NONEMSGLP
)@@G@@        YES, SO SAY '<NONE>'  @E@@@@          E$FD1     .               LQ
)@@G@@  EDIT FIELD CONTENTS   @C@@@@          J         TOT060            GO OLR
)@@G@@N     @]@@@@TOTDECV   . @E@@@@          E$FD2     0,X10             EDITLS
)@@G@@ KEY FIELD NAME   @C@@@@          E$SKIP    1                 SPACE OVERLT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$DECV    BRKVAL,X5         EDIT FIELD CONTENTS   @C@@@@LU
