)@@G@@IN1120    . @ @@@@          OFF       SNAPOK    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CHECVG
)@@G@@K IF SORT OF THIS SPEC IS DESIRED   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON      VH
)@@G@@  SORTOK    @D@@@@          TNZ       SRTHSP            SORT THIS SPEC? VI
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         IN1300            NO, GO ON @ @@@@          ONVJ
)@@G@@        OLDSTUFF  @ @@@@          LA,U      A1,-1     @C@@@@          TNVK
)@@G@@E,U     A0,'SIZ'          SIZE?     @F@@@@          SA        A1,TPT    VL
)@@G@@        YES, BETTER IGNORE TAPES    @ @@@@          OFF       OLDSTUFF  VM
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @G@@@@          TNZ       BRKTSP    VN
)@@G@@        IS BREAK-THIS-SPEC CLEAR, AND     @ @@@@          OFF       BRKOVO
)@@G@@K     @D@@@@          TNZ       BPT               IS B-OPTION SET?@C@@@@VP
)@@G@@          J         IN1250            NO, GO ON @G@@@@.                 VQ
)@@G@@                    YES, IGNORE CERTAIN SORT KEYS     @D@@@@          LAVR
)@@G@@        A0,TB4BITS        GET CONTROL BITS@F@@@@          TEP,U     A0,TVS
)@@G@@BSORT         AUTOMATICALLY DONE BY B-OPT?@F@@@@          J         IN13VT
)@@G@@00            YES, JUST DO IT AT THE END  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CREATE SORVU
)@@G@@T KEY PARAMETER   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN1250    LA        A0,TB4ADS       VV
)@@G@@  GET ASSUMED SORT DIRECTION  @F@@@@          TNZ       SDTHSP          VW
)@@G@@  REVERSE SORT FOR THIS SPEC? @C@@@@          J         IN1252          VX
)@@G@@  NO, GO ON @F@@@@          TNE,U     A0,'D'            DESCENDING SORT VY
)@@G@@ASSUMED?    @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,'A'-('D'-'A')  YES, ADJUST VALUVZ
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@          AA,U      A0,'D'-'A'        REVERSE SORT DIRECTIONWA
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                     ('A' -> 'D' OR 'D' -> 'A')  WB
)@@G@@@F@@@@IN1252    SA,S3     A0,TEMPKEY        STORE A/D SORT INDICATOR    WC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,TB4TYP         GET KEY TYPE (ALPHA/BINARY) WD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA,S2     A0,TEMPKEY        STORE FOR SORT  @F@@@@      WE
)@@G@@    LA        A3,TB4J           GET ASSUMED J-DESIGNATOR    @G@@@@      WF
)@@G@@    TNZ,S5    ELT$              WAS A J-DESIGNATOR SPECIFIED?     @E@@@@WG
)@@G@@          J         IN1254            NO, USE ASSUMED J     @D@@@@      WH
)@@G@@    LA,H1     A0,ELT$+8         YES, PICK IT UP @E@@@@          LR,U    WI
)@@G@@  R1,JTABL          GET LENGTH OF J TABLE @E@@@@          LX        A3,(WJ
)@@G@@1,-1)         SET INDEX INTO J TABLE@D@@@@          SE,H1     A0,JTAB+1,WK
)@@G@@*A3     FIND SPEC'D J?  @B@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO  WL
)@@G@@@F@@@@IN1254    LA        A0,JMSBIT,A3      GET MOST SIG BIT FOR THIS J WM
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                     NOTE THAT 'BREAK' CODE BELOWWN
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                     ASSUMES J-DES IS IN LOWER A3WO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. MOST OF THE SPECS WITH ASSUMED VALUES HAVE SINGLE-BIWP
)@@G@@T VALUES AND@D@@@@. TESTS.  FOR THESE, WE WILL DO A SINGLE-BIT SORT.    WQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,0              ASSUME NO ADJUSTWR
)@@G@@MENTS NEEDED@F@@@@          TNZ       TB4VAL            ASSUMED VALUE FOWS
)@@G@@R THIS SPEC?@C@@@@          J         IN1260            NO, GO ON @E@@@@WT
)@@G@@          LA        A1,TB4OP          GET ASSUMED OPERATION @D@@@@      WU
)@@G@@    TE,U      A1,TOP            IS IT A TOP     @D@@@@          TNE,U   WV
)@@G@@  A1,TEP               OR A TEP?    @B@@@@          J         $+2       WW
)@@G@@        YES @E@@@@          J         IN1260            NO, SKIP THIS STWX
)@@G@@UFF   @F@@@@          LA        A2,TB4VAL         YES, PICK UP ASSUMED VWY
)@@G@@ALUE  @D@@@@          LSC       A1,A2             FIND FIRST BIT  @F@@@@WZ
)@@G@@          AN,U      A2,29             COMPENSATE.  IF THE VALUE   @F@@@@XA
)@@G@@.                                     IS 2**5 (040), A2=0 BECAUSE @G@@@@XB
)@@G@@.                                     THE MS BIT IS ALREADY CORRECT     XC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. NOTE THAT TB4VAL IS ASSUMED TO BE A 6-BIT FIELD     XD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          A         A0,A2             ADJUST THE MS BIXE
)@@G@@T     @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,1              FLAG SINGLE-BIT SORT  XF
)@@G@@@F@@@@IN1260    SA,S4     A0,TEMPKEY        STORE IN SORT KEY PARAMETER XG
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                     WORD 1 OF PARAM COMPLETE    XH
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A0,JBITS,A3       GET ASSUMED # BITS FOR THIS XI
)@@G@@J     @F@@@@          TZ        A2                BUT IS IT A SINGLE-BITXJ
)@@G@@ SORT?@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,1              YES, SO SET # BITS TO XK
)@@G@@1     @E@@@@          JNZ       A3,IN1270         IF PARTIAL WORD, GO ONXL
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TP        TB4BITS           FULL WORD:  REALLY 72 BITS? XM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,72             YES, SET FOR 72 BIT KEY     XN
)@@G@@@F@@@@IN1270    SA,H2     A0,TEMPKEY+1      SET # BITS IN SORT KEY PARAMXO
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LMJ       X10,IN1340        GET SORT RECORD WORD # IN A2XP
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        BRKOK     @F@@@@          LXI       A3,A2     XQ
)@@G@@        SAVE WORD # FOR BREAK, BELOW@ @@@@          OFF       BRKOK     XR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AA        A2,(0770000)      SORT WANTS 077 IN S1  @F@@@@XS
)@@G@@          SA,H1     A2,TEMPKEY+1      STORE IN PARAM AND INC INDEX@G@@@@XT
)@@G@@          LA        A2,KEYIDX         GET CURRENT INDEX INTO ADDKEYS    XU
)@@G@@@G@@@@          DL        A0,TEMPKEY        MOVE CONSTRUCTED KEY PARAMETXV
)@@G@@ER    @C@@@@          DS        A0,ADDKEYS,*A2    TO ADDKEYS@E@@@@      XW
)@@G@@    SA        A2,KEYIDX         RESET ADDKEYS INDEX   @ @@@@          ONXX
)@@G@@        BRKOK     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SET UP REMOTE EX INSTRUCTIONS FOR XY
)@@G@@'BREAK' FEATURE IF NEEDED     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TNZ       BRKTXZ
)@@G@@SP            BREAK THIS SPEC?@B@@@@          J         IN1290          YA
)@@G@@  NOPE@E@@@@          LA,U      A2,010*/4         'LA A0' INSTRUCTION   YB
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TP        TB4BITS           SHOULD IT BE 'DL A0'  @B@@@@YC
)@@G@@          LA,U      A2,(071*/4)+013   YES @D@@@@          LA        A0,JYD
)@@G@@FLAGS,A3      GET JDES FLAGS  @H@@@@          TOP,U     A0,JSPECIAL     YE
)@@G@@  IF IT'S A SPECIAL J-DESIGNATOR, DON'T   @F@@@@          AA,U      A2,,YF
)@@G@@A3               ADD IN SAVED J-DESIGNATOR@E@@@@          LSSL      A2,8YG
)@@G@@              LEFT-JUSTIFY IN H2    @G@@@@          AA,U      A2,X8     YH
)@@G@@        MAKE WRD # REL TO SORT RECORD     @E@@@@          LDSL      A2,1YI
)@@G@@8             ADD WORD # IN U FIELD @G@@@@          SSL       A3,18     YJ
)@@G@@        MOVE J INDEX BACK INTO POSITION   @F@@@@          LA,U      A4,0YK
)@@G@@              ASSUME 0 LEFT, 0 RIGHT SHIFT@E@@@@          TOP,U     A0,JYL
)@@G@@SPECIAL       SPECIAL J-DESIGNATOR? @C@@@@          J         IN1278    YM
)@@G@@        NO, GO ON @H@@@@          LA        A0,JMSBIT,A3      GET MOST SYN
)@@G@@IGNIFICANT BIT (BIT 35 = 1)   @H@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1            YO
)@@G@@  ADJUST LEFT SHIFT COUNT (0 = NO SHIFT)  @G@@@@          LSSL      A0,1YP
)@@G@@8             MOVE LEFT SHIFT COUNT TO UPPER A0 @F@@@@          LXM,U   YQ
)@@G@@  A0,36             GET WORD LENGTH IN LOWER A0 @H@@@@          ANA     YR
)@@G@@  A0,JBITS,A3       CALCULATE RIGHT SHIFT COUNT (0 = NONE)  @G@@@@      YS
)@@G@@    SA        A0,A4             SET LEFT,RIGHT SIFT COUNTS IN A4  @F@@@@YT
)@@G@@IN1278    LA        A3,( TE A0,2,*X5) GET A 'TE A0' INSTRUCTION   @F@@@@YU
)@@G@@          TP        TB4BITS           SHOULD IT BE A 'DTE A0'     @C@@@@YV
)@@G@@          LA        A3,( DTE A0,2,*X5)   YES    @F@@@@          LA      YW
)@@G@@  A1,TB4VAL         GET ASSUMED VALUE IF ANY    @F@@@@          JZ      YX
)@@G@@  A1,IN1280         SKIP IF NO ASSUMED VALUE    @F@@@@          LA      YY
)@@G@@  A0,TB4OP          YES, GET ASSUMED OPERATION  @C@@@@          TE,U    YZ
)@@G@@  A0,TOP            IS IT TOP?@C@@@@          TNE,U     A0,TEP          ZA
)@@G@@     OR TEP?@B@@@@          J         $+2               YES @D@@@@      ZB
)@@G@@    J         IN1280            NO, SKIP AHEAD  @G@@@@          LA      ZC
)@@G@@  A3,( LMJ X11,BRKBIT)  GET AN 'LMJ X11,BRKBIT' INSTR @D@@@@IN1280    LAZD
)@@G@@        A0,BRKPNT         GET TABLE INDEX @E@@@@          NOP       0,0,ZE
)@@G@@*A0           ADJUST FOR NEW ENTRY  @G@@@@          DS        A2,BRKLOADZF
)@@G@@,A0     STORE LOAD AND TEST INSTRUCTIONS  @G@@@@          SA        A1,BZG
)@@G@@RKMASK,A0     STORE SINGLE-BIT MASK IF NEEDED   @G@@@@.                 ZH
)@@G@@                    (CONTENTS IGNORED IF NOT NEEDED)  @G@@@@          LAZI
)@@G@@        A1,TB4SPEC,X9     GET 1ST 3 CHARS OF SPEC (FOR H2)  @F@@@@      ZJ
)@@G@@    LXI       A1,NSSP           GET SPEC NUMBER (FOR S3)    @F@@@@      ZK
)@@G@@    SA        A1,BRKSPEC,A0     STORE FOR SUBTOTAL HEADER   @F@@@@      ZL
)@@G@@    LA        A1,BRKHDG         GET NEW-HEADING-WANTED FLAG @D@@@@      ZM
)@@G@@    SA,S2     A1,BRKSPEC,A0     STORE THAT ALSO @G@@@@          SA      ZN
)@@G@@  A4,BRKSHFT,A0     STORE LEFT,RIGHT SHIFT COUNTS     @D@@@@          SAZO
)@@G@@        A0,BRKPNT         UPDATE INDEX    @F@@@@          BUMP,A0   BRKCZP
)@@G@@NT          . INCREMENT BREAK COUNT BY 1  @ @@@@          OFF       BRKOZQ
)@@G@@K     @F@@@@IN1290    TZ        TB4VAL            SPEC WITH ASSUMED VALUZR
)@@G@@E?    @F@@@@          J         IN1080            YES, USER WANTS SORT OZS
)@@G@@N IT, @F@@@@.                                     SO THAT'S ALL WE DO WIZT
)@@G@@TH IT @]@@@@IN1300    . @ @@@@          OFF       SORTOK    @F@@@@      ZU
)@@G@@    TNZ       TB4VAL            ASSUMED VALUE FOR THIS ITEM?@C@@@@      ZV
)@@G@@    J         IN1310            NO, GO ON @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DON'T PERMZW
)@@G@@IT USER TO OVERRIDE OPERATION, J-DESIGNATOR, ETC., FOR@B@@@@. THE SPECIAZX
)@@G@@L ITEMS WITH ASSUMED VALUES.  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          LA        A0,EZY
)@@G@@LT$           GET SPEC INDICATORS   @E@@@@          SSL       A0,6      ZZ
)@@G@@        MOVE (FCY)/RK/WK TO H2@G@@@@          TZ,U      0,A0            AA
)@@G@@  IF ANY OF THOSE ARE SPECIFIED,    @D@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECERAB
)@@G@@           SPEC ERROR   @D@@@@          TZ,S1     ELT$+1            VALUAC
)@@G@@E GIVEN?    @D@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        YES, SPEC ERROR AD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SR,S1     R15,ELT$+1        SET VALUE-GIVEN FLAG  @C@@@@AE
)@@G@@IN1310    TZ,S4     ELT$              OP GIVEN? @D@@@@          J       AF
)@@G@@  IN1330            YES, CONTINUE   @F@@@@          TZ        TB4OP     AG
)@@G@@        ASSUMED TEST FOR THIS ITEM? @E@@@@          TNZ,S1    ELT$+1    AH
)@@G@@        YES, WAS VALUE GIVEN? @F@@@@          J         IN1320          AI
)@@G@@  NO, HANDLE POSSIBLE ERROR   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOTE THAT THE ABOVE TEAJ
)@@G@@ST WILL NOT WORK PROPERLY IF THE ASSUMED  @B@@@@. TEST FOR AN ITEM IS TZAK
)@@G@@, TNZ, TP, OR TN. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          LA        A2,TB4OP        AL
)@@G@@  GET ASSUMED TEST INDEX@E@@@@          LA,H1     A0,OPCODE-1,A2    GET AM
)@@G@@PROPER OP CODE    @E@@@@          SA,H1     A0,ELT$+7         STORE AS IAN
)@@G@@F SPEC'D    @E@@@@          SR,S4     R15,ELT$          SET SPEC-GIVEN FAO
)@@G@@LAG   @D@@@@          J         IN1330            GOT OPERATION   @]@@@@AP
)@@G@@IN1320    . @ @@@@          ON        SNAPOK    @E@@@@          TZ      AQ
)@@G@@  SNTHSP            SNAP ONLY SPECIFIED?  @E@@@@          J         IN10AR
)@@G@@80            YES, NO VALUE   NO    @ @@@@          OFF       SNAPOK    AS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        SORTOK    @E@@@@          TZ        SRTHSP    AT
)@@G@@        SORT ONLY SPECIFIED?  @C@@@@          J         IN1080          AU
)@@G@@  YES, OK   @ @@@@          OFF       SORTOK    @G@@@@          LMJ     AV
)@@G@@  X10,SPECER        NO OPERATION, AND NOT SNAP OR SORT@[@@@@.     @D@@@@AW
)@@G@@. DETERMINE WHICH WORD OF DIRECTORY ITEM TO CHECK     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@AX
)@@G@@IN1330    LA        A0,TESTS          GET TEST COUNT  @H@@@@          MSAY
)@@G@@I,U     A0,SSIZE          ADJUST FOR SUPER SPEC TABLE ENTRY SIZE  @G@@@@AZ
)@@G@@          SA        A0,X6             STORE THAT IN X6 FOR TABLE INDEX  BA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,INITLOAD       GET INITIAL LOAD INSTRUCTIONBB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A0,SSLOAD,X6      STORE IN SUPER SPEC TABLE   BC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,INITTEST       GET INITIAL TEST INSTRUCTIONBD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A0,SSTEST,X6      STORE IN SUPER SPEC TABLE   BE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,POLNTH         GET INDEX INTO POLISH TABLE BF
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA        A0,SSLINK,X6      STORE LINK TO POLISH TABLE EBG
)@@G@@NTRY  @H@@@@          SZ        POLISH,A0         ZERO OUT THAT ENTRY INBH
)@@G@@ POLISH TABLE     @F@@@@          A,U       A0,1              INC POLISHBI
)@@G@@ TABLE LENGTH     @D@@@@          SA        A0,POLNTH         STORE NEW BJ
)@@G@@VALUE @E@@@@          LX,U      X10,IN1400        SET SUBROUTINE RETURN BK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. SUBROUTINE TO RETURN SORT RECORD WORD # IN A2, BASEDBL
)@@G@@ ON   @A@@@@. SPECIFIED+ASSUMED ITEM OFFSET.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     BM
)@@G@@  ENTER VIA:  LMJ  X10,IN1340 @ @@@@.                   <RETURN>  @[@@@@BN
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.        DESTROYS:  A0, A2, X10     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@IN1340BO
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,0              INITIALIZE WORD #     @E@@@@          LABP
)@@G@@,S3     A0,ELT$           FCYCLE CHAR COUNT     @E@@@@          JZ      BQ
)@@G@@  A0,IN1350         IF NONE, ASSUME WORD 0@^@@@@          TG,U      A0,3BR
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        MAX 2 CHARS     @E@@@@      BS
)@@G@@    AA,S1     A2,ELT$+6         1ST CHAR OF FCYCLE    @D@@@@          ANBT
)@@G@@,U      A2,060            STRIP OFF FD    @C@@@@          TP        A2  BU
)@@G@@              NEGATIVE? @E@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        IF NBV
)@@G@@OT NUMBER, ERROR  @C@@@@          TNE,U     A0,1              1 CHAR?   BW
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         IN1350            YES @E@@@@          MSI,U   BX
)@@G@@  A2,10             MOVE TO TENS PLACE    @D@@@@          AA,S2     A2,EBY
)@@G@@LT$+6         ADD UNITS DIGIT @D@@@@          ANA,U     A2,'0'          BZ
)@@G@@  STRIP OFF FD    @E@@@@IN1350    AA        A2,TB4WRD         ADD ASSUMECA
)@@G@@D OFFSET    @D@@@@          LA        A0,TB4ITM         GET ITEM INDEX  CB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          MSI,U     A0,28             POINT TO PROPER ITEM IN RECOCC
)@@G@@RD    @ @@@@          AA        A2,A0     @E@@@@          J         0,X1CD
)@@G@@0             RETURN WORD # IN A2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN1400    SA,H2   CE
)@@G@@  A2,SSLOAD,X6      STORE IN SUPER SPEC TABLE   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CHECCF
)@@G@@K FOR LEGAL OPERATION   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          LA,H1     A0,ELT$+7 CG
)@@G@@        GET OPERATION (RKEY)  @D@@@@          LR,U      R1,OPCODL       CH
)@@G@@  # OF OPCODES    @E@@@@          LA        A3,(1,0)          FROM OPCODCI
)@@G@@E TABLE     @C@@@@          SE,H1     A0,OPCODE,*A3     FIND?     @C@@@@CJ
)@@G@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO, ERROR @G@@@@          LA,U    CK
)@@G@@  A10,,A3           YES, KEEP OPCODE INDEX IN A10     @B@@@@          TECL
)@@G@@,U      A10,DTE           DTE?@D@@@@          J         IN1440          CM
)@@G@@  NO, CONTINUE    @E@@@@          TZ,S5     ELT$              J-DESIGNATCN
)@@G@@OR GIVEN?   @F@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        YES, CAN'T HAVE CO
)@@G@@J-DES ON DTE@E@@@@          TNZ,S1    ELT$+1            WAS A VALUE GIVECP
)@@G@@N?    @E@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO, MUST HAVE A VALUE CQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,INITDTE        GET INITIAL DTE INSTRUCTION CR
)@@G@@@G@@@@          AA        A0,X6             POINT TO PROPER SSPVAL TABLECS
)@@G@@ ADDR @F@@@@          SA        A0,SSTEST,X6      STORE IN SUPER SPEC TACT
)@@G@@BLE   @F@@@@          LA,H1     A0,( DL A0,0,X8)  GET A 'DL A0,X,X8' INSCU
)@@G@@TR    @E@@@@          SA,H1     A0,SSLOAD,X6      CHANGE 'LA' TO 'DL'   CV
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         IN1490            CONTINUE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@CW
)@@G@@. OPERATION IS NOT DTE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN1440    LA,S4     A0,OPCODE-CX
)@@G@@1,A3    GET OCTAL CODE FOR THIS OP  @G@@@@          SA,S1     A0,SSTEST,CY
)@@G@@X6      STORE IT IN REMOTE TEST INSTR     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CHECK FOR CZ
)@@G@@LEGAL J-DESIGNATOR, IF GIVEN  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          TZ,S5     ELT$DA
)@@G@@              J-DESIGNATOR (WKEY) PRESENT?@D@@@@          J         IN14DB
)@@G@@70            YES, HANDLE IT  @G@@@@          LA        A0,TB4J         DC
)@@G@@  NO, GET ASSUMED J FOR THIS ITEM   @E@@@@          JZ        A0,IN1490 DD
)@@G@@        IF FULL WORD, SKIP IT @C@@@@          J         IN1480          DE
)@@G@@  CONTINUE  @F@@@@IN1470    LA,H1     A0,ELT$+8         PICK UP SPECIFIEDF
)@@G@@D J-DES     @D@@@@          LR,U      R1,JTABL          LENGTH OF TABLE DG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A1,(1,-1)         SEARCH J-DESIG TABLE  @C@@@@DH
)@@G@@          SE,H1     A0,JTAB+1,*A1     FIND?     @C@@@@          LMJ     DI
)@@G@@  X10,SPECER        NO, ERROR @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,,A1          DJ
)@@G@@  A0 NOW CONTAINS J CODE@E@@@@IN1480    LA        A1,JFLAGS,A0      PCIKDK
)@@G@@ UP JDES FLAGS    @E@@@@          TEP,U     A1,JSPECIAL       SPECIAL J-DL
)@@G@@DESIGNATOR? @F@@@@          J         IN1490            YES, DON'T MODIFDM
)@@G@@Y SSLOAD    @F@@@@          LSSL      A0,8              MOVE J CODE INTODN
)@@G@@ POSITION   @F@@@@          OR,H1     A0,SSLOAD,X6      COMPOSITE LOAD IDO
)@@G@@NSTR IN A1  @G@@@@          SA,H1     A1,SSLOAD,X6      STORE BACK IN SUDP
)@@G@@PER SPEC TABLE    @D@@@@          SSL       A0,8              MOVE J BACDQ
)@@G@@K     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. OPCODE INDEX REMAINS IN A10 @[@@@@.     @G@@@@DR
)@@G@@. ASSUME SPECIFIED TEST VALUE IS FIELDATA, AND STORE IT.  IF NECESSARY, DS
)@@G@@@F@@@@. SET SHIFT VALUE (SSHIFT) TO PERMIT SPECS LIKE  MI0(7)/TE/S1.C  .DT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN1490    DL        A2,ELT$+9         GET SUPER SPEC EDU
)@@G@@LEMENT (VALUE)    @E@@@@          TNZ,S1    ELT$+1            IF NO VALUDV
)@@G@@E WAS GIVEN,@E@@@@          DSL       A2,72                USE ZEROES INDW
)@@G@@STEAD @D@@@@          DS        A2,SSPVAL,X6      STORE SPEC VALUE@H@@@@DX
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A10,DTE           DOES THIS SPEC REQUIRE A DOUBLE TEDY
)@@G@@ST?   @F@@@@          J         IN1800            YES, ALL DONE WITH THIDZ
)@@G@@S SPEC@H@@@@          LA        A1,JMSBIT,A0      GET MOST SIGNIFICANT BEA
)@@G@@IT (BIT 35 = 1)   @F@@@@          ANA,U     A1,1              ADJUST (0 EB
)@@G@@IF NO LEFT SHIFT) @E@@@@          SA,H1     A1,SSHIFT,X6      STORE LEFTEC
)@@G@@ SHIFT COUNT@G@@@@.                                     VALUE IS ALREADYED
)@@G@@ LEFT-JUSTIFIED,  @F@@@@.                                        SO DON'EE
)@@G@@T SHIFT IT NOW    @D@@@@          LA,U      A1,36             GET WORD LEF
)@@G@@ENGTH @G@@@@          ANA       A1,JBITS,A0       COMPUTE RIGHT SHIFT (0EG
)@@G@@ IF NONE)   @F@@@@          SA,H2     A1,SSHIFT,X6      STORE RIGHT SHIFEH
)@@G@@T COUNT     @F@@@@          LA        A3,JFLAGS,A0      PICK UP J-DESIGNEI
)@@G@@ATOR FLAGS  @E@@@@          TEP,U     A3,JSIGN          SIGN-EXTENDED J EJ
)@@G@@FIELD?@F@@@@          J         IN1492            YES, DO ALGEBRAIC SHIFEK
)@@G@@T     @G@@@@          SSL       A2,0,A1           NO, SHIFT VALUE RIGHT EL
)@@G@@LOGICALLY   @C@@@@          J         IN1494            CONTINUE  @G@@@@EM
)@@G@@IN1492    SSA       A2,0,A1           SHIFT VALUE RIGHT ALGEBRAICLY     EN
)@@G@@@E@@@@IN1494    SA        A2,SSPVAL,X6      STORE SHIFTED VALUE   @E@@@@EO
)@@G@@          TOP,U     A3,JSPECIAL       SPECIAL J-DESIGNATOR? @E@@@@      EP
)@@G@@    SZ        SSHIFT,X6         NO, ZERO SHIFT COUNTS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@EQ
)@@G@@. CHECK FOR MASK BEING SPECIFIED.  IF SO, SET MASK IN SUPER SPEC TABLE  ER
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LA        A0,INITMASK       GET INITIAL MASKES
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A0,SSMASK,X6      STORE IN SSMASK FIELD @E@@@@ET
)@@G@@          LA,S2     A3,ELT$+1         GET VERSION CHAR COUNT@E@@@@      EU
)@@G@@    JZ        A3,IN1600         IF NONE, ASSUME -0    @D@@@@          ANEV
)@@G@@,U      A3,1              LESS 1 FOR JGD  @G@@@@          LA,H1     A0,EEW
)@@G@@LT$+11        GET FIRST THREE CHARS OF VERSION  @C@@@@          TNE,U   EX
)@@G@@  A0,'FD '          'FD'?     @E@@@@          J         IN1500          EY
)@@G@@  YES, NO MASK GIVEN    @D@@@@          LA,U      A1,0              CLEAEZ
)@@G@@R RESULT    @F@@@@          LX,U      X2,ELT$+11        SUPER SPEC MASK FA
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @D@@@@          LX        X1,(1,0)          SET TABLE INDEX FB
)@@G@@@C@@@@IN1498    EX        ACLD,*X1          GET A CHAR@C@@@@          TGFC
)@@G@@,U      A0,060            NUMERIC?  @C@@@@          TG,U      A0,070    FD
)@@G@@        AND OCTAL?@D@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO, SPEC EFE
)@@G@@RROR  @E@@@@          LA        A2,A0             YES, MOVE CHAR INTO A2FF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LSSL      A2,33             SHIFT OFF FD    @E@@@@      FG
)@@G@@    LDSL      A1,3              ADD DIGIT ONTO A1     @E@@@@          JGFH
)@@G@@D       A3,IN1498            GET OTHER CHARS    @E@@@@          SA      FI
)@@G@@  A1,SSMASK,X6      STORE MASK IN TABLE   @C@@@@          J         IN16FJ
)@@G@@00            GO ON     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. VERSION FIELD SAYS 'FD' -- IFK
)@@G@@S THAT ALLOWED FOR THIS SPEC? @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1500    LA        A0,TFL
)@@G@@B4BITS        GET ITEM FLAGS  @F@@@@          TEP,U     A0,TBNUM        FM
)@@G@@  NUMERIC VALUE REQUIRED?     @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,SPECER      FN
)@@G@@  YES @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PICK UP SPEC'D VALUE, IF ANY, AND CONVERT IT IFO
)@@G@@F NECESSARY @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN1600    TLE,U     A10,TEP           TZ,TFP
)@@G@@NZ,TP OR TN OPERATION?  @E@@@@          J         IN1800            YES,FQ
)@@G@@ NO VALUE NEEDED  @F@@@@          TNZ       TB4VAL            SPECIAL ITFR
)@@G@@EM W/ASSUME VALUE?@C@@@@          J         IN1610            NO, GO ON FS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA        A1,TB4VAL         YES, GET ASSUMED VALUE@E@@@@FT
)@@G@@          SA        A1,SSPVAL,X6      STORE IN SSPVAL ENTRY @E@@@@      FU
)@@G@@    J         IN1800            ALL DONE WITH VALUE   @F@@@@IN1610    TNFV
)@@G@@Z,S1    ELT$+1            ANY ELEMENT (VALUE) GIVEN?  @E@@@@          LMFW
)@@G@@J       X10,SPECER        NO, MUST HAVE A VALUE @D@@@@          LA      FX
)@@G@@  A0,TB4BITS        GET ITEM FLAGS  @F@@@@          TEP,U     A0,TBFD   FY
)@@G@@        ALWAYS TREAT VALUE AS ALPHA?@F@@@@          J         IN1800    FZ
)@@G@@        YES, ALL DONE WITH THIS SPEC@E@@@@          TEP,U     A0,TBNUM  GA
)@@G@@        MUST SPEC BE NUMERIC? @F@@@@          J         IN1710          GB
)@@G@@  YES, HANDLE NUMERIC SPEC    @G@@@@          TOP,U     A0,TBDATE       GC
)@@G@@  DOES ITEM REQUIRE A DATE SPEC?    @G@@@@          J         IN1730    GD
)@@G@@        NO, COULD BE ALPHA OR NUMERIC     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CAT/REF DAGE
)@@G@@TE TEST     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1700    TZ,S2     ELT$+1            VERSGF
)@@G@@ION GIVEN?  @C@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        YES, ERROR@D@@@@GG
)@@G@@          LA,S1     A3,ELT$+1         ELT CHAR COUNT  @E@@@@          TEGH
)@@G@@,U      A3,6              6 CHARS (MMDDYY) ?    @F@@@@          J       GI
)@@G@@  IN1707            NO, MIGHT BE RELATIVE DATE  @G@@@@          SZ      GJ
)@@G@@  SSPVAL,X6         INITIALIZE SPVAL ENTRY TO ZERO    @D@@@@          LXGK
)@@G@@,U      X2,ELT$+9         POINT TO SPEC   @E@@@@          LX        X1,(GL
)@@G@@1,0)          INITIALIZE LOAD INDEX @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,IN1704GM
)@@G@@        CONVERT MONTH   @D@@@@          TG,U      A1,1              WITHGN
)@@G@@IN RANGE?   @ @@@@          TG,U      A1,13     @B@@@@          LMJ     GO
)@@G@@  X10,SPECER        NOPE@G@@@@          SA,S5     A1,SSPVAL,X6      YES,GP
)@@G@@ STORE MONTH IN SPVAL TABLE   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,IN1704      GQ
)@@G@@  CONVERT DAY     @D@@@@          TG,U      A1,1              WITHIN RANGR
)@@G@@GE?   @ @@@@          TG,U      A1,32     @B@@@@          LMJ       X10,GS
)@@G@@SPECER        NOPE@G@@@@          SA,S6     A1,SSPVAL,X6      YES, STOREGT
)@@G@@ DAY IN SPVAL TABLE     @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,IN1704        CONVGU
)@@G@@ERT YEAR    @E@@@@          AN,U      A1,64             ADJUST FOR MOD 1GV
)@@G@@964   @F@@@@          TG,U      A1,0              WITHIN REASONABLE RANGGW
)@@G@@E?    @ @@@@          TG,U      A1,25     @B@@@@          LMJ       X10,GX
)@@G@@SPECER        NOPE@F@@@@          SA,S4     A1,SSPVAL,X6      YES, STOREGY
)@@G@@ YEAR FOR TEST    @F@@@@          J         IN1800            ALL DONE WGZ
)@@G@@ITH THIS SPEC     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. DATE CONVERSION SUBROUTINE  @[@@@@HA
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IN1704    LA,U      A1,0              INITIALIZE RESULT     HB
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A3,1              FOR 2 CHARS     @D@@@@IN1706HC
)@@G@@    EX        ACLD,*X1          PICK UP A CHAR  @C@@@@          TG,U    HD
)@@G@@  A0,060            NUMERIC?  @ @@@@          TG,U      A0,072    @B@@@@HE
)@@G@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NOPE@E@@@@          AN,U      A0,0HF
)@@G@@60            YES, STRIP OFF FD     @ @@@@          MSI,U     A1,10     HG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          A         A1,A0             ADD TO RESULT   @D@@@@      HH
)@@G@@    JGD       A3,IN1706         DO BOTH CHARS   @F@@@@          J       HI
)@@G@@  0,X11             RETURN WITH RESULT IN A1    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SPECHJ
)@@G@@ MIGHT BE MONTH, DAY, OR YEAR-RELATIVE DATE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@DATJ  HK
)@@G@@    NOP       0,0,0             DAY @C@@@@          J         IN1708    HL
)@@G@@        MONTH     @B@@@@          J         IN1709            YEAR@[@@@@HM
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IN1707    TG,U      A3,2              CAN BE 1-4 DIGITS     HN
)@@G@@@G@@@@          TG,U      A3,6              PRECEDED/FOLLOWED BY M, D, OHO
)@@G@@R Y   @C@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO GOOD   @D@@@@      HP
)@@G@@    LX,U      X2,ELT$+9         ADDR OF SPEC    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. TRY HQ
)@@G@@M/D/Y IN 1ST CHAR FIRST @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          LA,S1     A2,ELT$+9 HR
)@@G@@        GET FIRST CHAR OF ELT @H@@@@          LX        X1,(1,1)        HS
)@@G@@  SET FOR NUMBER STARTING WITH 2ND CHAR   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. CHECK FOR HT
)@@G@@M/D/Y @[@@@@.     @C@@@@IN1707A   TE,U      A2,'M'            MONTH?    HU
)@@G@@@B@@@@          TNE,U     A2,'D'            DAY?@D@@@@          J       HV
)@@G@@  IN1707B           ONE OF THE ABOVE@C@@@@          TNE,U     A2,'Y'    HW
)@@G@@        OR YEAR?  @B@@@@          J         IN1707B           YES @[@@@@HX
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. CHAR IS NOT M/D/Y.  IF FIRST TIME THRU, TRY LAST CHAR.  ELHY
)@@G@@SE, ERROR   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TNZ,U     0,X1              FIRSHZ
)@@G@@T TIME THRU?@C@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        NO, ERROR @F@@@@IA
)@@G@@          EX        ACLD-1,A3         PICK UP LAST CHAR OF SPEC   @D@@@@IB
)@@G@@          SA        A0,A2             STORE IN A2     @G@@@@          JGIC
)@@G@@D       X1,IN1707A        TRY ALT FORMAT (M/D/Y AFTER #)    @[@@@@.     ID
)@@G@@@D@@@@. FOUND M/D/Y.  NOW CHECK FOR 1-4 DIGIT DECIMAL NUMBER@[@@@@.     IE
)@@G@@@D@@@@IN1707B   SSL       A2,3              D=1, M=2, Y=3   @F@@@@      IF
)@@G@@    AN,U      A3,2              ONE LESS CHAR, -1 FOR JGD   @D@@@@      IG
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,0              INITIALIZE TOTAL@F@@@@          LMJ     IH
)@@G@@  X11,IN1752        CONVERT DEC NUMBER TO BINARY@D@@@@          LMJ     II
)@@G@@  X10,SPECER        NOT DEC NUMBER  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SPEC IS CONVERTEIJ
)@@G@@D TO BINARY - RESULT IS IN SSPVAL,X6@[@@@@.     @D@@@@          ER      IK
)@@G@@  TDATE$            GET TODAY'S DATE@E@@@@          DSL       A0,24     IL
)@@G@@        GET MON,DAY IN A0     @D@@@@          SA,T3     A0,TODAY        IM
)@@G@@  STORE MON,DAY   @C@@@@          SSL       A1,30             GET YEAR  IN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA,S4     A1,TODAY          STORE YR IN YR,MON,DAY FMT  IO
)@@G@@@G@@@@          EX        DATJ-1,A2         JUMP TO PROPER ROUTINE FOR MIP
)@@G@@/D/Y  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@. DAY @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LA        A0,SIQ
)@@G@@SPVAL,X6      GET DAYS SPEC'D @E@@@@          DSL       A0,36           IR
)@@G@@  PREPARE FOR DIVIDE    @F@@@@          DI,U      A0,30             DIVIIS
)@@G@@DE BY # OF DAYS IN MONTH@D@@@@          LA,S6     A2,TODAY          CURRIT
)@@G@@ENT DAY     @E@@@@          AN        A2,A1             SUBTRACT # OF DAIU
)@@G@@YS    @D@@@@          TG,U      A2,1              NEG OR ZERO?    @B@@@@IV
)@@G@@          J         $+3               NO  @F@@@@          A,U       A2,3IW
)@@G@@0             YES, SET FOR PREVIOUS MONTH @E@@@@          A,U       A0,1IX
)@@G@@              ADD 1 TO MONTH COUNT  @E@@@@          SA        A0,SSPVAL,IY
)@@G@@X6      STORE MONTH COUNT     @D@@@@          SA,S6     A2,TODAY        IZ
)@@G@@  STORE NEW DAY   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. MONTH     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1708JA
)@@G@@    LA        A0,SSPVAL,X6      MONTH COUNT     @D@@@@          DSL     JB
)@@G@@  A0,36             SET FOR DIVIDE  @G@@@@          DI,U      A0,12     JC
)@@G@@        DIVIDE BY # OF MONTHS IN YEAR     @D@@@@          LA,S5     A2,TJD
)@@G@@ODAY          CURRENT MONTH   @E@@@@          AN        A2,A1           JE
)@@G@@  SUBTRACT # OF MONTHS  @D@@@@          TG,U      A2,1              NEG JF
)@@G@@OR ZERO?    @B@@@@          J         $+3               NO  @F@@@@      JG
)@@G@@    A,U       A2,12             YES, SET FOR PREVIOUS YEAR  @E@@@@      JH
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              ADD 1 TO YEAR COUNT   @D@@@@          SAJI
)@@G@@        A0,SSPVAL,X6      STORE YEAR COUNT@C@@@@          SA,S5     A2,TJJ
)@@G@@ODAY          NEW MONTH @[@@@@.     @[@@@@. YEAR@[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1709JK
)@@G@@    LA,S4     A2,TODAY          CURRENT YEAR    @E@@@@          AN      JL
)@@G@@  A2,SSPVAL,X6      SUBTRACT # OF YEARS   @B@@@@          TP        A2  JM
)@@G@@              NEG?@C@@@@          LMJ       X10,SPECER        YES, ERRORJN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA,S4     A2,TODAY          STORE NEW YEAR  @F@@@@      JO
)@@G@@    LA,H2     A0,TODAY          GET ABSOLUTE YR,MON,DAY     @D@@@@      JP
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SSPVAL,X6      STORE IN SPEC   @E@@@@          J       JQ
)@@G@@  IN1800            GO ON FOR NEXT SPEC   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. SPEC MUST JR
)@@G@@BE DECIMAL OR OCTAL NUMBER    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN1710    LMJ       X11,JS
)@@G@@IN1750        CONVERT OCT/DEC SPEC TO BINARY    @E@@@@          LMJ     JT
)@@G@@  X10,SPECER        NOT OCT OR DEC - ERROR@H@@@@          J         IN18JU
)@@G@@00            CONVERTED - ALL DONE WITH THIS SPEC     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@JV
)@@G@@. SPEC PERMITS ALPHA AS WELL AS OCTAL/DECIMAL NUMBER  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@JW
)@@G@@IN1730    TNZ,S2    ELT$+1            VERSION GIVEN?  @C@@@@          J JX
)@@G@@        $+4               NO, GO ON @E@@@@          LA,H1     A0,ELT$+11JY
)@@G@@        YES, GET 1ST 3 CHARS  @B@@@@          TNE,U     A0,'FD '        JZ
)@@G@@  FD? @E@@@@          J         IN1800            YES, DON'T CONVERT    KA
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LMJ       X11,IN1750        TRY OCTAL/DECIMAL NUMBER FIRKB
)@@G@@ST    @E@@@@          J         IN1800            FD - LEAVE IT AS IS   KC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         IN1800            CONVERSION DONE, SPEC STOREDKD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SUBROUTINE TO CONVERT OCTAL OR DECIMAL FIELDATA SPECKE
)@@G@@ TO BINARY  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1750    LA,S1     A3,ELT$+1         ELT KF
)@@G@@CHAR COUNT  @C@@@@          AN,U      A3,1              -1 FOR JGD@D@@@@KG
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1,0              CLEAR RESULT    @D@@@@          LXKH
)@@G@@,U      X2,ELT$+9         POINT TO SPEC   @F@@@@          LX        X1,(KI
)@@G@@1,0)          INITIALIZE LOAD TABLE INDEX @D@@@@          EX        ACLDKJ
)@@G@@,*X1          GET 1ST CHAR    @C@@@@          TE,U      A3,11           KK
)@@G@@  12 CHARS? @E@@@@          TNE,U     A0,060            OR FIRST CHAR = KL
)@@G@@0?    @E@@@@          J         IN1760            YES, ASSUME OCTAL     KM
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         $+2               NO, CONVEET DECIMAL   @[@@@@KN
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. DECIMAL VALUE   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@IN1752    EX        ACLDKO
)@@G@@,*X1          GET NEXT CHAR   @D@@@@          TG,U      A0,060          KP
)@@G@@  DECIMAL DIGIT?  @ @@@@          TG,U      A0,072    @D@@@@          J KQ
)@@G@@        0,X11             NO, ERROR RETURN@E@@@@          MSI,U     A1,1KR
)@@G@@0             YES, ADD TO RESULT    @ @@@@          AN,U      A0,060    KS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          A         A1,A0     @D@@@@          JGD       A3,IN1752 KT
)@@G@@        DO FOR ALL CHARS@E@@@@          J         IN1770            EXITKU
)@@G@@ WITH RESULT IN A1@[@@@@.     @#@@@@. OCTAL VALUE     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@KV
)@@G@@IN1758    EX        ACLD,*X1          GET NEXT CHAR   @D@@@@IN1760    TGKW
)@@G@@,U      A0,060            OCTAL DIGIT?    @ @@@@          TG,U      A0,0KX
)@@G@@70    @D@@@@          J         0,X11             NO, ERROR RETURN@D@@@@KY
)@@G@@          SA        A0,A2             YES, PUT IN A2  @D@@@@          LSKZ
)@@G@@SL      A2,33             SHIFT OFF FD    @E@@@@          LDSL      A1,3LA
)@@G@@              SHIFT DIGIT INTO A1   @D@@@@          JGD       A3,IN1758 LB
)@@G@@        DO FOR ALL CHARS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@IN1770    SA        A1,SSPVAL,LC
)@@G@@X6      STORE BINARY SPEC IN SPVAL TABLE  @D@@@@          J         1,X1LD
)@@G@@1             NORMAL RETURN   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ALL DONE WITH THIS SPELE
)@@G@@C     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IN1800    BUMP      TESTS           . INCREMENT LF
)@@G@@NUMBER OF TESTS   @F@@@@          J         IN1080            GO BACK FOLG
)@@G@@R MORE, IF ANY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NO FILENAME GIVEN.  CHECK FOR ELEMLH
)@@G@@ENT...MUST BE 'AND', 'OR', OR 'XOR' @[@@@@.     @E@@@@IN1850    TNZ,S1  LI
)@@G@@  ELT$+1            ELEMENT SPECIFIED?    @D@@@@          LMJ       X10,LJ
)@@G@@SPECER        NO, SPEC ERROR  @F@@@@          LA,H1     A0,ELT$+9       LK
)@@G@@  YES, PICK UP 1ST WORD OF ELT@E@@@@          LR,U      R1,POLOPL       LL
)@@G@@  GET LENGTH OF OP TABLE@D@@@@          LX        X10,(1,-1)        SET LM
)@@G@@POLOP INDEX @F@@@@          SE,H1     A0,POLOP+1,*X10   FIND ELEMENT IN LN
)@@G@@POLOP TABLE?@F@@@@          J         IN1108            NO, TRY IT AS SPLO
)@@G@@ECIAL ITEM  @F@@@@          LA,S5     A0,POLOP,X10      YES, GET PROPER LP
)@@G@@BIT FOR AOX @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PUT AND/OR/XOR/NOT FLAG IN PROPER WORD OLQ
)@@G@@F POLISH TABLE    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          OR        A0,AOX          LR
)@@G@@  ADD NEW BIT TO AND/OR/XOR/NOT BITS@G@@@@          SA        A1,AOX    LS
)@@G@@        STORE NEW AND/OR/XOR/NOT BITS     @F@@@@          LA,S4     A0,PLT
)@@G@@OLOP,X10      GET VALUE FOR POLISH TABLE  @G@@@@          LA        A1,PLU
)@@G@@OLNTH         GET CURRENT POLISH TABLE LENGTH   @H@@@@          SA      LV
)@@G@@  A0,POLISH,A1      STORE AND/OR/XOR/NOT IN POLISH TABLE    @D@@@@      LW
)@@G@@    A,U       A1,1              INCREMENT INDEX @E@@@@          SA      LX
)@@G@@  A1,POLNTH         STORE NEW TABLE LENGTH@F@@@@          J         IN10LY
)@@G@@80            CONTINUE - GET NEXT SPEC    @^@@@@          OFF       NSSPLZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@/.   IF SORT IS BEING DONE, TERMINATE SORT KEY PARAMETER TABLE.   MA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@IN1900    . @ @@@@          ON        SORTOK    @D@@@@MB
)@@G@@          TNZ       SORT              SORT BEING DONE?@B@@@@          J MC

)@@G@@          LA,XH1    A0,BRKPNT         PICK UP INITIAL BRKTBL INCREMENT VME

)@@G@@SPEC 1@C@@@@NOOP      NOP       0,0,0             NO SPEC1  @[@@@@.     MT
)@@G@@@G@@@@. MOVE ELT$ BUFFER INTO MFD$, SINCE THIS SEGMENT WILL SOON BE OVERMU
)@@G@@LAYED.@[@@@@.     @A@@@@          LA        A0,(1,ELT$)     @A@@@@      MV

)@@G@@ FOR SPEC2 VERSION@C@@@@          LMJ       X11,SINF$         PRESENT?  NA

)@@G@@RROR  @E@@@@          TNZ,S3    OPTIONS-6,A0      REVERSIABLE OPTION?   NJ

)@@G@@@E@@@@NOINF     ER        PRINT$            PRINT INFOR$ ERROR MSG@[@@@@NP

)@@G@@    J         IN2000            JUMP TO INIT2 ROUTINE @#@@@@          ENNR
)@@G@@D     ___     A2,KEYIDX         GET ADDKEYS INDEX     @D@@@@          TNNS
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. TAGS AND EQUF'S USED THROUGHOUT @MFD    NT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          $DEF      .                 SIGNIFY DEFINITINU
)@@G@@ON MODE ASSEMBLY  @F@@@@          $LEVEL    0,1,0             MAKE TAGS NV
)@@G@@EXTERNALLY DEFINED@H@@@@          AXR$      .                 DEFINE THENW
)@@G@@ REGISTERS FOR THIS ASSEMBLY  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. @MFD'S DEFAULT MODE HANX
)@@G@@NDLES THE MASTER FILE DIRECTORY FILE (MFDF)     @F@@@@. FORMAT IMPLEMENTNY
)@@G@@ED IN EXEC-8 LEVEL 33.  TO TURN OFF THE PRE-33  @B@@@@. MFD COMPATABILITNZ
)@@G@@Y CODE, SET OLDMFD TO 0.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@OLDMFD    EQU       1         OA
)@@G@@        OLD DIRECTORY COMPATABILITY MODE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OLDSTUFF  EQOB
)@@G@@U       1                 SET TO ZERO TO TURN OFF ALL @F@@@@.           OC
)@@G@@                          THE FUNNY OLD OPTIONS.  THE @F@@@@.           OD
)@@G@@                          D,G,O,R,T,U, AND V OPTIONS  @G@@@@.           OE
)@@G@@                          ARE REPLACED BY SUPER SPEC TESTS. @[@@@@.     OF
)@@G@@@G@@@@MBPTUA    EQU       0                 MUST-BE-PRIV-TO-USE-A-OPTIONOG
)@@G@@ FLAG @G@@@@.                                     IF NONZERO, THEN @MFD,OH
)@@G@@A SPEC  WITH@G@@@@.                                     SPEC NOT EQUAL TOI
)@@G@@O RUN'S ACCOUNT # @G@@@@.                                     WILL NOT BOJ
)@@G@@E ACCEPTED UNLESS RUN   @G@@@@.                                     IS POK
)@@G@@RIVILEGED.  IF ZERO, IT'S OK. @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. THE SPECIAL SPEC FIELDOL
)@@G@@ TESTS KNOWN THROUGHOUT THE CODE AS 'SUPER SPECS'     @G@@@@. MAY BEGIN OM
)@@G@@IN SPEC2 IF OLDSTUFF IS 0, OR SPEC4 IF OLDSTUFF IS > 0.     @F@@@@. THE ON
)@@G@@LASTSPEC PARAMETER (BELOW) DEFINES THE LAST SUCH SPEC FIELD.@D@@@@. IF SOO
)@@G@@ET TO 0, ALL SUPER SPEC CODE WILL BE TURNED OFF.@ @@@@. (THIS IS NOT RECOP
)@@G@@OMMENDED).  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@LASTSPEC  EQU       18                LASTOQ
)@@G@@ SUPER SPEC @D@@@@.                                     MAY BE 0 OR 2-? OR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@NSSP      EQU       (LASTSPEC>1);   @F@@@@            OS
)@@G@@       *(LASTSPEC-1)      # OF SUPER SPECS (0 IF NONE)@[@@@@.     @F@@@@OT
)@@G@@SNAPOK    EQU       1*NSSP            ZERO IF ITEM SNAP CAPABILITY@D@@@@OU
)@@G@@.                                     NOT DESIRED     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OV
)@@G@@SNAPSUB   EQU       1                 (IGNORED IF SNAPOK IS ZERO) @H@@@@OW
)@@G@@.                                     IF THIS PARAMETER IS NONZERO, A SNOX
)@@G@@AP$   @H@@@@.                                     SUBROUTINE WILL BE USEOY
)@@G@@D RATHER THAN     @H@@@@.                                     ER SNAP$. OZ
)@@G@@ THE SUBROUTINE HAS A NICER   @H@@@@.                                   PA
)@@G@@  OUTPUT FORMAT, ESPECIALLY FOR DEMAND.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SORTOK    EQPB
)@@G@@U       1*NSSP            0 IF SORT CAPABILITY NOT DESIRED  @[@@@@.     PC
)@@G@@@G@@@@SRTDBG    EQU       0                 NONZERO TO TURN ON SORT DEBUPD
)@@G@@G     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@POLDBG    EQU       0                 NONZERO TOPE
)@@G@@ TURN ON SUPER SPEC DEBUG     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NFILES    EQU       6000PF
)@@G@@              APPROX. NUMBER OF FILES (FOR SORT ONLY) @H@@@@.           PG
)@@G@@                          WILL USE HALF THIS NUMBER UNLESS THE    @H@@@@PH
)@@G@@.                                     Z-OPTION IS USED IN PRIVILEGED MODPI
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@PRVSEC    EQU       0                 SET NON-ZEPJ
)@@G@@RO TO HIDE SECURE @F@@@@.                                     BACKUP REEPK
)@@G@@L NUMBERS FROM    @E@@@@.                                     NON-PRIVILPL
)@@G@@EGED USERS  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DSGUNL    EQU       0                 SET PM
)@@G@@NON-ZERO TO DISGUISE THE@G@@@@.                                     FACTPN
)@@G@@ THAT FILES ARE UNLOADED BY   @F@@@@.                                   PO
)@@G@@  USING THE BACKUP BLOCK COUNT@F@@@@.                                   PP
)@@G@@  FOR THE TRACK COUNT AND     @F@@@@.                                   PQ
)@@G@@  ZERO FOR THE HIGH REFERENCE.@[@@@@.     @E@@@@PROJCK    EQU       0   PR
)@@G@@              SET NON-ZERO TO REJECT@F@@@@.                             PS
)@@G@@        ANY FILES WITH A PROJECT    @F@@@@.                             PT
)@@G@@        DIFFERENT FROM THE PROJECT  @D@@@@.                             PU
)@@G@@        IN THE PCT.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LEGEND    EQU       1         PV
)@@G@@        SET TO ONE IF A LEGEND@G@@@@.                                   PW
)@@G@@  OF SPECIAL CHARACTER MEANINGS     @D@@@@.                             PX
)@@G@@        IS DESIRED.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@BRKOK     EQU       1**SORTOK PY
)@@G@@        SET TO 1 IF 'BREAK' QUALIFIER IS ALLOWED.     @H@@@@.           PZ
)@@G@@                          PERMITS SORTED LISTINGS WITH SUBTOTALS. @[@@@@QA
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@BRKMAX    EQU       3                 MAXIMUM NUMBER OF NESTQB
)@@G@@ED BREAK'S  @F@@@@.                                     (IGNORED IF BRKOQC
)@@G@@K IS ZERO). @[@@@@.     @F@@@@BRKDBG    EQU       0                 (IGNQD
)@@G@@ORED IF BRKOK IS ZERO)  @H@@@@.                                     NONZQE
)@@G@@ERO TO TURN ON BREAK FEATURE DEBUG  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@MULTISYS  EQU     QF
)@@G@@  0                 MULTIPLE-SYSTEM FLAG  @F@@@@.                       QG
)@@G@@              IF NONZERO, TURNS ON CODE IN@G@@@@.                       QH
)@@G@@              INIT1 TO OBTAIN SYSTEM ID FROM    @G@@@@.                 QI
)@@G@@                    MCT, AND INCLUDE IT IN SIGNON LINE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@QJ
)@@G@@SYSTEMID  EQUF      021,,S6           SYSTEM ID OFFSET AND PARTIAL@G@@@@QK
)@@G@@.                                     WORD WITHIN MCT.  HAS NO EFFECT   QL
)@@G@@@E@@@@.                                     IF MULTISYS IS 0.     @[@@@@QM
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. @MFD'S DIRECTORY FILE ($$--DGET--$$) MAY BE QUITE LARGE.  QN
)@@G@@THE MSTITE  @H@@@@. PARAMETER (BELOW) PERMITS A SITE TO SELECT THE LEASTQO
)@@G@@ UNDESIRABLE METHOD     @^@@@@. OF HANDLING THIS FILE.@[@@@@.     @I@@@@QP
)@@G@@. WHEN MSTITE IS ZERO, THE DIRECTORY FILE IS NOT FREE'D AT PROGRAM TERMIQQ
)@@G@@NATION,     @H@@@@. BUT REAMINS USABLE BY THE NEXT @MFD CALL.  SITES WITQR
)@@G@@H LARGE DIRECTORIES     @H@@@@. MAY FIND THIS MODE UNACCEPTABLE BECAUSE QS
)@@G@@MANY DEMAND USERS MAY CALL @MFD     @F@@@@. AND WIND UP WITH LARGE DIRECQT
)@@G@@TORY FILES ASSIGNED AND FORGOTTEN.  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. IF MSTITE IS NONQU
)@@G@@ZERO, THE M-OPTION IS REQUIRED TO PREVENT THE DIRECTORY     @H@@@@. FILEQV
)@@G@@ FROM BEING FREED AT PROGRAM TERMINATION.  SITES WITH LARGE DIRECTORIES QW
)@@G@@@G@@@@. MAY FIND THIS MODE UNACCEPTABLE DUE TO THE NEED TO DO ANOTHER DGQX
)@@G@@ET$ IF@G@@@@. SUCCESSIVE @MFD CALLS ARE NEEDED AND THE M-OPTION WAS FORGQY
)@@G@@OTTEN ON THE@#@@@@. FIRST CALL.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MSTITE    EQU     QZ
)@@G@@  1                 MS AT A PREMIUM?@[@@@@.     @G@@@@WOPTOK    EQU     RA
)@@G@@  1                 SET NONZERO IF W-OPTION ALLOWED   @F@@@@.           RB
)@@G@@                          (PRODUCES SDF OUTPUT FILE)  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@RC
)@@G@@WFILE     EQU       'OUT$$$      '    SDF OUTPUT FILENAME (IGNORED IF   RD
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                                     WOPTOK IS ZERO. @H@@@@.     RE
)@@G@@                                12 CHARS, LEFT-JUSTIFIED, SPACE-FILLED  RF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@DGFILE    EQU       '$$--DGET--$$'    DGET$ FILENAME  RG
)@@G@@@H@@@@.                                     12 CHARS, LEFT-JUSTIFIED, SPRH
)@@G@@ACE-FILLED  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@DCFZ      EQU       0                 SET RI
)@@G@@NON-ZERO IF LEVEL OF EDIT$    @G@@@@.                                   RJ
)@@G@@  BEING USED HAS EDCFZ$ ROUTINE     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@GVHUSH    EQU     RK
)@@G@@  0                 0 = PRINT G AND V OPTIONS, AND    @E@@@@.           RL
)@@G@@                              INCLUDE IN TOTALS @H@@@@.                 RM
)@@G@@                    1 = PRINT G AND V OPTIONS, BUT ONLY     @G@@@@.     RN
)@@G@@                                    INCLUDE IN TOTALS IF RUN IS   @D@@@@RO
)@@G@@.                                         PRIVILEGED  @G@@@@.           RP
)@@G@@                          2 = NEVER MENTION G AND V OPTIONS @F@@@@.     RQ
)@@G@@                                    UNLESS RUN IS PRIVILEGED@[@@@@.     RR
)@@G@@@H@@@@EXTRA     EQU       1                 SET TO ZERO TO TURN OFF PRINRS
)@@G@@TING OF     @H@@@@.                                     ADDITIONAL LINESRT
)@@G@@ FOR FILES WHICH HAVE   @H@@@@.                                     LAPSRU
)@@G@@E ENTRIES OR MORE THAN 1 REEL, PACK,@D@@@@.                             RV
)@@G@@        OR BACKUP TAPE. @[@@@@.     @H@@@@CHKPCT    EQU       1         RW
)@@G@@        IF NONZERO, SINGLE-FILE ROUTINE WILL    @G@@@@.                 RX
)@@G@@                    USE INFORMATION FROM THE RUN'S PCT@I@@@@.           RY
)@@G@@                          TO AUGMENT ITS DREAD$/FITEM$ INFORMATION.     RZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@LDJOK     EQU       1                 (NO EFFECT IF CHSA
)@@G@@KPCT = 0)   @H@@@@.                                     IF SET TO 0, A 0SB
)@@G@@1000-WORD BUFFER WILL   @H@@@@.                                     BE RSC
)@@G@@ESERVED, AND ER PCT$ WILL BE USED   @G@@@@.                             SD
)@@G@@        RATHER THAN LDJ OF THE PCT BANK.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FATSIZ    EQSE
)@@G@@U       300               (NO EFFECT IF CHKPCT=0)     @H@@@@.           SF
)@@G@@                          FOR TEMPORARY REMOVABLE DISC FILES,     @H@@@@SG
)@@G@@.                                     PCT AND FATBL MUST BE SEARCHED TO SH
)@@G@@FIND  @H@@@@.                                     PACKIDS.  IF THIS CODESI
)@@G@@ IS NOT NEEDED,   @H@@@@.                                     SET FATSIZSJ
)@@G@@ TO 0.  OTHERWISE, SET TO     @G@@@@.                                   SK
)@@G@@  THE EXPECTED MSALL$ BUFFER LENGTH.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@PRVOPS    EQU     SL
)@@G@@    (1*/('Z'-'Z')); PRIVILEGED OPTIONS (0 IF NONE)    @B@@@@            SM
)@@G@@        ++(1*/('Z'-'C'));     @B@@@@                    ++(1*/('Z'-'Y'))SN
)@@G@@;     @A@@@@                    ++(1*/('Z'-'X'))@[@@@@.     @E@@@@WRNCHRSO
)@@G@@    EQU       '?'               WARNING-ONLY DISABLED @E@@@@HDWCHR    EQSP
)@@G@@U       '!'               HARDWARE DISABLED     @D@@@@BBTCHR    EQU     SQ
)@@G@@  '#'               BAD BACKUP TAPE @E@@@@BMICHR    EQU       '%'       SR
)@@G@@        BAD M.I. SECTOR 1 LINK@D@@@@LPSCHR    EQU       '>'             SS
)@@G@@  LAPSES EXIST    @E@@@@NOBCHR    EQU       '&'               FILE HAS NST
)@@G@@O BACKUP    @G@@@@DELCHR    EQU       '*'               FILE IS MARKED 'SU
)@@G@@TO BE DROPPED'    @E@@@@BNCCHR    EQU       '^'               BACKUP IS SV
)@@G@@NOT CURRENT @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OVHDA     EQU       'SYS$        '    SYSTSW
)@@G@@EM OVERHEAD ACCOUNT     @H@@@@.                                     12 CSX
)@@G@@HARS, LEFT-JUSTIFIED, SPACE-FILLED  @F@@@@.                             SY
)@@G@@        (FOR @MFD,X EXEC FILES)     @A@@@@/.        DEFINE EQUF'S AND STSZ
)@@G@@UFF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@RTOT      EQUF      BRTOT,X4          REMOVABLE TA
)@@G@@TRACK TOTAL @E@@@@VTOT      EQUF      BVTOT,X4          V-OPTION TRACK TTB
)@@G@@OTAL  @E@@@@GTOT      EQUF      BGTOT,X4          G-OPTION TRACK TOTAL  TC
)@@G@@@E@@@@TOT       EQUF      BTOT,X4           TOTAL FIXED TRACKS    @F@@@@TD
)@@G@@SECTOT    EQUF      BSECTOT,X4        TOTAL SECURE BACKUP BLOCKS  @E@@@@TE
)@@G@@UNLTOT    EQUF      BUNLTOT,X4        TOTAL UNLOADED TRACKS @[@@@@.     TF
)@@G@@@E@@@@VFCT      EQUF      CNT1,X4,H1        V-OPTION FILE COUNT   @E@@@@TG
)@@G@@GFCT      EQUF      CNT1,X4,H2        G-OPTION FILE COUNT   @D@@@@TFCT  TH
)@@G@@    EQUF      CNT2,X4,H1        TAPE FILE COUNT @F@@@@RFCT      EQUF    TI
)@@G@@  CNT2,X4,H2        REMOVABLE DISC FILE COUNT   @E@@@@UFCT      EQUF    TJ
)@@G@@  CNT3,X4,H1        UNLOADED FILE COUNT   @E@@@@PFCT      EQUF      CNT3TK
)@@G@@,X4,H2        TOTAL FILES SELECTED  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@LONGLIST  EQU     TL
)@@G@@  A7                1=LONG LISTING, 0=SHORT LISTING   @E@@@@BACKEDUP  EQTM
)@@G@@U       A13               FILE-IS-BACKED-UP FLAG@F@@@@RDISC     EQU     TN
)@@G@@  A14               REMOVABLE DISC FILE FLAG    @G@@@@FILESIZE  EQU     TO
)@@G@@  A15               TOTAL TRACKS FOR CURRENT FILE     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@TP
)@@G@@. SORT RECORD DEFINITIONS     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@LI0       EQUF      0,X8TQ
)@@G@@              LEAD ITEM STARTS SORT RECORD@E@@@@MI0       EQUF      28,XTR
)@@G@@8             MAIN ITEM SECTOR 0    @E@@@@MI1       EQUF      56,X8     TS
)@@G@@        MAIN ITEM SECTOR 1    @E@@@@SAVEAREA  EQUF      84,X8           TT
)@@G@@  TOT TRKS SAVE CELL    @F@@@@FLAGS     EQUF      85,X8             FLAGTU
)@@G@@S SORTED WITH FILE ITEMS@[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         POLISH NOTATION TRANTV
)@@G@@SLATION TABLE ENTRY VALUES    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@FALSE     EQU       0   TW
)@@G@@              OPERAND IS FALSE@D@@@@TRUE      EQU       1               TX
)@@G@@  OPERAND IS TRUE @F@@@@AND       EQU       2                 LOGICAL 'ATY
)@@G@@ND' OPERATION     @E@@@@OR        EQU       3                 LOGICAL 'OTZ
)@@G@@R' OPERATION@F@@@@XOR       EQU       4                 LOGICAL 'XOR' OPUA

)@@G@@ ITEM FLAGS @E@@@@.                                     (SAVED THROUGH SUD

)@@G@@                    (SAVED THROUGH SORT)  @D@@@@VFIL      EQUF      FLAGUH
)@@G@@S,,S5         V-OPTION FILE   @E@@@@BMI1      EQUF      FLAGS,,S6       UI
)@@G@@  BAD MAIN ITEM SECTOR 1@[@@@@.     @D@@@@SFMODE    EQUF      MRFLGS,,S1UJ

)@@G@@@F@@@@SNL0      EQU         001               SNAP LEAD ITEM SECTOR 0   UO
)@@G@@@F@@@@SNL1      EQU         002               SNAP LEAD ITEM SECTOR 1   UP

)@@G@@.                                     (SINGLE-FILE MODE ONLY)     @G@@@@VI

)@@G@@MODE ONLY)  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@MFD$F     EQUF      FLAG5,,S1         NEW VL

)@@G@@    PROC      2,3 @D@@@@BUMP*     NAME      0                 INCREMENT ZZ
)@@G@@PROC  @C@@@@INC*      NAME      0                 SAME THING@D@@@@DEC*  AA
)@@G@@    NAME      1                 DECREMENT PROC  @E@@@@A(0)      EQU     AB
)@@G@@  X11               ASSUME REGISTER TO USE@C@@@@A(1)      EQU       P(2,AC
)@@G@@1)            U FIELD   @C@@@@A(2)      EQU       P(2,2)            X FIAD
)@@G@@ELD   @C@@@@A(3)      EQU       P(2,3)            J FIELD   @G@@@@      AE
)@@G@@DO P(0)>1 ,A(0)  EQU  P(0,1)    USE SPEC'D REGISTER, IF GIVEN     @C@@@@AF
)@@G@@      L  A(0),P(1,1),P(1,2),P(1,3)    GET INPUT @E@@@@      DO  P(0,0)=1AG
)@@G@@ , GO DEC1          JUMP IF DECREMENT     @E@@@@      DO       P=2 , A,UAH
)@@G@@  A(0),1      INCREMENT BY 1, OR    @E@@@@      DO P>2 , A A(0),A(1),A(2AI
)@@G@@),A(3)  BY SOMETHING ELSE     @E@@@@      GO       BUMP1                AJ
)@@G@@  SKIP DECREMENT STUFF  @C@@@@DEC1      NAME      .                 DECRAK
)@@G@@EMENT @E@@@@      DO       P=2 , AN,U A(0),1      DECREMENT BY 1, OR    AL
)@@G@@@E@@@@      DO P>2 , AN A(0),A(1),A(2),A(3) BY SOMETHING ELSE     @^@@@@AM
)@@G@@BUMP1     NAME      .   @D@@@@      S  A(0),P(1,1),P(1,2),P(1,3)    AND AN
)@@G@@STORE RESULT@^@@@@          END       .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          ENAO
)@@G@@D       .   ___SSIGNED  @E@@@@HITRACK   EQUF      MI0+23,,H1        HIGHAP
)@@G@@EST TRACK WRITTEN @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         TAPE FILES ONLY     @[@@@@AQ
